Commentary: Southee begins with an outswinger! He delivers it on a fuller length outside off and gets it to swerve away a bit. Abdullah Shafique watchfully leaves. For how long will this movement last?
Tim gets closer to off stump with his attempted outswinger, the length remains full. This time Abdullah Shafique is forced to get forward and play at it. He does so and pushes it to covers.
Keeps it full and on middle, very little movement, Abdullah brings down a straight bat and defends it back.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Shafique once again covers the line and dead-bats it towards mid on.

Pakistan have their first runs on the board, although a bit streaky. Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique goes driving at it with hard hands and slices it through the gap at point. He collects a couple of runs to open his account.
Beauty from Southee. Hurls a length delivery around off and gets it to shape away a bit at the last moment. Abdullah Shafique is beaten all ends up while trying to defend the line of the delivery.
A gentle delivery from the aggressive man. On a length and outside off, it's left alone by Imam-ul-Haq.
Fuller and on off, Imam gets forward to meet the ball and defends it to the off side.
Angling in from a length around off, Imam sticks back and defends it ahead of his front pad.
FOUR! Imam-ul-Haq gets off the mark with a boundary. Neil Wagner offers width outside off, it's short in length as well, Imam latches onto it and whacks it through backward point.
Pitches it up and around off, in hope of some movement. There is none. Imam easily defends it off his front foot to mid off.
Edgy! Around off on a length, straightening a hint, Imam defends it from the outer portion of his bat to gully. It's a late call for no ball as Neil has overstepped.
Angles in a length ball around off, Imam covers the line and defends it solidly. This time it's the end of the over.
Sliding down the leg side, on a good length, Abdullah Shafique lets it go to the keeper.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

Edgy from Abdullah Shafique. This time Tim Southee serves an inswinger, Abdullah tries to defend but it takes the inside edge of his blade. The ball finds its way in the gap at square leg and Pakistan get another two runs.
Another inswinger and another inside edge. This time Abdullah's defensive blade has sent the ball directly in the direction of the mid-wicket fielder.

Southee is certainly getting some movement from this new ball. Nipping into the batter from a length around off, Shafique tries to defend but it takes the inside edge once more. The ball dribbles wide of the square leg umpire and they cross.
Full and around off, shaping away, Imam covers his stumps and allows it through.
What a delivery! Spin, definite spin. A nicely tossed-up delivery, around off, Abdullah Shafique draws forward to defend but it spins past his blade.
And again! Nice loop from Ajaz Patel, he gets the ball to turn away from around off and Abdullah is beaten while trying to defend off the front foot.

OUT! STUMPED! Early success for the Kiwis. This is beautiful bowling from Ajaz Patel. He immediately got into the rhythm. A couple of great deliveries beat the bat of Abdullah Shafique and Ajaz smartly drags his length a bit back on the third delivery and keeps it just around off. Shafique tries to use his feet to smother the spin but fails to reach the pitch of the ball. He tries to defend but again the ball spins past his blade and Tom Blundell wastes no time in flicking the bails off. Outstanding flight and length of the ball there and Abdullah Shafique was completely at sea.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Masood defends it from the back foot.

What's going on? Spinning back in from outside off, Masood advances forward to heave it over the leg side but it turns and hits him on the back pad. Shan can take his time, he has the skills to take care of the spinning deliveries.
Better from Masood. Uses the depth of his crease and punches it through covers for three runs.
Gets on the front foot and pushes it defensively to point.
Fuller and on off, defended back to the bowler.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it to covers.
Flighted and on off, Masood walks forward and tries to drive. Only slices it towards point. What's the rush?
Full and floated on off, defended to covers.
Bracewell begins with a maiden! Flighted delivery on off, Masood is forward as he defends it to short extra cover.
Tossed up, on off. Imam-ul-Haq advances forward and lofts it to long on. The fielder chases it well as the batters collect two runs.
Bowls it slightly shorter and on leg, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to square leg for a brace.
Outside off this time, Imam-ul-Haq punches it but finds the man at point.
Slower one on middle, Imam-ul-Haq prods forward and defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller one again with a hint of turn, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Close!

OUT! ANOTHER STUMPING! Hard to understand what Shan Masood was trying to do since his arrival at the crease. It's spinning and he was looking to use his feet to smother the spin but premeditation in charging the bowler is never a good idea, especially so early in the innings. Michael Bracewell sticks to his line just outside off and offers a good flight to his delivery. Shan Masood runs down the track to heave it across the line but the ball spins away to beat his bat. Just like Abdullah Shafique, Shan was also nowhere near the pitch of the delivery. Tom Blundell is once again alert with his glovework. Poor from Pakistan. The approach is questionable.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Babar Azam looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg. Lucky for Azam that it did not end up in the hands of the fielder at short leg.
Another fuller one as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Keeps bowling it fuller in length, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Quicker one on off, Babar Azam hangs back and blocks it to the man at mid off.
Tosses it fuller around the off. Babar strides forward and blocks it back at the bowler. A wicket maiden from Michael Bracewell.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to the fielder at square leg.
Turning in from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq hangs back and flicks it to the fielder at square leg.
Bowls it outside off, Imam-ul-Haq taps it to point. Another dot.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq covers the line and blocks it to square leg.
Goes fuller again, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and knocks it to the fielder at mid on.
This was similar to the last delivery, Imam-ul-Haq stays back this time and defends it to mid on. Another maiden over!
Fuller one turning in, Babar Azam prods forward and blocks it solidly.
Some extra bounce this time, Babar Azam defends it to square leg.
Bowls it fuller and on off, turning in, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it to mid off.
Slightly shorter, outside off. Babar fails to get any connection on the attempted cut shot.
Short of a length, this one spins back in. Babar Azam rocks back to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads as the ball bounces off the deck.
Fuller-length delivery on the stumps. Babar Azam steers it to backward point for a single.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it solidly.
Bowls it on leg this time, Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, on middle with some turn, Babar Azam looks to defend it but gets an inside edge towards square leg.
FOUR! This is good from the Pakistan skipper. Slightly shorter and on off, Babar Azam hangs back and punches it through mid on for a boundary!
Full and on the stumps, Babar Azam prods forward and defends it to the right of the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Babar Azam moves forward and pushes it to the man at mid on. Ends with a dot.
Flighted and full, around off, Imam skips down the track a shade and defends it to the off side.
Flatter through the air, full and on off, Imam stays back and defends it from the inner part of his blade.
A touch short and outside off, Imam goes on the back foot and guides it with the spin to backward point.
Fuller and on off, defended off the front foot to short mid-wicket.
Loopy and full around off, Imam leans forward and defends it with an angled bat to point.
FOUR! Nice shot! Tossed up around off, fuller in length, Imam-ul-Haq gives himself some room as he advances down the track and hammers it over wide mid off. Lovely footwork.
Floated one, full and drifting in around off, Babar defends it off his front foot.
Very full this time, around middle, Babar closes the face of his bat and defends it on the leg side towards mid-wicket.
Patel pulls his length back and lands it around off, Babar goes deep inside the crease and works it through the gap at mid-wicket. Gets a couple of runs.
Again the length is slightly short, around off, Babar hangs back to hit across the line but the short leg fielder gets his left hand to it and stops the ball partially.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller and off, defended off the front foot by Babar.
Quicker and fuller on off, Imam walks forward and defends it down on the track.
Fuller and on off, Imam lunges and defends it back in the direction of the bowler.

FOUR! Superbly timed! The initial call from Imam was for two runs but it races away to the fence. Short and around middle, skidding down, Imam-ul-Haq goes deep inside the crease and tucks it through backward square leg.

Shout for an lbw, not given! Michael Bracewell gets this one to skid into the batter from around off, Imam-ul-Haq advances down the track and tries to flick but misses. It hits him on the pads and rolls to first slip. The bowler puts in an unsuccessful appeal. Tim Southee doesn't go for the DRS.

FOUR! Fine shot! Imam-ul-Haq has looked good on the back foot. The length is short, around off, Imam goes back inside the crease and flicks it through the gap between mid on and mid-wicket and finds the boundary.
Fuller and outside off, Imam pads it away to negotiate this one. End of the over.
Fuller and on middle, defended back.
Loopy and full around middle, this time Babar jumps down the track and wrists it in front of square on the leg side. It races away and is retrieved near the fence. The batters get three runs.
Lunges to a full ball around off and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Imam defends it from the inner edge to short leg.

FOUR! Boundaries have started to come in the last few overs. Once again Imam-ul-Haq is quick to judge the length and use the depth of his crease. Short and on off, Imam smacks it through covers for a boundary.
Spinning down the leg side, the length is short and that's why Imam goes on the back foot in his attempt to flick it fine. Fails to connect. A good take by Tom Blundell.
Flighted and on off, Babar remains on the back foot as he defends it down in front of silly point.
Short and on off, turning in, Babar goes back and punches it to sweeper cover for a couple of runs. The Kiwi spinners are falling 'short' in their lengths in the last few overs.

DROPPED! What a big moment in this Test match! Michael Bracewell delivers it full and on off, Babar tries to drive but gets a fat outside edge towards Daryl Mitchell at first slip. It hits him high on the palms and slips out. Costly, very costly. We all know Babar's love for Karachi!
Goes on the back foot and wrists it towards mid-wicket for a quick run.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Are Pakistan trying to emulate 'Bazball'? If they are, somebody should tell them that they are failing miserably. Yet another questionable shot selection. Flighted delivery, full and on middle, Imam skips down to heave it across the line but gets it away from the outer portion of his blade. The ball flies towards mid off where Tim Southee is ready to gulp it in his safe hands. Trying to be over-aggressive against the spinners is costing Pakistan at the moment. They are 48 for 3 which could have been four had Babar been caught on the third ball of this over.
Howout: c Tim Southee b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Tossed up, on off with a hint of turn. Babar Azam defends it solidly.
This one lands outside off, Babar Azam reads it well and leaves the harmless delivery.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to mid off.
Slightly shorter this time, Babar Azam cuts it but finds the man at point.
Bowls it fuller on leg, on off. Babar Azam knocks it to long on for a brace.
Another fuller one with some turn, Babar Azam prods forward and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it away.
Fuller one again, Saud Shakeel blocks it solidly to the man at silly mid off.
Bowls it on middle with a hint of turn, Saud Shakeel looks to block it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards the short leg fielder.
Outside off, defended to the man at silly point.
Turning in from outside off, Saud Shakeel blocks it back towards the bowler.
Off the mark. Slightly shorter, on middle. Saud Shakeel works it to square leg for a brace.
Tossed up, on off. Babar Azam lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up, outside the off stump and the ball turns away, Babar shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam blocks it watchfully.
Tosses it up on middle, Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on off, Babar Azam moves forward and flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it outside off, turning in, Saud Shakeel lunges and defends solidly.
Over the wicket, full on middle, Babar Azam pushes it to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on off, this is again defended towards mid on.
Bowls it on off, Babar Azam eases it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Slightly short and outside off, slower too. Babar Azam rocks back and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Full and on off, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it out.
Short on a length and on off, Babar Azam punches it to deep cover. The fielder chases it as the batters collect three runs.
Fuller one on middle, Babar Azam eases it back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Babar Azam defends it to the man at silly point.
Touch fuller and on off, Babar Azam moves forward and nudges it towards deep mid-wicket. They collect a couple of runs.
Bowls it outside leg, Babar Azam lets it through towards the keeper.
Tosses it up on off, Babar Azam prods forward and blocks it away.
This one lands outside off, Babar Azam knocks it to the man at mid off. Patel ends with a dot ball.
Flighted one, full and on off, Shakeel defends it towards mid-wicket.
Presses forward to a full ball outside off and defends it towards silly point.
Short and wide outside off, Saud Shakeel rocks back and slaps it towards backward point. Ajaz Patel dives across to his left and takes the pace off the ball. Saves three runs.
Fuller and on off, Babar wrists across the line but finds mid on.
Loopy and full, landing around off, Babar gets forward and defends it watchfully.

FOUR! That's a lovely shot from Babar Azam, timing at its best. Michael Bracewell drops it short and on off, Babar goes back and waits for the ball to spin back in. As soon as that happens, he crunches it through cover-point for a boundary.
The leggie begins with a trademark short delivery outside off, Shakeel goes back and cuts it to deep point for a single.
Tossed up around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.

Appeal for an lbw! Not given. A late call from Tim Southee to review the decision. Coming to the delivery - Perhaps a flipper, landing short around off and skidding in, Babar Azam goes back to cut and seems to just keep it out ahead of his back pad. Sodhi appeals but to no avail. He convinces his skipper for the DRS. The replays show that it's pad first but Ball Tracking confirms that the impact is outside the line of the stumps. New Zealand lose a review.
Eases a full ball wide of the cover fielder for a single.
Tossed up around off, defended from the back foot to square leg.
Loopy and full, around middle, Saud flicks a bit aerially but wide of short mid-wicket. The mid on fielder mops it up.
Floated and full outside off, Babar is on the front foot as he pushes it in the gap at covers for a run.
Tossed up on middle, defended towards short leg.
Fuller and on off, driven past silly point to covers.
Turning away from a short length around off, it's worked wide of mid on for a single.
Full around off, flicked towards mid-wicket.
The length goes short and Babar goes inside the crease. He wrists across the line but again finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter on middle, skidding off the surface, Shakeel gets back and eases it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Bang! Sodhi delivers it short and around off, Babar pounces onto it and pulls it disdainfully to the deep mid-wicket fence. Babar is looking dangerous, in the mood to punish the Kiwis for that dropped catch.
Short and wide outside off, Azam cuts but finds the fielder at cover-pont.
Too full and on off, Babar lunges to defend and it goes off the inside edge to backward square leg.
Floated and full, around off, Babar calmly flicks it in the gap at mid-wicket for one.

Turning in from outside off, short in length, Shakeel goes back and dabs it down towards third man. The batters look good to fetch three runs but Babar Azam slips and they have to settle with a couple of runs.
Ajaz Patel begins his second spell from the opposite end with a full toss. Around off and Babar hits it towards deep mid-wicket for two runs.

FOUR! Not from the middle of the bat but it speeds away to the fence. A loopy full toss around off, Babar Azam forces it down the ground and the ball goes past mid on for a boundary. Is Ajaz Patel struggling to grip the ball after hurting his fingers while putting a dive in the field?
Tossed up on middle, defended back.
FOUR! Ominous signs for the Kiwis. Babar is motoring now. Advances down the track to a full ball and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Flighted and full on off, Babar is forward in defense.
Very full and on off, Babar keeps it out towards mid on. A good over for Pakistan.
Flatter and outside off, Saud Shakeel looks to drive but gets it away from the inside half of the bat. Luckily for him, the ball beats the stumps by a whisker.
Quicker and on off, Saud Shakeel eases it to backward point for a single.
Slightly shorter and on off, Babar Azam hangs back and punches it towards deep cover for a brace.
A low full toss on off, Babar Azam knocks it to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam pushes it to the fielder at mid on again.
Outside off, turning away from the batter, Babar Azam looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Close!
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel sweeps it straight to the man at square leg. Dot.
This one lands outside off, Saud Shakeel defends it towards the silly point region.
FOUR! Finds the gap this time. Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel reads it well and sweeps it in the gap through square leg for a boundary.
Turning in from outside off, Saud Shakeel defends it with his pads as the ball lobs towards slips.
Fuller and on middle with some turn, Saud Shakeel defends it solidly towards mid on.
Bowls it fuller again, Saud Shakeel dances down the track to heave it but miscues it to square leg. They collect one. Devon Conway seems to have hurt his knee in an attempt to stop the ball.
Flatter and on middle, Saud Shakeel works it to square leg for one. The 50-run stand comes up!

FOUR! Fifty up for Babar Azam, his 27th in Test cricket! A slightly shorter and slower one, Babar Azam rocks back and punches it past mid on for a boundary. He is a class act! New Zealand will be ruing the dropped catch even more now. 100 up for Pakistan as well.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length and outside off, Saud Shakeel slaps it but doesn't power it well enough to send it over the rope. It races towards deep cover. They collect three runs.
Bowls it outside off, turning away, Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Babar Azam covers the line of the delivery and leaves it alone.
Round the wicket, fuller and on middle, Saud Shakeel blocks it solidly.
FOUR! Another fuller one on off, shaping into the batter, Saud Shakeel opens the face of the bat and drives it through backward point for a boundary!
Bowls it fuller again, Saud Shakeel eases it to the man at covers.
Good length and on the middle stump line, Saud Shakeel defends it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel drives it but finds the man at covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another blow to Pakistan. Tim Southee strikes at the stroke of Lunch and it's yet another loose attempt from a Pakistan batter. This one is fuller and outside off at 132.6 kph, it moves away a tad at the last moment. Saud Shakeel looks to drive it but hits it uppishly towards Henry Nicholls at gully. He takes a comfortable catch and Pakistan lose their fourth wicket. Smart move from the skipper to bring himself on and also his strategy to get the batter driving pays off.
Howout: c Henry Nicholls b Tim Southee

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one as this is defended towards the fielder at covers.
Good length angling in, Babar Azam defends it to the man at mid on. They collect one.
Slightly short and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it to the fielder at mid-wicket.
FOUR! Sarfaraz Ahmed is off the mark in style. Tossed up, giving it some air, Sarfaraz Ahmed reads it well and knocks it through to long on for a boundary.
Fuller and on leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it solidly back towards the bowler. That will be LUNCH on Day 1.
Full and straight, Babar is firmly behind the line as he blocks it safely.
Sliding down the leg side, Babar clips it with great timing through backward square leg. Ish Sodhi puts in a dive near the fence and the batters collect two runs.
Around off, on a good length, Babar defends it from the back foot.
Pitches it up and around off, Babar defends it watchfully towards short cover.
Too straight in line from Southee, Babar flicks it through mid-wicket and the ball races away. Ajaz Patel chases it down and pulls it back just before the fence, saving one run for his team.

Almost a run out! Babar Azam survives. Length delivery outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes it to covers and sets off for a run. Babar responds but then Sarfaraz stops. The fielder has an immediate shy at the bowler's end but misses. Babar is safe but a direct hit would have got him despite of his dive. Sarfaraz Ahmed is quick to apologize to his skipper.
Skidding down the leg side, it's nudged away to fine leg for a couple.
Leans forward and defends a full ball to the off side.
Another one on the pads and Babar neatly deflects it down to fine leg. Daryl Mitchell chases and stops it just before the fence. Three runs taken.
Shortish and on off, Ahmed goes on the back foot and punches it to short cover.

FOUR! Second from the bat of Sarfaraz Ahmed. Full delivery down the leg side, Sarfaraz goes down with his sweep shot and rolls his wrists over it. Keeps it all along the ground as the ball speeds away to the fence at long leg.
Flatter around leg, defended from the back foot by Ahmed.
Full in length, around off and angling in, Babar plays near his front pad and defends it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Babar is quite watchful in his defense.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Length ball on the pads, Babar nudges it fine and the ball races away to the fence at fine leg.
Around off on a length, the batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Fuller on off, Babar flicks it to deep square leg and rotates the strike.
Fuller and on middle, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it solidly.
Tossed up, on middle. This is defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on middle and leg, Babar Azam defends it to short leg.
Pulls his length back and bowls it slightly shorter, on off. Babar Azam punches it to the man at extra cover.
Tossed up, on leg. Babar Azam knocks it to mid on for one.
This one is on the middle stump, Sarfaraz defends it off the front foot.
Bowls it outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes it to short cover.
Shorter and on off, Babar Azam leans back and leaves it alone.
On a length and outside off, Babar Azam covers his line and lets it go.
Good-length delivery, angling in, Babar Azam defends it solidly towards mid off.
Touch fuller and on leg, Babar Azam defends it to short cover.
Slightly shorter one, slower too. Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on middle and leg, this is again defended towards the bowler.
Slower one outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed sweeps it but doesn't connect well. It rolls towards backward square leg as the batters collect one.
Bowls it on middle, Babar Azam eases it to mid on.
Fuller and just outside off, Babar Azam lunges and defends it watchfully.
Another fuller one, Babar Azam leans forward to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards short leg. Dot.
Keeps bowling fuller in length, Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
Full and around off, Babar opens the face of the bat to push it to the man at extra cover. Ends with a dot.
On a length and on middle and leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it back towards the bowler.
Touch fuller this time, on middle. Sarfaraz Ahmed works it to backward square leg for one.
On a length again with some extra bounce. Babar Azam fends it back towards the bowler.
Full ball on the middle stump, Babar flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

This one lands down the leg side, Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to flick it but gets a rap on his pads and the ball rolls towards square leg. A stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They cross for a leg bye.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller one on off, turning in. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it to the man at short cover.
FOUR! Easy pickings. Errs his line and bowls a full toss down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed uses the pace of the ball and sweeps it through backward square leg for a boundary!
Fuller and on middle, Sarfaraz Ahmed sweeps it to square leg for one.
Another fuller one, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it out solidly.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam taps it to the man at mid off.
This one lands on leg, Babar Azam flicks it straight to the fielder at mid-wicket. Ends with a dot ball.
On a length and on off, this one keeps a tad low. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it watchfully.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bowls it down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and races away the fine leg fence for a boundary!
This one lands wide outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to put his bat to it but misses.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz pushes it to point for one.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Babar Azam flicks it to square leg for one.
Another length ball, this one shapes away a bit. Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it to the man at point and looks for a run. He is sent back.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and outside off, Babar Azam bends his back knee and caresses it through covers for a boundary!
Bowls it fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to mid on.
This one lands on middle, Babar Azam flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter one, slower too. Babar Azam reads it well and blocks it out.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam nudges it to the right of mid on for one.
Another fuller one, angling into the batter. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it back towards the bowler.
Angling away from the batter, on a length, Azam is not chasing it.
Quick run. Fuller in length, around middle and off, Babar bunts it towards mid off and rushes to the other end.
On a good length at 128.7 clicks but down the leg side, Sarfaraz Ahmed fails to get any wood behind it. Misses out.
Too full and too wide outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed lets it through to the keeper.
Neil Wagner switches to 'round the wicket and bowls a length ball outside off, Sarfaraz pushes it off the front foot to covers.
This one is angled in from outside off, fuller in length, Sarfaraz Ahmed walks forward and across before working it to short mid-wicket.
Short in length around off, at 133.5 kph, Babar stands back and pulls it past the diving square leg fielder for a single.
Southee goes full and around off, Sarfaraz doesn't take his front foot forward and just blocks it from the crease.
FOUR! Guided away! Width there outside off, on a good length, Sarfaraz Ahmed plays late and guides it past the gully fielder for a cheeky boundary. The 50-run stand comes up!
Some zip from the surface as it lands on a length around off at 132 clicks. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends from the back foot and does so from the inner part of his blade.
Full and on off, Sarfaraz defends it from the crease towards mid on.
Keeps it full and close to off, this time Ahmed is on the front foot as he defends it to short cover. 'Wait in' is the shout from him.
Wagner eyes a yorker from 'round the wicket but it ends up being a low full toss, Babar defends it back to the bowler.
Harmless delivery. Slightly short but down the leg side, Babar shoulders arms and then turns to watch the ball go into the gloves of Tom Blundell.
Down the leg side, Babar tickles it to deep square leg for a single.

Almost drags it on! Effort delivery from Wagner. It's short and around leg, Ahmed tries to pull but it takes the under-edge, deflects off the arms, and goes onto the thigh pad before nearly falling on the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed is lucky there!
Bouncer around leg, not rising much but Ahmed goes down low and ducks.
Down the leg side, Sarfaraz Ahmed leaves it alone and it goes swinging to the keeper.
Flatter and shorter on middle, Babar punches it to long on for a single.

'Catch it' is the shout... Nothing doing. Too full and around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed goes down low and sweeps and it hits the short-leg fielder on the right leg. The replays suggest that it was on the full but Tom Latham was ducking to save himself and was never in with a chance.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Walks down the track but is nearly beaten in the flight. Sarfaraz Ahmed adjusts well to push it towards the cover fielder.
Quicker and fuller around leg, Ahmed sweeps it down to fine leg for a couple of runs.
Loopy and full around off, Sarfaraz defends it by pressing forward.
On a length and down the leg side, Babar leaves.
Another delivery down the leg side, a bit of a negative line from Wagner, Babar is content in leaving it alone again.
Around middle and off, on a good length, Babar uses is bat and defends.
Back of a length around off, Babar is on his toes as he defends it down on the surface.
Short and on off, Babar pulls but finds one of the three fielders in front of square on the leg side.
Length delivery on leg, Babar helps it behind square leg and keeps strike with a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Babar Azam lunges and blocks it solidly.
Fuller one and on middle, Babar Azam covers his line and blocks it watchfully.
Fuller again, Babar Azam prods forward and blocks it to mid on.
Tosses it up on off, Babar Azam comes down the track and mistimes his lofted drive towards mid off.
This one lands down leg, Babar Azam tickles it towards fine leg for one.
Goes fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it to the man at mid off.
Shorter and on off, Babar Azam pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, Babar Azam flicks it too deep mid-wicket. The fielder has a long chase to do which he does. The batters collect two runs.
On a length and on off, Babar Azam pulls it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Short of a length and on off, Babar Azam pulls it again but once more finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
On a length and on leg with some extra bounce, Babar Azam defends it to mid on.
Short ball on the waist height, Babar Azam pulls it down to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to mid off.

SIX RUNS! Slightly shorter and on leg, Babar Azam flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a brace. The throw from the deep comes towards the striker's end where the short leg fielder collects and has a needless shy at the bowler's end. Ajaz fails to gather and it races away to the fence. Babar breaks into the 90s.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam pushes it to covers for one.
Fuller and around off, Ahmed sits down on one knee and sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
On off, this is defended towards mid off.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly shorter and on off, Babar Azam pulls it to square leg for one. He moves to 97 now!
Fuller one down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed knocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it to mid off.
Slightly shorter and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed knocks it to long off. The fielder has a long chase. They collect three runs.
Back of a length on the body of the batter, Babar Azam tucks it to short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter again, Babar Azam eases it to right of mid on. Ends with a dot.

Given caught behind and Sarfaraz Ahmed has immediately reviewed the decision. It's a length ball around middle and off, shaping away a shade, Sarfaraz Ahmed leans forward to work it across the line but it whizzes past his blade as he is squared up. There is some noise and they appeal. The finger goes up. DRS time. Nothing on the UltraEdge when it passes the bat and perhaps it clipped the pocket of Sarfaraz Ahmed. The on-field decision is overturned.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fuller one outside off, it shapes away a bit. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to play at it but gets an outside edge as the ball races away to the third man fence for a boundary!
Full-length delivery on the stumps. Sarfaraz knocks it to the man at mid on.
Another fuller one and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed lunges and defends it away.
On a length just outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it towards mid off. Ends with a dot.
Michael Bracewell returns to bowl for the first time in this session. Begins with a full ball around off, Babar gets forward and blocks it back.
Turning down the leg side, Babar gets back and works it off his pads. Finds square leg. Stays on 97.
Loopy and full around off, Azam is forward as he defends it off the inner edge to short leg.
Flighted and on middle, Babar dances down the track and flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
A dipping full toss outside off, Babar tries to slog-sweep but scuffs his shot off the inner edge to mid on. 'Koi baat nahi' shouts Sarfaraz Ahmed from the non-striker's end, meaning doesn't matter.
Short outside off, Babar hits across the line but finds mid-wicket. Maiden.
Controlled edge. Full and around off, Ahmed defends it with a loose bottom hand. It takes the outside edge and rolls to gully.
Bowls it very full and outside off, Ahmed digs it out to mid on.
Some reverse swing there. Nipping away from a length outside off, Ahmed shoulders arms.
Lands it on a length around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed is forward as he blocks it close to his body.
Fuller in length and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it with excellent timing but Michael Bracewell dives across to his left and makes a one-handed stop at short cover.
FOUR! Fine shot! Some reverse movement again but the line is too straight. It starts from middle and curves down the leg side, Sarfaraz Ahmed plays late and nudges it to fine leg for a boundary.

SIX! HUNDRED FOR BABAR and he reaches there in style. Loopy and full, landing around off, Babar goes down on one knee and smokes it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. 9th Test hundred for Babar Azam, his third in Karachi and after getting dropped on 12, he has played a gem of a knock. The crowd appreciates him by giving a standing ovation and Babar raises his bat to acknowledge the applause.
Full and outside off, Babar gets forward to drive but edges it down towards third man. They cross for a run. 200 up!
Flighted and outside off, knocked down to long on for one.
Turning in a hint from a fuller length around off, Babar defends off the front foot.
A touch short and outside off, Babar goes on the back foot and guides it with soft hands through point. A single is taken.
Loopy and full, wide outside off, Ahmed reaches out to drive but slices it towards point.
Serves it on a length around off, Babar defends it back from the crease.
Very full and outside off, Babar pushes off the front foot to short cover.
In the channel outside off, on a length, Babar makes a watchful leave.
Another delivery outside off, on a length and moving away late, Babar covers his stumps and allows it through.
Length ball on the pads, Azam wrists it through square leg for a single.
Fullish and around off, moving into the batter, Sarfaraz Ahmed has his bat down in time as he keeps it out towards short mid-wicket.
Floated full, around off, Babar defends it back off the front foot.
FOUR! Boom! Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Babar fetches it from there and smashes it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

EDGY FOUR! Michael Bracewell drags his length short and delivers it close to off, Babar goes back to punch but it takes the shoulder of his bat and hurries past Daryl Mitchell at first slip for a boundary. The century stand comes up!
Shortish and on off, Babar uses the inward spin and works it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Full and outside off, Babar presses forward to defend and pushes it away off the outer edge to point. They cross for a single.
Short and on off, turning into the batter, Ahmed hangs on the back foot and defends it down safely.
Neil Wagner comes back into the attack and bowls a fuller one wide outside off, Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Another one wide outside off, Babar Azam lets it through towards the keeper.
Touch fuller and outside off, Babar Azam gets into two minds but leaves it alone in the end.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to mid off.
Another fuller one, shaping away, Babar Azam blocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and outside off, angling away, Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Bowls it outside off, turning away, it keeps a tad low. Sarfaraz Ahmed guides it to backward point for a brace.
Fuller and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes it to covers for one.
Another fuller one on off, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it on middle this time, Babar Azam covers the spin and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it up and lands it fuller outside the off stump. Babar strides forward and drives it straight to the man at short extra cover.
Slightly shorter one, Babar Azam knocks it to mid on for a single.
Full and on off, Babar Azam drives it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Finds the gap. Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it in the gap through covers for a boundary!
This one lands wide outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed leaves the harmless delivery.
Bowls it outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it to covers for a single.
On a length and outside off, shaping away, Babar Azam leaves it alone. That will be TEA BREAK on Day 1.
Tossed up, on off. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it to the man at point.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed flicks it to short fine leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Babar Azam pulls it. The fielder at short mid-wicket manages to get his hand to it. The batters collect one.
Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it to covers for one.
Another fuller one, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it to the man at mid off.
This one lands wide outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed leaves it alone.
On a length and on middle, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it towards covers for a single.
Good-length delivery outside off. Azam leaves it alone through to Tom Blundell.
Fuller one this time, Babar Azam knocks it but finds the man at mid off.
Flighted and full, around off, Ahmed presses forward and pushes it defensively to short cover.
Was there some edge? Loopy and full outside off, turning away, Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to push at it but fails to connect cleanly. Tom Blundell fails to gather the ball. There was some noise.
Fullish and on off, pushed to covers. No ball called for overstepping.
Short around off, Ahmed goes back and pulls it wide of mid on for a quick run. Wagner has a shy at the bowler's end but misses as Sarfaraz Ahmed dives in.
Flatter and shorter on off, Babar goes back and punches it to mid on. He looks for a run but is sent back.
Shortish on off, turning away, Babar moves back and turns it through square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, some good loop on this one, Ahmed is forward in defense. He then stretches his right leg.
Fuller in length, around off, Babar pushes it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Angling away from the batter, on a good length, Babar shoulders arms.
This one is on a driving length outside off, Babar stays patient and lets it be.
Wagner serves it up and close to off, Babar is forward as he drives it towards mid off.
Fuller in length and around leg, Babar clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length outside off, Ahmed reaches out and strokes it to sweeper cover for one.
Sodhi serves it full and on middle, Ahmed flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Pitches it up and around off, Ahmed drives but finds short cover this time.
Loopy and full on off, Ahmed drives but straight to short cover again.

Slightly short and outside off, Ahmed delays his shot and guides it past backward point for a couple of runs. Sarfaraz Ahmed brings up his fifty, 19th in Tests and he is making his 50th Test special. Great return to this format so far.
FOUR! Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Ahmed tries to drive through covers but it gathers the outside edge and races away to the fence at third man.

Fuller and on off, driven back to the bowler who failed to collect the ball cleanly as he was too eager to mime a throw at the batter. Sarfaraz Ahmed wanted to pick a run but Babar Azam shouted 'na na na na na' ...meaning a straight no.
Harmless delivery, on a length and wide outside off, Babar leaves.
Another gentle delivery, in the zone outside off, Babar is not chasing it.
Another delivery which is quite full and quite wide outside off, Babar walks forward but then finds it futile to chase.
Wagner sticks to his line outside off, on a length, this time Babar makes no movement and just leaves it alone.
Makes the batter play. Wagner angles in a full ball around off, Babar presses forward and across before dead-batting it on the surface.
In the right channel outside off, Babar covers the line and offers no shot.
FOUR! Puts it away! Ish Sodhi delivers a rank long hop, around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed camps on the back foot and hammer-pulls it to wide long on for a boundary.
Flighted and outside off, a touch on the shorter side, Ahmed plays late and taps it wide of backward point for a single.
Short again from Sodhi, around off, Babar goes back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket. There is a fielder in the deep now, so only a run.
Quicker and flatter through the air, short and on off, Babar defends it from the back foot to covers.
Sodhi gives this one some extra loop and plants it on a fuller length outside off, Sarfaraz digs it out to point.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball around off and pushes it to mid off.
Good-length ball outside off, Babar lets it through to the keeper who is standing up to the stumps.
On a length and on off, Babar Azam taps it to point for one.
Half volley outside off, Sarfaraz pushes it to the deep extra cover region for a single.
Lands it on a length outside off, Babar leaves.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Babar Azam plays it with soft hands towards slips. Dot.
Shorter and on leg, Babar Azam leaves it alone. The keeper fails to grab it and the batters collect two byes.
Fuller one down the leg side, Sarfaraz Ahmed flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Babar Azam defends it to the man at mid on.
Another fuller one, on middle. Babar Azam works it to square leg for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it but finds the fielder at extra cover.
Full-length delivery angling into the batter, Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it to mid on.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it to mid off.
Touch fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to mid off.
Good-length delivery around off. Azam defends off the front foot towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed fends it to covers.
Fuller and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed prods forward and blocks it to short cover.
This one lands on leg, pace off. Babar Azam flicks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to the fielder at mid on.
Good-length delivery on off and middle, Babar Azam taps it to mid on.
Bowls it on off, Babar Azam drives it but finds the man at covers.
On a length angling into the batter, Babar Azam hangs back and blocks it to mid on.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam gets behind the line and defends it firmly down to mid on.
On a length and on middle, Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it to the mid on fielder.
Goes fuller and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it to deep cover for a single.
Bowls it on off, Babar Azam nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Fuller one on off, Babar Azam pushes it off the front foot to mid on.
Another fuller ball defended towards mid on by Babar Azam.
Full and on off, Babar Azam pushes it to the man at the cover region.
Back of a length outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed goes on his toes and plays it down towards point. Looks for a run but it's not available.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Ahmed reaches out and taps it down to the off side.
Fuller this time and in the line of the stumps, Ahmed covers the line and defends it from the inside part of his blade. It goes to short mid-wicket.
Some movement this time, tailing back in from a length around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it from the back foot.
Once again a length ball tails back into the batter, Sarfaraz Ahmed though is ready and blocks it safely.
Maiden! Serves it around middle, keeping a touch low, Ahmed has his eyes glued to the ball as he keeps it out safely on the on side.

Wagner bowls it from wide of the crease and delivers it on a length outside off, Babar drives through the line and shouts 'rehne do-rehne do' (let it be) as he sees the cover fielder charging across to stop the ball. He though fails to pick it up and they cross for a single.
Short on off, a controlled pull shot from Ahmed but he finds mid-wicket.
Fuller and straighter, Ahmed defends it back with a straight blade.
On a length and outside off, Sarfaraz reaches out and pushes it away towards the cover fielder.
Width there outside off, short in length, Sarfaraz Ahmed reaches out again and guides it to sweeper cover for one.
Wagner overcooks the line and sprays it on the pads, Babar Azam eases it to deep mid-wicket for a run. 3600 Test runs for Babar Azam and his average is now exactly 50.
Slants a length ball on middle, Babar defends it ahead of his front pad.
On the pads, it's clipped down to fine leg for a single.
Short and outside off, steered towards backward point for a brisk run. The 150-run stand comes up!
A touch short and on off, Babar stays on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fuller in length around off, Babar prods forward and eases it to mid off.
Length delivery on middle, Babar brings down a straight bat in defense.
Flatter around off, played from the back foot to covers.
Presses forward and defends it watchfully to covers.
Short and wide outside off, Ahmed cuts but without much conviction. Finds point.
Again the length is on the shorter side, outside off, Ahmed places his square cut past the diving point fielder for a run.
Fullish around off, the batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Fires a full ball on the pads, it's nudged down to fine leg for a couple.
Starts with a length ball on middle, shaping down, Sarfaraz Ahmed helps it towards square leg for a run.

Shout for an lbw! Again good inward shape from Daryl Mitchell but the line starts from middle and leg. Babar fails to flick and is hit on the pads. The appeal is not entertained, perhaps missing the leg stump. The batters pick a leg bye.
Fuller and on off, Ahmed forces it down to mid on where the fielder dived but failed to stop it cleanly. They crossed.
Full and around off, Babar drives it towards silly mid on.
Inswinger, from a length around off, Azam watchfully defends it on the leg side.
Keeps it full and in the line of the stumps, Babar blocks it safely. A decent first over from Daryl.
Tossed up, on middle. Sarfaraz Ahmed lunges and blocks it solidly.

Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives off the front foot but it hits the right leg of Latham at silly point and deflects in the direction of the stumps. Ahmed quickly returns inside the crease as Blundell tries to flick it onto the stumps.
Arm ball, around off and skidding in, Sarfaraz defends it off the inside half of his bat.
A touch short and on off, Ahmed gets back and punches it to mid off.
Quicker through the air, an arm ball on the shorter side, Sarfaraz Ahmed forces it to mid off.

Could easily have been a boundary. Shortish and on off, Ahmed punches it to deep point and it races away. Devon Conway puts in a sliding effort near the fence and pulls it back. In the process, he pushed the boundary cushion behind as well. Neil Wagner then retrieves the ball and returns it back into play. The third umpire has a look at a few replays and judges that it's cleanly done. To be honest, the ball was touching the marking below the cushion. Anyway, three runs added to the total.
Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed flicks it to mid-wicket for one.

On a length and on off, Babar Azam eases it to mid-wicket and scampers through for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. A direct hit would have been close! The replays show that Babar had to run around the bowler and that could have cost him his wicket. Nothing wrong that Daryl Mitchell did there as he stood his ground!
Good-length delivery, angling in. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed flicks it to backward square leg for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller one and on off, Babar Azam leans forward and caresses it through point for a boundary.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Babar Azam flicks it to the man at mid-wicket. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes it to the left of mid off and scampers through for a quick single.
Bowls it on off, Babar Azam taps it to covers for one again.
This one lands on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed hangs back and guides it to backward point for one more.
Full and on middle, Babar Azam defends it to square leg.
Tosses it up around off, some turn there, Babar Azam prods forward and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Babar Azam knocks it to the man at mid off.
Fuller one, on middle and leg. Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed hangs back and cuts it through backward point for a brace.
Slightly shorter one, slower too. Sarfaraz Ahmed rocks back and guides it to deep backward point for three runs.
EDGED AND FOUR! Short in length and outside off, Babar Azam looks to slap it square of the wicket on the off side but gets an outside edge. The ball races away to the third man fence. Lucky boundary!
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam pushes it to mid off for one.
Touch fuller and just outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it to the fielder at covers. Ends with a dot.
On a length and on off, Babar Azam knocks it to long on for one.
Fuller one, on off. Sarfaraz Ahmed works it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Another fuller one with some turn, Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to sweep it but gets a top edge as the ball flies over the man at short fine leg and lands safely. They collect two runs.
This one lands on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it back towards the bowler.
Short ball, spins away outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed cuts it down to deep point for a single.
Slightly shorter and on off, Babar Azam rocks back and cuts it but finds the fielder at point.

Bowls it full and wide outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed reaches out and drives it to sweeper cover for a couple. The new ball will come nicely onto the bat and these two are set batters. We can expect some quick runs here.
Serves it on a length around off, Ahmed is on the back foot as he defends it calmly to the off side.

Big appeal for an lbw! The umpire remains unmoved. Tim Southee looks at his keeper and then goes for the DRS. It's a full ball around off, shaping in a shade, Sarfaraz Ahmed gets half-forward to defend but misses and is rapped on the pads. They appeal unsuccessfully. The UltraEdge finds nothing. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's hitting the wickets. The on-field decision stays.
Delivers it on a good length, around off and shaping in, Ahmed defends it on the leg side.
Fuller and around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to push through the line but it takes the inside edge and rolls to short mid-wicket.
Drifting down the leg side, Ahmed fails to flick and Tom Blundell is a bit untidy in collecting the ball. They cross for a bye.
Too full in length around leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed goes down to sweep but doesn't time it well. Still, he pushes it towards the vacant square leg region and grabs a single.
Tossed up around middle, defended off the front foot to the leg side.
Loopy and full, around leg, Babar is forward as he defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Excellent footwork. Flighted delivery, landing full around off, Babar Azam dances down the track and lofts it inside-out over extra cover for a boundary.

Ajaz Patel fires in a quicker one, full and on middle, Babar knocks it down to long on for one. Gets to his second score of 150 or more in Tests! His best came against Australia at this very ground back in March - 196!
Floated and full around off, Ahmed defends it watchfully to end the over.
Hurls across a length ball in the channel outside off, Babar finds it too far away to play any shot. Leaves it alone.
Delivers it on a good length around off, Babar sticks on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Serves it on a length and outside off, some extra bounce, Babar defends it to the off side and then pulls back the bottom hand. Perhaps felt the vibration.
Keeps it full and targets the off stump, Babar is very composed as he defends it near his front pad.
A bit loose this time from Babar. He chases a length ball wide outside off and strokes it to deep cover. Collects a single.
Lands it on a length and around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed is behind the line of the delivery as he blocks it towards the cover region.
Tossed up around off, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted and full, around middle and skidding in, Babar is forward in defense but it takes the inner edge and rolls behind square leg. They cross.
Loopy delivery, pitching full around off, Ahmed drives it back to the bowler.
Too full and around leg, Ahmed flicks it to the right of mid-wicket and the fielder there quickly gets to the ball. Dot.
Fuller and on middle, defended back safely.
Slightly slower through the air, full and around off, Sarfaraz pushes it away with an angled bat towards cover-point. Looks for a run but it's not on.
Digs it in short, outside off, Babar leans back and allows it through to the keeper.
Around off, on a length, Babar hangs back and turns it in the gap at deep mid-wicket for one.
Lands a length ball around middle and gets it to drift down the leg side, Sarfaraz helps it towards square leg for a run.
Pitches it up and outside off, Babar plays a nice flowing drive but picks out the cover fielder.
Bowls it full and on middle, Babar brings his bat down and pushes it defensively towards wide mid on.
On a length around off, Babar is on the back foot as he keeps it out safely on the off side.
Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed knocks it straight to the man at mid on.
Bowls it on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it to short cover.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! This time Daryl Mitchell hangs onto it as he redeems himself. Ajaz Patel gives some extra pace on this delivery, serves it at 91.6 kph and gets it to drift in around off. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to drive this full ball with hard hands but all he manages is an outside edge. It goes quickly to Daryl Mitchell at first slip who takes a good low catch. The umpires get together to check whether it's a clean catch and refer it upstairs. The replays find that all is good and Sarfaraz Ahmed has to depart after a 196-run stand with Babar Azam.
Howout: c Daryl Mitchell b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Agha Salman knocks it to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman eases it towards mid off.
Fuller and around leg stump. Agha Salman lunges forward and turns it towards backward square leg. Ends with a dot.
FOUR! A full toss around off, Babar clobbers it wide of mid on and fetches himself a boundary.
Fuller and around off, Babar goes for the drive but gets an inside edge onto the boot.
Presses forward to a full ball and pushes it to covers.
Quicker and on middle, eased down back towards the bowler.
Floated and around off, Babar is on the front foot as he blocks it back to the bowler.
Fractionally short and on off, Babar goes on the back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for a brace.
Fuller and on middle, Agha stretches forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Fires it very full and on off, at 86 kph, Agha squeezes it out to point.
Leans forward and defends a full ball back to the bowler.
Skidding into the batter from around middle, Salman leans forward to defend and does so from the inside half of his blade.
And again. Another arm ball has been defended from the inner portion of the bat by Agha Salman.
Loopy and full around leg, Salman plants his front foot forward and defends it nicely.
Bowls it full and on off, Babar knocks it down to long on for a run.
Serves it full and wide outside off, Salman tries to defend the line but it takes the outside edge and rolls down to third man. They get a couple of runs.
Full toss on off, Salman drives but it hits the fielder at silly point and stays there.
Loopy and full on off, defended off the front foot.
Identical to the last delivery, again Salman draws forward in defense.
Quicker one on off, Salman defends it back towards the bowler.

GIVEN LBW! Babar Azam reviews the decision. Drama late in the day. Ajaz Patel serves a full ball around leg and gets it to spin away sharply. Babar Azam leans forward and tries to defend the line but it spins past his bat and strikes him high on the back leg. They appeal and the finger goes up. Nothing on the UltraEdge and Ball Tracking shows that it's heading over the stumps. The on-field decision is overturned and Babar survives much to the delight of the Karachi crowd.
Floated and full around off, Azam defends it off the front foot.
Very full and on off, Babar forces it down to long on for a single.
Flighted delivery, landing full and outside off, Salman defends it with an angled bat to point.
A low full toss this time, around off, Salman drives it back to the bowler who fails to stop it and they cross for a run. Babar on strike for the last ball...
Loopy delivery, pitching full and on middle, Azam defends it with a straight bat to end the over. STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Tim Southee starts the day from over the wicket. Good length delivery angling into the middle and leg line. Agha Salman tucks it to deep square leg for one.
On a length and outside off, Babar Azam leaves it alone.
Another one outside off, Babar Azam leaves it alone again.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Early success for New Zealand and they have netted the big fish. Babar Azam departs without adding anything to his overnight score. A lazy attempt from him. He kept his patience on the last two deliveries but goes for a waft at the third one. Southee has served it on a good length outside off at 127.4 clicks. To be honest, it's quite a harmless delivery, could have been easily left alone but the Pakistan skipper throws his hands at it and nicks it behind. Maybe, the scrambled seam offered Tim some extra lift from the pitch. Tom Blundell does the rest and New Zealand have an opening early in the day.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Tim Southee

Commentary: Around off, Ali defends it off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Nauman Ali once again defends it to the off side.
Flighted delivery, landing full around off, Salman is on the front foot as he defends it to covers.
FOUR! Too full in length and down the leg side, Salman goes down and calmly places his sweep shot to fine leg for a boundary.
Flighted and full, around off, Salman drives it through the line but finds mid off.
Gets forward to a full ball and defends it watchfully.
Loopy and full, around off, good lines now from Patel, Salman defends by prodding forward.
Tossed up, pitching around leg and skidding through, Salman tries to work it across the line but misses. He wears it on his pads.
Back of a length around off, Ali is on his toes as he defends it unconvincingly to the off side.
Full this time, outside off, Nauman Ali defends it to the off side from the outer portion of his bat.
Fuller again, around off, it's driven to covers.
Some extra bounce from a shortish length around off, Nauman sits on the back foot and guides it off the outer half to short third man for a run.
Full and on off, Salman is forward with an angled bat as he pushes it away to point.
Lands it full and around off, Salman is on the front foot as he strokes it to mid off.
Loopy and full, landing in the rough outside off for the left-hander, Nauman defends it off the front foot.
Flighted and outside off, Ali defends it from the outer edge to the off side.
Very full and on off, Ali goes hard at it and pushes it towards mid on without any timing.
Slower through the air, full and around off, turning in a bit, Nauman prods forward and blocks it towards cover-point.
Fuller and on off, defended solidly to silly point.
Puts it on a fuller length outside off, Ali gets forward and gently defends it to the off side. A quick maiden over from Patel.

FOUR! There is protection out there in the deep but it still races away. Full in length and wide outside off, Salman allows the ball to come close and drives it through backward point. The timing is crisp and it beats the fielder in the deep.
Outside off, on a length, guided wide of gully for a single.
Just short! Southee pitches it up and invites the drive. Nauman Ali slices it towards gully and it goes on one bounce to Daryl Mitchell.
From 'round the wicket, Southee gets a length ball to straighten from around off, Ali is caught pushing and missing inside the line.
Around off, on a length, angling in, Ali defends it from the back foot.
Quite wide this time from Southee, it's outside off and Nauman shows no interest in chasing it. Tim was trying to lure the batter there!
Flatter one, on middle and skidding in. Agha Salman lunges and defends it.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Agha Salman blocks it back towards the bowler.
Similar length, on leg. Agha Salman eases it to the man at mid on.
A shade short and outside off, Agha Salman slaps it but finds the fielder at point.
Back of a length again, Salman defends off the back foot back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller this time, slower through the air. Salman prods forward and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller in length, around off. Nauman Ali strides forward and pushes it firmly down to covers.
This one lands outside off, Nauman Ali leaves the harmless delivery.
Similar to the last delivery, outside off. Nauman Ali shoulders arms at it.
Fuller one, angling in. Nauman Ali blocks it to the man at mid off.
A low full toss, around off. Nauman Ali pushes it towards the fielder at short cover.
On a length and outside off, Nauman Ali lets it through towards the keeper.
Tossed up, outside off. Agha Salman pushes it but the ball deflects off the silly point fielder towards the keeper. Dot.
Another fuller one, this is defended towards the off side.
Tosses it up, full on middle and leg. Salman drives it straight back to the bowler.
Flighted up, on off. Agha Salman blocks it back towards the bowler again.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman defends it to the man at silly point.
Full-length delivery, on off. Salman lunges forward to push it towards short cover.
Fuller one, around off. Nauman Ali lunges and blocks it to mid off.
Bowls it fuller again, this is pushed towards the man at silly point.
Another fuller one, on off. Nauman Ali eases it towards silly point again.
Flighted up, on middle. Nauman Ali blocks it towards the off side.
Another fuller one is defended towards the fielder at silly point.
Flighted up, on off. Nauman Ali again defends it to the man at silly point.
Slower one on off, Agha Salman eases it to the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it fuller and outside off, Nauman Ali pushes it to the fielder at covers.
This one lands on off, Nauman Ali lunges and blocks it to silly point.
This one lands outside off, Nauman Ali covers his line and leaves it alone.
Fuller in length and outside off, Nauman hangs back and defends to the right of silly point.
Tosses it up outside the off. Nauman Ali drives it straight towards the fielder at short extra cover. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and on off, Agha drives firmly but finds extra cover. Pakistan have gone into a shell at the moment.
Floated one, landing full and on off, Salman blocks it off the front foot.
Full and outside off, Agha lunges and drives it to sweeper cover for a couple of runs.
Flighted and around off, Agha plays late and guides it through backward point for a run.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flighted and around off, full in length, Ali is forward as he defends it watchfully. Close to 45 minutes of play done where 11 overs have been bowled and Pakistan have managed only 15 runs.
FOUR! Agha Salman decides to show some intent. He jumps down the track to a full ball and drills it down the ground for a boundary at long on.
Loopy and full around off, Salman draws forward and defends it back.
Flatter and shorter on off, Salman goes back and punches it to point.
Flighted one, drifting in around middle, Agha is forward in defense.
Quicker and shorter on off, Salman gets back and pushes it to point.
A touch short on middle, Salman gets back and punches it down to mid on. Nauman Ali shows interest in a run but is sent back.
Very full and around off, Nauman drives it from the bottom part of his bat, towards the bowler.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it quietly back towards Bracewell.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball again and this time pushes it to covers.
Fuller on off, Ali drives and the silly point fielder jumps to evade the ball. The cover fielder is again in action to collect the ball.
Fires it in, full and on middle, it's defended back.
Lands it around off, breaking away a bit, Nauman stays on the back foot and taps it down towards silly point.
FOUR! Poor delivery and put away. It's tossed up nicely but the line is around leg and it's overpitched, Salman plays against the spin but whips it past mid on for a boundary.
Loopy and full, around off, Salman defends it back off the front foot.
Presses forward to a full ball again and defends it to silly point.
Very full and on off, Salman drives but finds the cover fielder.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Salman defends it well to the off side.
Slower again, at 77.8 kph, very full on off, Salman flicks but finds mid-wicket.
Pitches it up and around off, Ali is very watchful as he defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, again Nauman defends it solidly.
Fullish and on off, Nauman defends it off the inner half to the leg side.
Extra air on this one, landing full on middle, Nauman pushes it back defensively to the bowler.
Fires it very full and on off, Nauman keeps it out safely.
Slider this time, landing full around off and skidding back in, Nauman defends it next to his front pad. Another maiden for Bracewell!
Bowls it outside off, Agha Salman plays it uppishly but through the gap at covers. The fielder chases it as the batters collect three runs.
FOUR! Nauman Ali plays something different here. Fuller and on off, Nauman Ali sweeps this one all of a sudden through square leg for a boundary! He gets out of his shell.
Fuller and on off, Nauman Ali eases it towards silly point.
Bowls it outside off, Nauman Ali drives it but finds the man at extra cover.
Full ball on off, this is defended back to the bowler.
Another fuller one, Nauman Ali lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler again.
Fuller and on middle, Agha Salman covers his line and blocks it away.
This one lands on middle and leg, Agha Salman eases it towards the mid on fielder.
Fuller and outside off, Agha Salman lunges and blocks it towards mid off.
Overpitched on off, Salman puts a dead-bat back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman moves forward and knocks it to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman looks to block it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg. They collect one.
Flatter and on off, Agha Salman pushes it to covers for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Nauman Ali blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on leg, Nauman Ali tickles it to short fine leg and scampers through for a single.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on off, Agha Salman rocks back and whips it through wide mid on for a boundary.
Bowls it on off, Agha Salman knocks it to extra cover for one.
Fuller and on middle, Nauman Ali defends it to the man at short leg.
Tossed up, on off. Agha Salman eases it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman defends it to mid off.
Full ball and on middle, Agha Salman pushes it to the man at mid-wicket.
Tosses it up on off, Agha Salman lunges and defends it to the left of the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, on middle. Agha Salman guides it to point for a single.
Tosses it up on off, Nauman Ali hangs back and defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off, this one keeps a tad low. Agha Salman slaps it but finds the man at point.

Shout for an lbw, the finger stays down! Tim Southee has a word with his players and takes the DRS. This one appears to be a flipper which skids on after landing around middle. Salman gets forward to defend but it beats his pat and pings him on the front pad. The appeal is unsuccessful. DRS time! There is nothing on the UltraEdge and Ball Tracking shows that it's missing the leg stump. New Zealand have only one review left now.
Flatter and on off, Agha Salman prods forwards and defends it solidly.
Full ball and on middle, Salman plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller again, on off. Agha Salman pushes it to covers and scampers through for a quick single.
Another fuller one on off, Nauman Ali pushes it to the man at mid on. Ends with a dot.
Flighted and full on middle, Salman uses his feet and flicks but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Knocks a full ball down to mid on and scampers across for a quick run.
Drags his length short and delivers it on middle, Ali moves back and punches it towards the bowler.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Skidding in from around off, fuller in length, Nauman is forward as he defends.
Flighted and full on middle, Nauman clears his front leg and drives it towards mid on.
Flighted around off, Salman is on the front foot as he defends it to the off side.
Shortish and on off, Salman goes on the back foot and punches it towards the bowler.
Loopy and full on off, Salman lunges and blocks it safely.
Sodhi goes short and around off, Agha moves back and cuts but finds the fielder at cover-point.
Floated this time, full and around off, Salman draws forward and opens the face of his bat in defense. It rolls away to backward point.
Quicker one, short and on off, Salman forces it off his back foot and finds the gap at cover-point. Collects a single and retains strike.
Tossed up, full and around leg, Salman defends it on the leg side.
Full and on off, defended back with ease.
Slower through the air, full and drifting in around off, Salman again presses forward in defense.
FOUR! Wrong line. Turning down the leg side from around leg, Agha gets back to flick and gets some gloves behind it. The ball races away to the fence at fine leg.
OUCH! Flatter delivery, full and around leg. It shoots off the surface as Agha shapes up to defend. He misses and gets hit on the chin as the ball ricochets off his pads.
Shortish and on off, skidding away, Salman stays back to play late but the first slip fielder reacts quickly and stops the ball with a dive.
Too full and around off, Ali drives it back and the bowler fails to stop. The mid off fielder cuts it off.
Presses forward to a full ball and drives it to the right of the cover fielder for a single.
Tossed up, full and wide outside off, Salman reaches out and squeezes it towards backward point.
Fuller and on off, pushed away with an angled bat to cover-point.
This one goes straight on after landing around middle, Salman moves back and tucks it through square leg for a single.
Loopy and full, outside off, Ali is forward in defense.
Flighted around leg, Agha uses his feet and works it off his pads to deep mid-wicket. They cross for a single.
Loopy and full, around off, Nauman lunges and defends near his front pad.
Around off, full and skidding in, Ali is forward as he blocks it to the off side.
Too full and on middle, Ali pushes it back to the left side of the bowler.
Full and on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Puts it on a fuller length around off, Nauman again is content in blocking it off his front pad.
Sliding down the leg side, Salman gets back and helps it to fine leg for a run.
Tossed up, on middle and leg, Nauman Ali pushes it to mid on.
Turning in from outside off, Nauman Ali looks to cut it but misses. Close!
Fuller and on off, Nauman Ali lunges and blocks it away.
Full ball and on middle, Nauman flicks it with soft hands to the man at short mid-wicket.
Bowls it outside off, Nauman Ali moves back and pushes it to covers.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Agha Salman defends it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! 4th Test fifty for Agha Salman! Overpitched on middle, Agha Salman gets behind the line and knocks it past mid on for a boundary. A vital knock from him! The 50-run stand comes up as well.
On a length and on off, Agha Salman defends it to covers.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Agha Salman pulls it to backward square leg for one.

OUT! TAKEN! Excellent one-handed catch from Michael Bracewell. The short ball does the trick for Neil Wagner. Bowls it around off, Nauman Ali pulls it but doesn't get it away from the sweet spot of his bat. The ball flies towards square leg where Michael Bracewell takes a one-handed catch stretching to his left. Nauman Ali departs and the gritty stand has been broken at the stroke of Lunch!
Howout: c Michael Bracewell b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Shorter one just outside leg, Mohammad Wasim leaves it alone.
Slightly short, turning away, Agha Salman pulls it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman drives it to extra cover for one.
Slightly shorter and on off, Mohammad Wasim punches it to covers and wants a single. A bit of a mix-up between the batters and they decide not to take it in the end.
Tossed up, on off. Mohammad Wasim defends it to covers.
Bowls it on middle, Mohammad Wasim gets on his knee and scoops it over short fine leg for a brace.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A good reflex catch from the keeper. Ish Sodhi delivers it slightly short and on middle and leg, Mohammad Wasim looks for the scoop again but ends up gloving it behind. The ball lobs up in the air, and Tom Blundell reacts well to gather the catch safely.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Slightly shorter and on leg, Agha Salman pulls it to backward square leg and declines the single.
Another shorter one, slower too. Agha Salman pulls it to short fine leg. Doesn't take the single again.
Bowls it down leg, Agha Salman looks to pull it but misses.
Shorter and on leg, Agha Salman pulls it to deep backward square leg and takes one.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Mir Hamza defends it to the leg side.
On a good length with some extra bounce, Mir Hamza blocks it to short mid-wicket. Ends with a dot.
Bowls it outside off turning away, Agha Salman taps it towards the man at point.
Slightly shorter, with some extra bounce. Agha Salman gets back and dabs it towards gully.
Tosses it up on middle, Agha Salman defends it off the back foot and towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Agha Salman eases it to the man at point.
Fuller and on middle, Agha Salman sweeps it to square leg for one.
Fuller and on off, Mir Hamza looks to defend it but gets an inside half of his bat and the ball rolls towards the man at short leg. That will be LUNCH on Day 2.
FOUR! A good start to the session for Pakistan! Back of a length, around off and angling away, Salman rocks back and punches it sweetly down to long off for a boundary.
Shortish and down the leg side, Salman hits across the line and sends it to deep backward square leg. Denies the run.
Fraction short and on off, Salman goes on the back foot and forces it to covers.
A bit short and on off, Salman steers it through point for a single.
Wagner switches to 'round the wicket and slips a length ball down the leg side, Hamza tries flicking but misses.
Wide! A harmless delivery, short and down the leg side, Hamza leaves it alone. The umpire calls it a wide.
Shortish and on middle, Hamza hangs on the back foot and defends it to the leg side.
Floated and full, around off, Salman draws forward and defends it down safely.
FOUR! Edgy! Sodhi bowls a googly on the shorter side, around off, Salman rocks back to cut and does so very late. It takes the outer half and speeds down to third man for a boundary.
Quicker and fuller outside off, Salman tries to dig it out but gets it away off the bottom edge.The ball races down to third man and they take two runs.
Short around middle, turning down, Salman pulls it to long leg for a single.
Loopy and full around off, Hamza presses forward and blocks it to the off side.
Just wide! Sodhi gives this one some extra air and extracts some extra spin as well. Full and on off, turning in, Hamza looks to defend but it takes the inner edge and just eludes short leg.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Short in length, around leg and middle, Agha Salman steps back to make some room and slaps it through point for a boundary. Moves to 70.
Short in length again, around leg, Salman pulls it to fine leg where Ish Sodhi makes a sliding stop. No run taken.

Almost carried to the man at square leg. Back of a length, around middle, stopping a bit off the surface, Salman plays a half-hearted flick shot and it goes aerially in front of square on the leg side. Bracewell puts across a dive to his left but it goes wide of him.
Takes the single this time. Shortish and on middle, Salman guides it through point and hands the strike to Hamza.
Wagner keeps bowling short. Around leg this time, Mir fails to flick and it goes off his thigh pad to leg gully. Daryl Mitchell dives across to his left and stops the ball.
