Delivers it on a length around off, Mir stands back and defends it with a straight blade.
Play and a miss! Flatter leg spinner, turning away from the batter outside off, Agha tries to cut but misses.
Sodhi goes fuller and around off, Salman drives it to the cover fielder.
Loopy and full, landing around off, Salman pushes it gently through cover-point and declines the single.
Agha leans forward to a full ball and drives it square of the wicket on the off side. He picks up a single.
Fullish and around off, Hamza is forward as he blocks it towards silly point.
Mir does his job well. Defends another delivery off the front foot and survives the two balls.
Falls short! Back of a length down the leg side, Salman tries to paddle it away but it takes his gloves and goes on one bounce to the keeper.

FOUR! Smashing short! Wagner digs it in short, around middle and leg, Salman rides the bounce and rolls his wrists on the pull shot. Keeps it all along the ground as the ball speeds away through backward square leg. 400 comes up!
On middle, helped towards mid-wicket.
Another short ball, on middle, Salman pulls but finds square leg.

FOUR! Agha Salman is adding valuable runs to the total. Wagner comes from 'round the wicket and delivers a full ball around off, Agha leans forward and lofts it over extra cover. He wants his hundred.
FOUR! Another fine shot! Neil Wagner overpitches around off, Salman allows it to come to him and then drills it through cover-point for a boundary. Three boundaries from the over.
Tossed up, on off. Mir Hamza taps it to the man at covers.
A touch short and outside off, Mir plays late and places it past backward point. They cross for a run as Kane Williamson chases it down. Had they tried, they could have got three runs.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Agha Salman plays a reverse sweep in the gap through backward point for a boundary.
Another fuller one, on off. Agha Salman again reverse-sweeps but this time towards short third man. Takes a single.
Full ball on the middle, Hamza defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.

OUT! Given lbw! Mir Hamza has straightaway reviewed the decision. A tossed-up delivery, landing full around off and turning back in. Hamza prods forward to defend but is beaten and is rapped on the front pad. They appeal and the finger goes up. DRS time! There is no bat involved, confirms the UltraEdge and Ball Tracking shows that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's hitting the stumps. The on-field decision stays and Hamza returns after a vital 39-run stand with Agha Salman.
Howout: lbw b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Over the wicket, good length and on off, Salman clears his front foot and looks to go for an off drive but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. Denies the single.
This one lands down leg, Agha Salman shuffles across to play at it but gets a rap on his pads. Dot.
FOUR LEG BYES! On a length and down the leg side, Agha Salman looks to flick it but the ball brushes his pads and races away the fine leg fence for a boundary.
This one lands on off, Agha Salman drives it but finds the man at the covers.
FOUR! Well timed. Fuller and on off, Agha Salman reads it well and lofts it over mid off for a boundary. Great intent here by Salman as he breaks into the 90s.
This one lands on off, Agha Salman guides it to point for a single. He moves to 94 now!
Slightly shorter and on off, Agha Salman cuts it straight to the man at deep point and declines the single. What happened there? The bails have come off. Okay, it's off the keeper's gloves.
Full and on leg, this is defended off the front foot back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, driven to extra cover.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on middle, Agha Salman dances down the track and drills it through mid off for a boundary.

FOUR! MAIDEN TEST HUNDRED FOR AGHA SALMAN! What a moment for him! Short and on the pads, Salman moves to the back foot and pulls it to the deep backward square leg region for a boundary. It's been a great knock for him, especially for the way he stitched partnerships with the lower order. Babar is standing in the balcony applauding for him. The crowd is on its feet too. Well played!
On a length and on middle, Abrar Ahmed defends it to mid off.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Abrar Ahmed looks to play at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Dot.
This one lands outside off, Abrar Ahmed plays it with soft hands towards the man at slips.
Shorter and on leg, Abrar Ahmed leaves it alone.

SIX! Abrar Ahmed loves to swing his willow. Fuller and on middle, angling in, Abrar clears his front foot and powers it behind the bowler's head for a biggie. A big smile on Salman's face as he has a word with Abrar.
Lands it on a good length, around middle, Ahmed stands back inside the crease and defends it down on the leg side.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Agha Salman lunges and defends it solidly.
Sharp spin. Ajaz bowls it outside off, getting it to turn away, Agha Salman looks to defend it but misses.
Another fuller one on off, Agha Salman eases it to the man at covers.
Fuller and on middle, Agha Salman reads it well and gently sweeps it to backward square leg for one.
Tossed up, slower through the air. Abrar Ahmed prods forward and defends it solidly.
Bowls it on off, Abrar Ahmed blocks it back towards the bowler.
Angles in a full ball on middle, Salman wrists it across the line but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Southee drops it on a good length around off, Agha is on the front foot as he blocks it down on the pitch.
Fuller this time from Southee, outside off, Salman drives it to deep cover and keeps strike by denying the single.
Pitches it up and around off, Agha brings his bat down in time and keeps it out towards mid-wicket.

OUT! That's plumb in front! Tim Southee fires in a length ball, around middle, at 131.6 kph, Agha Salman clears his front leg for a big swipe across the line but misses and is rapped on the back leg. They appeal and the finger has gone up. Salman takes the DRS but to no avail. No bat is involved and it's crashing onto the middle stump, confirms the Ball Tracking. Pakistan are all out for 438!
Howout: lbw b Tim Southee

Commentary: Starts with a length delivery outside off, shaping away, Latham allows it through to the keeper.
Mir Hamza gets close to off, on a length and getting it to shape away a hint again, Latham is forced to play at it and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Hamza is a touch straight on this occasion with his line, Tom works it wide of mid on and opens his account with a single.
Serves it full and outside off, Conway attempts to defend minus any footwork. It takes the inside part of his bat and strikes him on the back pad.
Mir Hamza delivers it on a driving length outside off, Conway takes his front leg forward to cover the line and then shoulders arms.
Identical to the last delivery, skidding away off the surface, Conway guards his stumps and allows it through outside off.
Wasim begins his spell from 'round the wicket and angles in a full ball around off, Latham defends it close to his body.
FOUR! A 136.9 kph delivery, on a length but drifting down the leg side, Tom Latham gets a gentle tickle on his attempted flick shot and it races behind to fine leg for a boundary.
Slightly short in length and wide outside off, Tom has nothing to do with it.
Darts in a good-length delivery, around off, Latham once again defends it close to his body.
A touch fuller and on off, angling in, Latham plays from the back foot and pushes it to mid on.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Latham taps it down from the back foot to covers.
Some movement in the air but very little off the surface. Full and close to off, Conway drives away from his body but finds point.
It's full again and outside off, this time Conway keeps the bat close to his body and allows it through to the keeper.
Hamza is bowling good lines. He puts it on a fuller length just around off and gets it to go straight on, Conway presses forward and leaves.
Close to off, on a length and staying a bit low, Conway defends it from the back foot.
Delivers it on a length and around off at 132 kph, Conway brings down a straight bat and jams it down on the surface.
A length ball around off at 132.6 kph, Conway sticks back and uses the angle to work it towards square leg. Maiden.
Serves it on a length and around off at 139 kph, Latham defends it from the back foot to point.
Angling in from a length around off at 135.7 kph, Tom is quite assured with his defensive game.
Wasim keeps bowling close to off, on a length at 138.9 clicks, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it back to the bowler.
Beaten! A 137.8 kph delivery, landing on a fuller length outside off, Latham has a tentative poke inside the line and misses.
Bowls it full and around off, Latham knocks it down towards mid on where Nauman Ali makes a nice diving stop. Another maiden!
FOUR! Delightful shot to open his account! Back of a length, around off at 130.1 kph, Conway goes on the back foot and punches with authority through covers for a boundary.
Fuller on this occasion, outside off, Conway drives but finds the fielder at covers.
On a good length around off, Devon pushes it from the back foot to mid off.
FOUR! Poor delivery and it's duly punished! Short and wide outside off, Conway latches onto the gift and whacks it through point for a cracking boundary.
A touch short in length around off, some extra bounce, Conway tries to defend from the back foot but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller around off, defended watchfully to end the over.
Around the wicket. Good-length delivery angling into the batter. Latham defends it back at the bowler.
This was similar to the last delivery, Tom Latham again defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham defends it towards mid off.
This one lands outside off, Latham defends it towards short extra cover.
Touch fuller and shaping it in, Tom Latham tucks it towards the man at short mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, around off. Latham strides forward and is rock solid with his defense.

Shout for an lbw! Fuller delivery, this one keeps very low. Devon Conway looks to defend it but misses and is hit on the pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They decide not to review it. A good call as it was pitching outside the leg stump.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway blocks it towards mid off.
Tosses it up on off, Devon Conway lunges and blocks it away.
FOUR BYES! This one lands outside leg, Devon Conway looks to flick it but misses. The keeper fails to grab it as the ball races away to the fine-leg fence for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway defends it to mid off.
Bowls it on middle, Devon Conway defends it solidly off the front foot.
On a length and angling in, Tom Latham eases it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Lovely shot. Touch fuller and on off, Tom Latham prods forward and drives it crisply through mid off for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Tom Latham eases it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it fuller again, Tom Latham eases it to mid off.
On a length, angling in. Tom Latham defends it off the front foot to mid on.
Touch fuller and on middle, Tom Latham tucks it to the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway eases it to the leg side. Dot.
FOUR! Just a push off the front foot. Fuller and on off, Devon Conway moves forward and caresses it through mid on for a boundary.
Fuller on the stumps. Conway turns it to short mid-wicket.
Full length on the stumps. Conway strides forward and defends it back at the bowler.

Appeal for a run out! Flighted delivery around off, Conway drives it back and the bowler goes down low to get some touch on the ball. It deflects behind and collides with the stumps and the bowler appeals. The third umpire is troubled and the replays find that Latham is alert and has dragged his bat inside the crease nice and early.
Flatter and on middle and leg, Devon Conway eases it to the fielder at mid on.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham tucks it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Fine shot. Shorter and on off, Tom Latham hangs back and pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on off, Tom Latham defends it to mid off.
This one perhaps slips out of Wasim's hand as he serves a full toss on middle, Latham defends it back.
FOUR! Shorter in length and outside off, Tom Latham rocks back and slaps it uppishly over backward point for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham pushes it to mid off. Ends with a dot.
Quicker through the air, full and on middle and staying low, Conway stays back and brings his bat down in time to keep it away.
Loopy and full around off, Conway defends it off his front foot.
Loopy and full, around middle and off, Conway is watchful as he defends it on the leg side.
Miscued! Flighted delivery around leg, this one scoots low as well. Conway tries to flick but gets a leading edge past first slip. They get two runs.
Tossed up around off, full in length, Conway lunges and defends it to the off side.
Very full and around off, Conway drives it back to the bowler.
Flighted and around off, defended to the off side.
Fuller and around leg, Latham sweeps but finds the fielder at short fine leg.
Flatter and shorter on off, Latham goes back and defends it to the off side.
Loopy and full around off, Tom rushes down the track and flicks it from the inner half to deep square leg. They cross.
Slightly short and outside off, some extra bounce, Devon controls well and steers it wide of backward point for one.
Quicker one, outside off, Conway stands across the stumps in his stance and defends it watchfully.
Fuller and around leg, Conway defends it near his pads and taps it to short leg.
Floated one, full and on middle, Conway is forward in defense.

Slower through the air, full and on middle, Conway gives the charge but is beaten in flight. It stays low as well. Conway adjusts well and pushes it defensively to mid off. It rolls wide of the fielder and they cross. Conway gestures to his partner that - Loopy one is the leg spinner and the flatter one is spinning away from the left-hander! Has he decoded Abrar?
A little quicker through the air, around off and short in length, Latham defends it from the back foot.
Leans forward to a full ball and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Quicker and fuller on off, Latham lunges and defends it to the off side.
Babar brings himself into the attack and delivers a quicker one on off, Conway pushes it to cover-point for one.
Short and around off, Latham goes back to cut but finds point.
Flatter and on off, Latham stays back in defense.
Extra loop on this one, drifting in very full on off, Latham digs it out back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, Lathan cuts it wide of the sweeper cover fielder for a couple of runs.
Flighted delivery on middle, fuller in length, Latham defends it back with a straight bat. That will be Tea on Day 2.
Starts with a flatter and shorter delivery outside off, Conway gets behind the line and pushes it away with an angled bat to point.
Nauman goes fuller and serves it around off, Conway is forward as he defends it towards short mid-wicket.
Full and floated, on off, Conway draws forward and defends it to the off side this time.
A bit quicker through the air, full and on off, Conway walks down the track and knocks it to mid on.

NOT OUT! A touch short in length around off, Conway rocks on the back foot and punches it towards the bowler. Ali tries to grab the ball but it bursts through his palms and goes on to break the stumps at the other end. Nauman appeals and is celebrating as he is sure that Latham is outside the crease. It's referred upstairs and the replays find that Latham is safely in.
FOUR! This one is very full and outside off, Conway leans into the drive and thumps it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Tom Latham defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one and this is again defended back towards Abrar Ahmed.
This one lands on leg, Tom Latham eases it to the man at short leg.
Fuller and on off, Tom Latham defends it back towards the bowler.
This one keeps a tad low, on leg. Tom Latham blocks it to the man at short leg.
Bowls it on off, Tom Latham lunges and blocks it away.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Devon Conway leaves the harmless delivery.
This one lands on off, Devon Conway lunges and blocks it to mid off.
Fuller and on middle, slower too. Devon Conway eases it back towards the bowler.
Quicker one outside off, Devon Conway plays it with soft hands towards slips.
FOUR! Fuller one on middle, Devon Conway reverse-sweeps it past the slip fielder and towards third man for a boundary.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Devon Conway punches it to extra cover and scampers through for a quick single. 50 up!
Bowls it outside leg, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, Devon Conway blocks it solidly back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Devon Conway prods forwards and defends it to covers.
Bowls it on leg this time, Devon Conway eases it to mid on.
Fuller and on middle, Devon Conway nudges it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Perfectly timed. Slower one and on off, Tom Latham reads it well and sweeps it past square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway lunges and blocks it to mid off.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway moves forward and defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Conway steps down and then presents a dead bat to it.
This one lands outside off, Devon Conway looks to play at it but misses and gets hit on his pads. A stifled appeal turned down. The impact looked outside off.
This one lands outside off, Devon Conway cuts it but finds the fielder at point.
Fuller and on off, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Tom Latham defends it to the man at silly point.
Another fuller one, on middle. Tom Latham sweeps it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Tom Latham looks to reverse sweep but doesn't connect well. It takes a bounce and goes towards the slip fielder who fails to collect it. They cross.
Fuller and on middle, Devon Conway clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Keeps bowling it fuller, Tom Latham sweeps it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Latham defends it solidly off the front foot.

FOUR! Streaky! Fuller and around off, Conway brings out the reverse-batted shot again but this time it grabs the under edge and screams past the stumps to the fence at fine leg. That's the danger when you are sweeping out of the rough.
Tosses it up and lands it full outside off, Conway drives it to covers where a fumble allows the single.
A touch quicker and around off, Latham sweeps it well to deep square leg and takes a single.
Loopy this time, full and on off, Conway defends it with soft hands to covers.
This one is very full and on off, Conway drills his drive through the line but finds mid off.
Slower through the air, full and drifting around off, Conway brings his bat ahead of the front pad as he defends it down.
Slightly short and on off, Latham goes on the back foot and plays it down in front of short leg.
Short again, around off, Tom hangs back and works it wide of square leg for a single.
FOUR! Conway continues to impress! Too full in length from Abrar, around off, Conway presses forward and unfurls a picture-perfect straight drive for a boundary.
Tossed up around off, defended to the off side.
FOUR! The intent with the bat from Conway is not allowing Abrar to settle down. Full and flighted around off, Conway gets on the front foot and crunches it through point for a beautiful boundary.
Flighted and outside off, defended. It's been a great start for the Kiwis.
Slower through the air, short and around off, Latham eases himself on the back foot and pushes it to mid on.
Floated and full, around off, Tom jumps down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Play and a miss! Loopy and full outside off, Latham tries to sweep but misses. It goes off his thigh pad to first slip.
Connects well this time. Full and around off, Latham kneels down and sweeps it in front of square on the leg side. The fielder in the deep makes a diving stop and the batters take a run.
Tossed up around off, again Latham uses his feet to smother the spin as he defends.
Serves it full and on off, Latham hangs on the back foot and keeps it out towards short mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery, full and around leg, Conway defends it from the inner edge to backward square leg.
Fuller and on off, Conway defends it in front of his eyes.

Appeal for an lbw! Not given. Around leg, full in length, Conway hangs back to work it on the leg side but misses. He is rapped on the pads and they appeal. Nothing from the umpire. Pitching outside leg.
Quicker one, full and on off, defended to the off side.
Floats this one around leg, full in length, Devon tries to flick but misses.
Shortish and on off, Conway goes deep inside the crease and forces it past mid off for a couple of runs.
Doing it with ease. Fuller and on off, Latham sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Flatter delivery, short and on off, it's punched back to the bowler.
Loopy one this time, full and on off, Conway defends it calmly to the leg side.
Fuller one outside off, Conway reverse-sweeps but not from the middle of the bat. He mistimes it towards point and the first slip fielder is quick to get to the ball.
Fuller on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Advances down the track and nearly yorks himself in the process. Conway eventually digs it out back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tom Latham punches it to the man at mid on.
Bowls it on off again, Tom Latham works it to square leg for a single.
This one lands on middle, Devon Conway blocks it towards the man at short leg.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller one around middle and leg, Devon Conway charges down the track and heaves it over wide mid on for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Devon Conway blocks it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one and this is again defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Tom Latham clips it to deep mid-wicket off the back foot for a couple of runs.
Fuller and on off, Tom Latham sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Devon Conway punches it to deep cover for a brace.
Bowls it on middle, Devon Conway plays it back towards the bowler.

FIFTY! Turning in from outside off, Devon Conway looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg. They scamper through for a quick single. This brings up the fifty for Devon Conway, his fifth in Test cricket! It's been an innings of good composure and very good command.
Fuller and on off, Latham steps down and pushes it back to the bowler. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway pushes it to the man at covers.
Another fuller one, Devon Conway defends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Bowls it outside off, Devon Conway eases it towards the gully region.
Fuller one, angling in. Devon Conway defends it solidly back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, angling in. Devon Conway defends it to covers.
FOUR! Brilliant wristwork. Wasim bowls it fuller and on middle and leg, Devon Conway flicks it beautifully it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tom Latham punches it towards extra cover for one.
Drags his length short again, Devon Conway times it perfectly and punches it towards deep extra cover. The fielder has a long chase to do. The batters collect three runs. 100 up for New Zealand!
Tossed up, on off. Tom Latham flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and on middle, Devon Conway defends it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Another fuller one, this is again defended back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, Devon Conway eases it back to Nauman. Nothing happening for the Pakistan spinners at the moment.
Around the wicket. Bowls it fuller and on off, Tom Latham pushes it to mid off.
Another fuller one, on off. Tom Latham drives it to deep cover-point for a brace.
Bowls it outside off, Tom Latham guides it to the man at gully.
On a length and on off. Tom Latham pushes it to mid on.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Tom Latham knocks it to extra cover for a single.
Another fuller one on off, Devon Conway defends it to covers. Ends with a dot.
Loopy and full, around off, Tom calmly paddles it down to fine leg for a run.
Fuller on off, defended back to the bowler.
Presses forward with a straight bat and pushes it defensively towards Nauman.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Nauman is bowling full around off and Conway dead-bats it.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

Appeal for a caught behind! Some extra spin from outside off, Conway tries to play late but it whistles past the edge of his bat. Sarfaraz Ahmed collects and appeals but nothing from the umpire. No thought is given to taking the DRS. Wow, the UltraEdge detects an edge. A chance goes begging for Pakistan.
A bit short in length and outside off, Latham steers it through point for a single.
FOUR! Fabulous shot! Full in length and around off, angling in, Conway shows the full face of his bat and creams it down the ground, past mid on, for a boundary.
Delivers it on a good length outside off, Conway shoulders arms.
Lands it on a good length, targeting the off stump, Conway stays on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Pitches it slightly up and around off, Devon stays back-footed in defense.
Fuller in length around off, Conway leans across and flicks but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.
Very full and around off, Latham goes down and across to sweep but he fails to beat the short fine leg fielder.
FOUR! Placed well this time! Quicker one through the air, full and around leg, Latham goes down on one knee and sweeps it firmly past the right side of short fine leg for a boundary.
Loopy and full outside off, Latham tries to paddle it around but gets an under edge.

FIFTY FOR TOM LATHAM, his 24th in Test cricket to go along with 12 centuries. He reaches there with a sweep shot. Sends the ball behind square leg and rotates the strike. It's a secured knock from Tom thus far.
Fuller and on off, driven through the line to mid off.
Fullish around off, Conway tries to play the reverse sweep but fails to connect cleanly.
Angles in a length ball on off, Latham stays on the back foot and defends it to mid-wicket.
Wasim goes very full and on off, at 137 clicks, Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Wasim serves it on a length around off, angling in, Latham is sound in his defense.

Wasim eyes a yorker but ends up serving a full toss on middle at 138.4 kph, Latham pushes it straight back and the bowler fails to stop it. The mid off fielder chases it down and they get a couple of runs.
Back of a length around off, Latham camps back and steers it past backward point for another couple of runs.
Lands it full and outside off, Latham defends it solidly back to the bowler.
Starts his second spell with a flighted delivery around leg, Conway gets forward and defends it back.
Around the pads, Conway works it around but finds backward square leg.
Fuller on middle, Conway presses forward and defends it with ease.
Fuller and on the pads this time, it's clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Slower through the air, full and drifting around off, Latham lunges and defends.
Tossed up around middle, Tom is forward as he covers the spin and defends it towards Abrar.
Over the wicket. Back of a length and outside the off stump. Devon Conway punches it to the man at covers.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Devon Conway looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards short leg.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards mid off.
Bowls it fuller again, Devon Conway drills it down the ground and the ball hits the stumps at the other end. This has happened quite a few times in this inning.
Slightly shorter and on off, this one keeps a tad low. Devon Conway pulls it but gets the toe end of his bat as the ball rolls towards deep mid-wicket. They collect two.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway eases it to mid on. Ends with a dot.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Tom Latham lunges and blocks it away.
This one lands outside off, Tom Latham plays the reverse sweep towards third man. They collect two.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Latham sweeps it to deep square leg for a brace.

Fuller again, just outside off, Tom Latham looks to sweep it but misses and gets his pads. A stifled appeal turned down. The players decide not to review it. The replays show that it came out from the shoulder of the bat. So no pad was involved as we thought earlier. Great decision by the umpire.
Full and on off, Tom Latham eases it to mid off.
This one lands on off, Tom Latham defends it to mid off.

Appeal for an lbw! Landing on a length around middle and leg, drifting down, Devon Conway looks to flick it but misses and gets rapped on his pads. A huge appeal from the bowler alone but the umpire is unmoved. Babar Azam decides not to review it.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Tom Latham works it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Tom Latham defends it to mid on.
Touch fuller, down leg. Tom Latham flicks it to deep square leg for a brace.
On a length and just outside off, Tom Latham guides it to point for one.
Fuller one, on middle. Devon Conway flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Tom Latham gently sweeps it to backward square leg for one.

FOUR! Perfectly timed. Slightly shorter and on off, slower too. Devon Conway rocks back and punches it through extra cover for a boundary. Mohammad Wasim was giving the chase but his dive at the last moment was quite ordinary.
Bowls it on off, Devon Conway guides it to covers for one.
FOUR! Slightly shorter one again, on off. Tom Latham hangs back and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, this is defended towards square leg.
Bowls it on off, Tom Latham turns it to square leg again. Ends with a dot.
On a length and on leg, Devon Conway tucks it to backward square leg for a brace.
On a length and on off, Devon Conway pushes it to covers.
Touch fuller and on off, Devon Conway eases it towards mid off.
Another fuller one, Devon Conway looks to defend it but gets the inside half of his bat as the ball rolls towards mid on. Dot.
Keeps it bowling fuller in length, Devon Conway clips it towards backward square leg for one.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Tom Latham defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller around leg, defended off the pads to short leg.
Fullish on off, spinning away, Conway leans forward and defends it with the outer half of his blade.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Around middle, Conway stays back and punches it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller around leg, Conway wrists it away to mid-wicket.
Flighted around leg, turning away a bit, Conway is solid in his front-foot defense.
Length ball angling into the middle stump line. Latham flicks it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and around off, Tom is on the back foot as he defends it down safely.
Delivers it full around middle and leg, Latham flicks but finds the fielder in front of square on the leg side.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Full in length and sliding down the leg side, Latham tries to flick but gets a faint inside edge. The ball gathers enough speed to run away to the fence at fine leg.
Angling in from a length around off, Tom works it quietly through square leg for a single.
Pitches it up and on middle, Conway clips it behind square leg for another single.
Floated delivery, landing full outside off, Conway uses his feet and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and down the leg side, Conway nudges it down to fine leg for a run. 150 up for New Zealand!
Another full ball, around middle, Latham helps it past short leg for one.
Spinning down the leg side, this time Devon fails to get any bat behind it.
Quicker through the air, around middle at 89 kph, Conway flicks it to mid-wicket.
Slightly slower this time, at 82 clicks, around off and drifting in, Conway tries to defend but gets it away off the outer edge. It dribbles to backward point and they cross.
Short and outside off, Conway cuts it through point for a single.
Flighted and full, around off, Latham is on the front foot as he defends it to the off side.
Fuller and on off, Latham walks down the track and eases it past mid on for a single.
A dipping full toss on off, Conway drives it towards wide mid off for a run.
A touch short and on off, Tom goes on the back foot and blocks it down.
Short again from Babar, outside off, Latham cuts it through point and picks another single in the over.
Too full and on middle, Latham eases his sweep shot behind square leg for a run.
Turning in a hint from a fuller length around middle, Conway flicks it gently past short leg for a run.
Very full and on off, driven square of the wicket on the off side for one.
Loopy and full around off, Conway lunges and defends it with soft hands towards point. They cross for a run.
Quicker and around middle, blocked from the back foot by Latham.
Floats this one around off, full in length, Latham prods forward and defends it.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway taps it to the man at mid on.
Tosses it up, fuller outside the off stump. Conway drives it to deep cover for a single.
Full and on off, Tom Latham eases it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tom Latham cuts it to point for one.

This one lands on off, Devon Conway flicks it to mid-wicket for one. The misfield allows the batters to take one more. Two in total. Conway completes 1000 runs in Test cricket, quickest to that mark for New Zealand, in only 19 innings.
This one lands outside off, Devon Conway leaves the harmless delivery.
Around the wicket. Fuller and on off, Tom Latham flicks it down to mid on for a single.
Fuller and outside off, Devon Conway defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, Devon Conway turns it to the man at short leg.
Bowls it on middle, Devon Conway lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Fullish and around off, Conway lunges and defends it to the off side.
Loopy and full on middle, Conway does well to keep it out. That will be Stumps on Day 2.
Hamza begins with a wrong line. Slips a full ball down the leg side, Latham tries to buy some cheap runs with a fine tickle but fails to connect.
Full in length and this time it is served in the line of the stumps, Tom flicks but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Hamza continues to be quite straight with his line. Latham works a full ball down to fine leg and opens his account for the day with a single.
Lands it on a fuller length, close to off, Conway is on the front foot as he blocks it to the off side.
Puts it on a full length around off, shaping in a touch, Conway tries to defend but gets an inside edge. It rolls away to short mid-wicket. That's the line for Mir.
Identical to the last delivery, this time Conway defends it more in a controlled manner on the leg side.
Wasim begins with a delivery on the fuller side, around off and angling in, Latham blocks it safely to the on side.
Another full ball has been angled in around off, Latham defends near his front pad.
Latham uses the angle of the bowler this time and works a length ball through square leg for a single.
Too full in length and on middle, Conway leans across to flick but again he has picked out the short mid-wicket fielder.
A hint of movement back into the batter from around off, from a length, Conway helps it on the leg side but not in the gap.
Fuller and on off, Devon covers the line and defends it back in the direction of the bowler.
Hamza pitches it up and on off, Latham is confident as he defends it on the leg side from the crease.
Full and on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.

FOUR! A bit aerial but through the gap for the first boundary of the day. The short-leg fielder moved to the forward short-leg position before this ball and that flying ball wen through backward short leg. Could have been a chance. Full and around middle, shaping in, Latham flicks across the line and sends it to the fence in no time.
Full and around off, defended.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball and blocks it safely.
Around off, on a fuller length, Latham covers the line and defends it again. Umpire Aleem Dar was seen having a word with Latham. He asked the batter to stay away from the danger area while running.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Devon Conway defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it slightly shorter and outside off, Devon Conway cuts it to deep backward point for a brace.
Over the wicket. Bowls it fuller and on off, Devon Conway taps it to short cover.
Another fuller one and on off, Devon Conway defends it to covers again.
This one lands outside off, shaping it away, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Conway covers the stumps and taps it to short cover. Ends with a dot.
Touch fuller and on leg, Tom Latham flicks it to the man at leg gully.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Latham flicks it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Easy pickings. This one lands down leg, Devon Conway uses the pace of the ball and tickles it through to fine leg for a boundary.
On a length and outside off, angling in. Devon Conway reads it well and leaves it alone.
Touch fuller and on off, shaping it in. Devon Conway defends it to mid off.
On a length and on middle. Devon Conway fends it to mid on.
It's time for some spin as Nauman Ali comes into the attack. He begins with a tossed-up delivery, on off. Tom Latham eases it to short leg.
Fuller and on off, Tom Latham sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Devon Conway shimmies down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary. He moves to 92 now!
Fuller again, on off. Devon Conway defends it solidly off the front foot.
Tosses it up on off, Devon Conway looks to drill it but gets it away off the inside half of the bat and it strikes him on his toes. It rolls back towards the bowler.

OUT! LBW! Finally, Pakistan have a breakthrough and it's Nauman who has done it. It's nicely looped up and lands around off, turns back in sharply and catches Conway on the back foot. He attempts to work it on the leg side but misses and is rapped on the pads. The finger stays down as they appeal and Pakistan take the referral. Perhaps turning too much there! UltraEdge takes some time to load. It shows that there is some murmur when the ball is close to the inside edge of the bat. The third umpire spends some time on it and then finds out that there is a tiny gap between the bat and ball. So no bat is involved. Ball Tracking goes on to suggest that it's hitting the stumps. The on-field decision is reversed and Conway departs, missing out on his hundred. A great review from Pakistan.
Howout: lbw b Nauman Ali

Commentary: On a length angling it into the batter, Tom Latham blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off shaping in a bit, Tom Latham drives it to deep extra cover for a brace.
On a length with some extra bounce, Tom Latham fends it to silly mid on. There are two fielders in the catching position on the leg side at the moment.
Bowls it fuller and on middle and leg, Tom Latham covers his line and defends it to silly mid on.
Another fuller one on off, Tom Latham drives it to mid off and he scampers through for a single. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
On a length with some extra bounce, angling away. Kane Williamson looks to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge. That was close!
Bowls it fuller and on off, Tom Latham sweeps it through square leg for one.
Tosses it up on middle and leg, Kane Williamson eases it to the leg side.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller again and on off, Kane Williamson blocks it to silly mid off.
Bowls it on off, Kane Williamson eases it to the man at short leg.
Fuller and on the middle stump line, Kane Williamson drives it back to the bowler. Ends with a dot.
Serves it on a length and close to off, Latham is on the front foot as he drives it to covers. Not in the gap.
Pitches it up and around off, Latham drives again but finds the fielder at covers.
The line is straighter this time and Latham works it through square leg for a single.
Full and outside off, Williamson plays his trademark dab to gully and opens his account with a single.
Fuller on off, Latham strokes off the front foot but finds covers.
Spears in a very full ball on off, Latham brings his bat down and squeezes it out towards deep point. They collect a single to close the over.
Flighted and full around off, Latham uses his feet and forces it down to long on for a single.
Uses his feet to come down the track and pushes a full ball to mid on.
Flighted around middle, Williamson gets on the front foot and defends it on the leg side.
Loopy and full, drifting in around off, Kane jams it down off the front foot.
Very full and on middle, Williamson calmly wrists it to mid-wicket.
Again the length is very full, around off, and Williamson knocks it down to mid on.
Flighted and around middle, turning in, Tom helps it off his pads to short fine leg.

Aerial but safe! Abrar Ahmed lands it full outside off, on the rough and gets it to turn in with some extra bounce. Latham top-edges his attempted sweep shot and it flies down to long leg. They collect three runs.
Full and on middle, Williamson defends it on the leg side.
Fuller and on middle, defended towards short leg.
Lunges to a full ball and defends it watchfully to the off side.
A bit quicker through the air, on middle, Kane keeps it out safely to mid-wicket.
Beaten all ends up! Flatter outside off, a bit short and turning back in, Tom goes back to cut but it beats the inside part of his bat.
In the air... Safe! Latham tries to sweep out of the rough again and there is a top edge once more. It flies over square leg and he gets a couple. Tom is looking a bit edgy in his 90s.
Loopy and around middle, Tom Latham walks forward and eases it down to long on for a single. Moves to 99!
Quicker and flatter on off, Williamson goes on the back foot and defends it to cover-point.
Flatter again, around off and turning away with some low bounce, Kane does well to keep it out on the leg side.
Too full this time, around middle, this time Kane Williamson easily defends it back.
Floated and full, around off, Latham jumps down the track and pushes it to mid on.

Risky single and TOM LATHAM COMPLETES HIS 13TH TEST HUNDRED! He has now the most number of Test centuries for a New Zealand opener, surpassing John Wright. Coming to the delivery, it's full and around off, Latham sweeps it towards short fine leg and completes a brisk single. The helmet comes off and Tom raises his bat to celebrate the moment.
Tossed up around middle, Williamson works it wide of short fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! A tossed-up delivery, around off, Latham brings out the reverse sweep and nails it down to third man for a boundary. It was a bit from the top part of his bat but went in the gap.
Loopy and on off, defended to short leg.
Fuller and on middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on middle, skidding in. Kane Williamson blocks it to silly mid on.
Fuller one this time, outside off. Kane Williamson defends it to the gully region.
Another fuller one, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it solidly.
Tosses it up, on off. Kane Williamson eases it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it up on the off stump channel, Kane Williamson lunges forward and defends it.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Kane Williamson covers the line and blocks it solidly.
This one lands down leg, Kane Williamson looks to flick it but gets the inside edge of the bat as the ball rolls to fine leg. They collect two.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson defends it solidly.
Another fuller one and on off, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it away.
Flatter and quicker on off, Kane goes on the back foot and blocks it to mid-wicket.
Edgy! Turn and bounce from around off, Kane hangs on the back foot and has a gentle poke inside the line. It takes the outer edge and drops in front of first slip. Soft hands.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Latham reverse-sweeps it to backward point for a single.

FOUR LEG BYES! This one lands down leg, it keeps very low. Kane Williamson looks to flick it but misses and the keeper misses it as well and the ball races away to the fine leg fence. The umpire though thinks that it's off the batter's pad and gives it as leg byes.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson blocks it solidly.
Full and on middle, Williamson comes forward and turns it towards short mid-wicket. Dot.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson moves forward and looks to loft it but miscues it to long on. They collect two.
Fuller and on off, this is defended off the front foot.
Bowls it outside off, Tom Latham blocks it to silly point.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Tom Latham lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Turning in from outside off, Tom Latham blocks it towards the off side.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Tom Latham flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
This one lands on off, Kane Williamson eases it to the man at mid off.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson turns it to short fine leg. They wanted a single but decided not to take it. Ends with a dot.
Slightly shorter and on middle and leg, Tom Latham flicks it to the man at backward square leg.
Bowls it on off, turning in. Tom Latham moves forward to play at it but the ball hits the inside half of his bat and rolls towards mid on. Dot.
Another fuller one, Tom Latham tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Around the wicket. Bowls it fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it away.
Another fuller one as Kane Williamson blocks it to the man at mid on.
Keeps it bowling fuller in length, Kane Williamson prods forward and plays a solid defense back at the bowler.
Oohhh... once again there is some extra bounce as it turns the other way from outside off, Latham pushes at it and misses.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Quicker and fuller on off, defended off the front foot.
Spinning in from around off, shorter in length, Latham gets back and punches it to mid-wicket.
Drifting on the pads, Latham stands back and works it through backward square leg for a single.

Loopy and full, around leg, Williamson goes down to sweep but fails to middle it from the sweet spot of his bat. They appeal but more in hope than anything. Going down leg and perhaps there was some bat as well.
Shortish and on off, Latham punches from the back foot to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Latham sweeps hard from the rough to square leg for a quick run.
A bit slower through the air this time, full and on off, Williamson prods and defends it to the off side.
Flatter through the air, darts it on middle and leg, Williamson defends it off his pads to the leg side.
Controls well in the end. Some extra bounce from around off as it spins away, Williamson gets on top of the delivery and steers it through point for two runs.

FOUR! Well played! Too full from Nauman Ali, on middle and Kane Williamson brings out the conventional sweep shot. He times it well and places it through square leg for his first boundary. The stand moves to 36 and New Zealand trail by 215 runs.
Tossed up outside off, Latham defends it to the off side.
Goes down and sweeps a full ball through square leg for a single. This is his pet shot and has fetched him many runs in this knock.

GIVEN LBW! Kane Williamson has reviewed it quickly. Coming to the delivery, it's floated and full around off, Williamson tries to defend ahead of his front pad but seems to have missed it. He is pinged on the pads, they appeal and the finger goes up. Kane takes the referral and the UltraEdge finds a spike. Technology saves Kane. He was always confident and even nodded when asked by one of the Pakistan players for the reason behind his referral.
On middle, worked through square leg for a single.
Flatter and on middle, Tom goes on the back foot and keeps it out on the leg side.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Latham presses forward and defends.
Very full and on off, Williamson lunges and jams it down on the surface.
Arm ball, around middle and leg, Williamson turns it off his pads to square leg and steals a quick run.
Sprays it full and wide outside off, Latham tries to fetch it and sweep but fails to connect.
Connects this time with his sweep shot but finds the fielder at square leg.
Slightly short and on off, Latham moves back, allows the ball to spin back in and punches it to deep cover for a run.
Poor delivery. Nauman fires it very full down the leg side, Williamson fails to sweep and Sarfaraz Ahmed too fails to collect it. Two byes added to the scoreboard.
Shortish and around middle, Latham goes on the back foot in defense.
Fuller and on off, Latham defends it with the spin to the leg side.
Quicker this time, too full and on off, Latham reverse-sweeps it behind backward point for two.
Allows it to spin back in and works it from the back foot towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tom Latham's fine knock has come to an end and Pakistan have a timely breakthrough just at the stroke of Lunch. Abrar Ahmed delivers a full ball around middle and gets it to spin down the leg side, Latham goes down to play his favourite reverse sweep but this time it takes his gloves and loops behind the keeper. Kamran Ghulam (sub) moves across to his right from first slip and takes the simplest of catches. Latham is disappointed on his way back. New Zealand trail by 207 runs. The replays show that after brushing the gloves, it took Tom's forearm as well and that's why the ball ballooned more.
Howout: c sub Kamran Ghulam b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Loopy and full around off, Nicholls presses forward and defends it back with a straight bat.
Around the wicket. Bowls it on middle and leg, Kane Williamson tucks it to deep square leg for a brace.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller and on leg, Kane Williamson works it towards square leg for one.
Over the wicket. Slower through the air, full around off. Henry Nicholls defends it towards the leg side.
Another fuller one, Henry Nicholls lunges and blocks it to silly mid on.

FOUR! Fuller and on middle, Henry Nicholls reads it well and sweeps it across the line through the legs of the fielder at short leg. The backward square leg fielder is late in taking off and as a result, even his dive is not enough to stop the racing ball.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter one this time, Kane Williamson fends it to mid on for a single.
Tosses it up on off, Henry Nicholls flicks it towards backward square leg for a quick single.
This one lands on off, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it to mid off.
Full on the off. Williamson comes forward and blocks it to the right of the fielder at short leg.
Another fuller one, Kane Williamson lunges and offers a dead bat to it. Ends with a dot.

Appeal for an lbw! Umpire Aleem Dar disagrees. Sarfaraz Ahmed has decided to send it upstairs by taking the DRS. Meanwhile, Dar is seen gesturing that the impact was outside off. Coming to the delivery, it's turning in from outside off, Nicholls gets back and across to defend but misses and is pinged on the pads. DRS time. Nothing on the UltraEdge and Ball Tracking vindicates Aleem Dar's observations. It's indeed hitting the batter outside the line of the off stump. Pakistan lose one review.
Slightly shorter and on off, Henry Nicholls defends it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on middle, Henry Nicholls sweeps it to the man at backward square leg.
FOUR! Connects well this time. Fuller and on off, Henry Nicholls gets on his knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Turning in from outside off, Henry Nicholls looks to block it but gets an inside edge towards the leg side. Dot.
Slightly shorter one, outside off. Henry Nicholls punches it towards covers for a single. That will be LUNCH on Day 3.
Bowls a fuller one on off, Henry Nicholls offers a solid forward defense.
This one lands outside off and keeps a tad low. Henry Nicholls looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller again, on off. Henry Nicholls flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Another fuller one on middle, Henry Nicholls sweeps it towards backward square leg for one.
Over the wicket. Turning in from outside off, Kane Williamson taps it to short covers.
Full-length delivery on the middle and leg line, Kane Williamson lunges and turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller one and on middle, Henry Nicholls sweeps it towards square leg for a single.
Around the wicket. Bowls it slightly shorter and on off, Kane Williamson hangs back and defends it to short cover.
This one lands on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it to short mid-wicket.

Bowls it on off, fuller in length. Kane Williamson eases it to the man at covers and sets off for a run. His partner shows no interest and Kane has to return. He was quite a few steps down the track but the calling from Henry Nicholls was loud and clear.
Tosses it up on off, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Full-length delivery on off, Kane Williamson works it down towards deep square leg for a single.
Abrar begins with a flighted delivery, full and down the leg side, Williamson sweeps it towards fine leg and picks up a single.
A touch short and around leg, Henry Nicholls goes on the back foot and defends it to mid-wicket.
Beats the batter in flight and length. Full and floated, around off, Nicholls fails to get forward and just defends it somehow from the crease.
Turns it with the spin to the leg side towards square leg. Another confusion over a run which is not taken.
Leans forward to a full ball and taps it down on one bounce to silly point.
Quicker and around leg at 86 clicks, Nicholls sticks on the back foot and defends it down.
Flighted delivery, full and around off, Williamson pushes it away with an angled bat and the first slip fielder quickly moves across to his right to stop the ball with a slide.
Fuller and on middle, defended wristily to the leg side.

Was that a stumping chance? Nauman gives this one some extra flight and lands it full around off. The ball lands and turns away a bit, Kane Williamson stretches forward to drive but misses and Sarfaraz Ahmed fails to gather the ball. Kane is outside the crease as he goes off balance but survives a stumping opportunity.
Fuller and on middle, defended.
FOUR! Fine footwork! Nauman flights this one around middle, full in length, Kane Williamson dances down the track and lifts it cleanly over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Tossed up around off, Williamson is watchful as he defends it off the front foot.
Googly around off, Nicholls punches it from the crease to mid on.

FOUR! Bang! Too full this time, around off, Henry Nicholls latches onto it and smacks it past the bowler for a cracking boundary at long off. Kane Williamson was seen taking cover as he goes down on the ground.
A touch short and on middle, Henry goes back and works it with the spin through square leg for a couple.
Loopy and full on off, Nicholls defends it off his front foot.
Fuller around leg, Nicholls sweeps it down to fine leg for a single.
Flighted and full around off, Kane is on the front foot as he defends it on the leg side.
Lands it full and outside off, Nicholls goes down and across to sweep but misses. He is hit on the back thigh and the ball deflects away towards slip.
A touch short and on off, turning in, Nicholls gets the chance to go on the back foot as he pushes it down to long on for a run.
Very full and on middle, drifting in, Kane drives it back and the bowler stops it to his left.
FOUR! Nicely timed. Nauman Ali is too full with his length around leg, Kane Williamson goes down on one knee and sweeps it sweetly in front of the square on the leg side for a boundary.
FOUR! Consecutive boundaries! Again Nauman serves it outside leg, targeting the rough with a fuller-length ball, Williamson kneels and sweeps it nicely to fine leg for another boundary.
Tossed up outside leg, Kane pads it away.
Flighted and on middle, Henry gets back and tucks it through backward square leg for a single.
Loopy delivery, landing full on off, Williamson strides forward and defends it back.
Slower through the air, pitching full and around off, Williamson again defends it patiently off the front foot.
Short and around off, Williamson goes deep inside the crease and cuts. Finds the point fielder.
Quicker one, skidding in from around middle, Williamson helps it behind square leg and picks up a single.
The length is on the shorter side, landing around off and turning back in slowly, Henry presses back and guides it through point for a single.
Slightly shorter and on off, Henry Nicholls defends it to silly point.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Poor shot selection and Henry Nicholls departs. This one lands outside off on the rough and turns back in quite sharply, it keeps a shade low as well. Henry Nicholls looks to cut it buts gets a thick inside edge and the ball shatters the stumps. Henry Nicholls returns with New Zealand trailing by 166 runs.
Howout: b Nauman Ali

Commentary: Bowls it fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell lunges and defends it back towards the bowler. No ball is called for overstepping.
FOUR! Excellent timing on this. Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell reads it well and plays a reverse sweep through point for a boundary. Gets off the mark.
Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell defends it solidly.
Tossed up, on off. Daryl Mitchell knocks it towards mid on for one.
Slower one, on middle. Kane Williamson hangs back and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell moves forward and flicks it to wide mid on for a quick single.
This one lands outside off, some extra bounce. Kane Williamson leaves the harmless delivery.
Bowls it fuller and down leg, Kane Williamson tickles it to fine leg for a brace.
Goes fuller again, on middle. Kane Williamson offers a dead bat to it.
Another one on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, turning away, Kane Williamson shoulders arms at it.
Around the wicket. Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell lunges and blocks it away.

SIX! All the way. This is how he will approach his inning against the spinners, in particular. Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell shimmies down the wicket and powers it over long on for a maximum. Excellent use of the feet.
This one lands on off, Daryl Mitchell lunges and defends it this time.
Bowls it on off, Daryl Mitchell eases it to the man at mid off.
Another one on off, fuller in length. Daryl Mitchell leans forward and blocks it to silly point.
Ali goes fuller again, on middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Kane Williamson blocks it solidly off the front foot.

FOUR! Timing of the highest order! A touch short and on middle, turning away, Williamson goes on the back foot and works it with sublime timing through mid-wicket. It keeps on running away from the chasing fielder and finds the fence.
This one lands on off, Kane Williamson defends it to mid on.
FOUR! Even better! Again Abrar delivers it a bit short on middle, staying low, Kane gets low in his stance and through his wonderful wrists, he flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson blocks it watchfully.
Another fuller one, Kane Williamson lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Doesn't time it well but gets the result he wanted. This one lands fuller and on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and lofts it over mid on, from the inside half of his bat, and gets a boundary.
Goes fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off, Daryl Mitchell defends it to mid on.
Another one on off, fuller in length. Daryl Mitchell prods forward and defends it to mid off.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards mid on for a single. 300 comes up for New Zealand!
Slightly shorter, turning away from the right-hander, Kane Williamson hangs back and guides it late past first slip and backward point. Gets a single.
FOUR! Williamson continues to target the mid-wicket region. Short and on middle, Kane waits on the back foot for a fraction longer and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Moves to 49!
Tossed up around off, defended back.
Fuller and on off, defended with a dead bat.
FIFTY! Quicker and shorter on off, Williamson goes on the back foot and forces it through point for a single. This is his 34th fifty in Tests. A fine knock from the former skipper.
Extra flight there as it lands full around off, Mitchell wrists it to wide mid on for a single.
This one goes straight on from around off, Kane goes back in defense.
Wasim runs in from over the wicket and serves it full around off, Daryl drives it off the front foot to mid off.
Hurls it across on a length and quite outside off at 129.7 kph, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms.
FOUR! This partnership continues to blossom at a brilliant rate. A low full toss on off, at 131.1 kph, Daryl Mitchell strides forward and drives it firmly down the ground for a boundary at long off.
FOUR! Daryl Mitchell has come out with attacking intent. Short in length and wide outside off, Mitchell rocks back and smacks it through point for a boundary.

FOUR! Little streaky on this occasion. Wasim delivers it on a length and close to off, Mitchell tries to push inside the line and edges it. The ball races down to third man for a boundary. Three in a row!

FOUR! Fourth boundary in a row and the 50-run stand comes up in no time. Fuller in length around middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell unfurls a beautiful on-drive and fetches another boundary. He is on fire and the deficit is down to 115 runs.
Fuller delivery, around middle, Williamson gets behind the line and defends it back.
Back of a length, around leg, Kane brings his bat down and gets it away off the inner half. The ball dribbles behind square leg and they cross.
Delivers it on a length outside off, angling away, Mitchell plays inside the line and guides it past gully for a couple of runs.
Shortish around leg, Daryl Mitchell fails to glance and it goes off his thigh pad to square leg. They cross for a leg bye.
On a good length around off, Williamson goes on the back foot in defense.
Full and around off, angling away, Williamson covers the stumps and shoulders arms.
Daryl Mitchell is timing his shots brilliantly. This time though it is not in the gap. Full and outside off, it's driven to mid off.
Fuller and on off, again Daryl Mitchell plays a lovely off drive but only to find the fielder.
Close to off, full and angling in, Mitchell defends it near his front pad.
Lands it on a good length around off, Mitchell goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
This one is on a driving length outside off, Mitchell doesn't accept the proposal and allows it through to the keeper.
Wasim goes fuller and on off, Daryl is forward as he meets it with a straight bat in defense. Maiden!
Serves it on a length around off, shaping back in a hint, Williamson covers his stumps and allows it through.
Delivers it full and on off, Williamson drives but finds the fielder at short cover.
Hamza again keeps it full and lands ti wide outside off, Williamson tries to drive but it takes the inner half and rolls back to the bowler.
On a good length around middle and off, Kane defends from the back foot.
Pitches it up and around off, Kane Williamson drives but the cover fielder is alert and stops the ball.
Bowls it in the line of the stumps, on a length, Williamson stays on the back foot and dead-bats it near the surface.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Sublime timing. Mohammad Wasim goes fuller this time, Daryl Mitchell flicks it and times it perfectly through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards covers for a single.
Keeps it bowling fuller in length, Kane Williamson nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Bowls it on off, Daryl Mitchell looks to drive it but miscues it to the man at mid on. Dot.
Touch fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it to the point region.
On a length and outside off, shaping away a touch, Kane Williamson looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length again with some extra bounce, Kane Williamson blocks it solidly towards mid off.
Bowls it outside off, shaping it away, Kane Williamson leaves the harmless delivery.
Touch fuller this time, Kane Williamson drives it to deep cover for one.
This one lands on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell offers a dead bat to it.
Fuller and just outside off, Daryl Mitchell prods forward and defends it to mid off.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Kane Williamson eases it to the man at mid off.
This one lands on middle and leg, Kane Williamson tucks it to square leg for one.
Bowls it on middle, Daryl Mitchell looks to loft it but the ball hits the inside half of his bat and carries towards the right of mid on. It lands safely as the batters collect one.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson defends it solidly.
Slightly shorter and on the pads, Williamson tucks it to short leg.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson stands tall and defends it solidly.
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. Daryl Mitchell lets it through towards the keeper.
Another one outside off, shaping away. Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms at it.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell blocks it back towards the bowler.
Length ball on off. Mitchell defends off the front foot towards mid off.
On a length and on off, Mitchell flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
This one lands outside off, Daryl Mitchell prods forward and defends it firmly down to short cover. Ends with a dot.
Beaten! Ahmed delivers it full and around off, Williamson gets forward to defend the line but it spins away to beat the outside edge.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it towards square leg for one.
Bowls it on off, Daryl Mitchell lunges and blocks it to mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another Kiwi batter falls gloving his attempted reverse sweep. Abrar tosses it up around off, gets a hint of turn with some extra bounce, Daryl Mitchell looks to play the reverse batted shot but fails to connect and the ball hits his gloves. It lobs up in the air and Sarfaraz Ahmed moves forward to take a simple catch. The bowler had turned to appeal for an lbw but then found out that it was off the gloves and caught. The finger is up and Daryl Mitchell starts to walk. Kane Williamson just checks with him whether he is sure, Mitchell nods and returns.
Howout: c Sarfaraz Ahmed b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it towards square leg and gets off the mark. They cross.
Touch fuller and on leg, Kane Williamson hangs back and blocks it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full in length and outside off, Tom Blundell leans forward and crunches it through point for a boundary. The deficit is below 100 now.
On a length around middle, defended from the back foot.
Full and around off, angling away, Tom is batting outside his crease, and he defends it with ease.
In the channel outside off, on a good length, Tom Blundell shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.
Another delivery in the region outside off, Blundell covers his stumps and makes another leave.
Flighted and full on middle, Williamson lunges and defends it off the inner half to short leg.
Slightly short and on leg, Williamson gets back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Leans forward to a full ball and drives it through covers for a run.
Floated delivery, full and on off, Blundell defends it ahead of his front pad.
Fuller and on off, easily defended off the front foot by Tom.
Abrar drops it short around off, Blundell gets back and punches it towards cover-point.
Fractionally short from Wasim, around off, Williamson is on the back foot in defense.
A length ball on off, Williamson uses the angle and tickles it through backward square leg for a single.
Pitches it up and around off, Tom Blundell meets it with a dead bat in defense.
Fuller and on off, Tom drives it down the ground and Kane Williamson jumps to make way. It though goes straight to the fielder at mid on.
Full again, around off, Blundell gets behind the line and defends it towards silly mid on.
Lands it on a length, around off, Blundell gets forward and defends it to the off side.
Loopy and full on off, Williamson presses forward and blocks it to the off side.
Quicker through the air, a bit short and on middle, Kane gets back and wrists it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Williamson draws forward and defends. It hits the shoulder of his bat and rolls back, beats the stumps by not much.
Flatter and on middle, skidding in, Kane nudges it behind square leg for a run.
Googly around off, fuller in length, Blundell lunges to defend and does so off the inside edge. It rolls to short leg.
Fuller on middle, defended towards short leg again.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works a full ball to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Wasim lands it on a length, around middle and leg, Williamson waits and deflects it neatly off his pads to fine leg for a boundary.
Full and on off, Kane defends it back.
In the zone outside off, on a length, Williamson shoulders arms.
Close to off, full and angling in, Williamson plays near his body and defends it to the off side.
Another length ball angling in from around off, Kane Williamson defends it as well to end the session. TEA ON DAY 3!
Bowls it fuller and on middle and leg, Tom Blundell defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter and on middle, slower too. Tom Blundell hangs back and punches it to mid off for a quick single.
Tossed up, on middle. Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it away.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Kane Williamson works it to square leg for one.
Slower one on leg, Tom Blundell flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Kane Williamson guides it towards the man at backward point. Ends with a dot.
Tossed up, on middle. Tom Blundell eases it to mid off.
Fuller again, on middle. Tom Blundell lunges and blocks it to point.
Slightly shorter one, Blundell defends off the back foot to the right of the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Tom Blundell steers it to point for one.
FOUR! Excellent footwork. Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson uses his feet and lofts it over the bowler for a boundary.
Quicker one on middle, Kane Williamson looks to defend it but gets an inside edge to square leg.
Drags his length short and bowls it outside off, Tom cuts but finds the fielder at backward point.
Tossed up, with some turn. Tom Blundell looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and on off, Tom Blundell looks to slap it but gets a bottom edge as the ball goes past the keeper and Mohammad Wasim (chasing from short fine leg) for a boundary.
This one lands on off, Tom Blundell defends it towards mid off.
Tossed up, on middle. This is defended back towards the bowler.
This one lands outside off, Tom Blundell blocks it to covers.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
This was similar to the last delivery, Kane Williamson again defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on leg, Kane Williamson flicks it to square leg for one.
Flatter and on middle, Tom Blundell shuffles across and eases it to covers.

In the air but lands safely. Fuller and on off, turning away a shade with some extra bounce, Tom Blundell advances down the track for a lofted shot but slices it towards extra cover. Wasim runs across to his left from mid off but it drops in front of him. He tries to collect it on the bounce but instead kicks it away with his right leg. The batters get the chance to complete the second run.
Full and on the stumps. Tom Blundell blocks it back at the bowler off the front foot.
Bowls it on leg, Kane Williamson flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Slightly shorter one, Tom Blundell hangs back and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Tom Blundell drives but finds the fielder at covers.
Goes fuller and on off, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
Slower one on off, Tom Blundell blocks it back.
SIX! Sweetly connected. Fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell dances down the track and heaves it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
Flatter and on middle, Kane works off his pads but finds short leg.
Allows the ball to come close to his body and nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
Slower one, full and floated on middle, Blundell is forward as he defends it back.

Fuller and on off, Tom hurries down the track and drills it straight back. Nauman Ali goes down to stop the ball but it brushes his right hand and sneaks past the stumps at the other end as Kane turns to plant his bat inside the crease. Blundell shows interest in a run but Kane Williamson sends him back.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.

Streaky. Fuller and on off, turning away, Tom Blundell again advances down the track to flick it across the line but it takes the leading edge and goes in the air. It's again in the gap at covers and they cross.
Flatter one on off, Blundell goes on the back foot and defends.
Fullish and around off, Blundell lunges and defends it back.
Googly around off, on the shorter side, Tom punches it from the back foot to extra cover for one.
Extra flight this time, full and drifting in around off, Williamson is forward as he defends it to short leg.
Shortish and on off, Kane goes back and pushes it to covers.
Flighted delivery, pitching quite full outside off, Williamson presses forward and jams it down.
Skidding down the leg side, Blundell tries to flick but misses.

Miscues again! Full and floated around off, Tom Blundell skips down the track to heave it over the leg side but ends up dragging it off the inner edge. The ball dribbles behind square leg for a couple of runs.
Full in length around middle, Blundell lunges shows the full face of his bat in defense.

Mistimed once more! Nauman Ali serves a full ball around leg and gets it to straighten from there, Tom Blundell plays the line and tries to flick but it takes the leading edge and scoots wide of first slip. They cross.
Nauman comes from over the wicket and delivers a full ball outside leg on the rough. Williamson pads it away.
Fullish and landing outside leg, once again Kane uses his front pad to keep it out.
Going straight on after landing around off, Blundell defends it from the back foot.
Quicker through the air, again a bit short, Blundell pushes it back from the crease.
FOUR! Smacked! Tossed up, full and around middle, Tom Blundell jumps down the track and drills it past his partner at the other end for a boundary at long on.
Shortish and on middle, punched off the back foot to mid-wicket.
Loopy and full, around off, Tom defends off the front foot.
Slightly short and on middle, Blundell moves back and forces it down to mid on for a single.
A shade flatter and shorter on off, Tom Blundell defends it back from the back foot.

Well stopped by Zahid Mahmood (sub)! Fuller and on middle, Blundell whips it across the line and Zahid reacts quickly to his right from mid on. He dives to stop the racing ball and saves three runs. The 50-run stand comes up.
Full and outside leg, Williamson pads it away.

In the air but safe! Floated delivery, full and around leg, Williamson tries to sweep out of the rough but gets a top edge. It flies behind short fine leg and they cross for a run. The deficit now is 50.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Blundell defends it from the inner half of his bat.
Bowls it full and around off, Tom walks forward and then checks his shot. He defends it to covers.
FOUR! Superbly executed! Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson dances down the track and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
This one lands on off, Kane Williamson blocks it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
This one lands down leg, Kane Williamson looks to flick it but gets a rap on his pads and it bounces off the deck. Dot.
Bowls it on off, Kane Williamson drills it to long on for one.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Tom Blundell flicks it to mid on for one more.
Tosses it up down leg, Tom Blundell pads it away.
Another one outside leg, Tom Blundell defends it with his pads again.
Bowls it on middle, Tom Blundell eases it to the man at mid on.
Tossed up, on middle. Tom Blundell lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on middle, Tom Blundell looks to flick it but miscues it to covers off the leading half. They cross.
This one lands outside leg, Kane Williamson looks to defend it with his pads but misses.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tom Blundell fends it to short covers.
On a length, angling in. Tom Blundell blocks it back towards the bowler.
Another one on a length, shaping in. Tom Blundell taps it to the man at extra cover.
Bowls it fuller this time, on leg. Tom Blundell works it towards square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery, angling in. Kane Williamson offers a dead bat to it.
Fuller one on off, Kane Williamson defends it to silly mid off. Ends the over with a dot.
Tossed up, down leg, Tom Blundell pads it away.
Fuller and down leg, Tom Blundell moves forward to flick it but miscues it to cover-point. They cross.
Another one down leg, Kane Williamson defends it with his pads.
Keeps it bowling down leg, Kane Williamson puts his pads forward as the ball lobs up towards slips.
This one lands outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Another one skidding away from outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away once more.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell digs it towards mid on. Dot.
Angles in a length ball around middle, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads as the ball rolls towards point. The bowler gets excited for a moment.
Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell looks to play at it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards leg slip. They collect one.

Fuller and on middle and leg, Kane Williamson drills it down the ground. The fielder, Shan Masood, has a long chase and he stops it just before the fence by sliding. The batters collect three. With those three runs, New Zealand cross the 400-run mark.
Good-length delivery, on middle and leg, Tom Blundell defends it solidly.
On a length and on middle, Tom Blundell turns it to short leg.
Flighted and full around leg, Williamson defends it off the front foot.
Identical to the last delivery, Kane stretches forward and blocks it safely.
Fuller and around leg, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Fuller around middle and leg, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Loopy and full around leg, Blundell draws forward and defends again.
Puts it on a fuller length around off, Blundell comes down with a little shimmy and then defends it.
A length ball on off, angling into the batter, Williamson plays it with soft hands and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length around off, Kane stays on the back foot and blocks it to covers.
