Lands it on a length outside off, Williamson pushes it with an angled bat through cover-point for a single.
Drifting down the leg side, a length ball, Tom Blundell clips it through square leg and shouts 'push-push'. They do push hard and complete the second run.
Fuller and on off, shaping in a bit, Blundell drives it from the inner half and it goes straight down the ground. They cross for a run.
Full again, on off and reversing back into the batter, Kane helps it to mid-wicket to complete the over.
Extra turn and bounce from around leg, Blundell gets back to defend but misses and is hit on the back thigh.
Flighted around leg, Blundell gets forward and defends it to the leg side.

IN THE AIR... And the ball drops between the two fielders. Babar cannot believe it. Flighted delivery on middle, Tom Blundell advances down the track for a lofted shot but mishits it behind the bowler. Imam from mid on and Abrar Ahmed from mid off charge for it but then they both pull off, leaving it for each other. The batters get two runs. Imam-ul-Haq later gestures that he wanted to dive but then pulled off seeing Abrar. Hmm... there was on calling!
Fuller on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flatter on off, defended from the back foot.
Flighted around leg, it's blocked safely by Tom.
Around off, on a good length, Williamson defends from the back foot.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it solidly.
On a length around off, Kane plays late and turns it on the leg side. The fielder stops it in front of square.
Calm and composed. Full and around off, Williamson again allows the ball to come close and dead-bats it near the surface.
Wasim errs in line and delivers a full ball around leg, Williamson clips it down to fine leg for a single.
Short delivery on off, Tom swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Loopy and full, around leg, Blundell defends it off his front foot.
Very full and around leg, Blundell helps it towards square leg.
Tossed up outside leg, landing on the rough and spinning towards the batter, Blundell moves back to work it on the leg side but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.

This one turns a lot. Slower through the air, full and around off, Tom Blundell tries to drive but it spins away viciously and beats the edge. Babar Azam collects it at first slip. That was a surprise delivery as Nauman suddenly changed his line and Tom nearly fell for it.
Nauman returns bowling outside leg, Tom defends.
Full and floated on middle, Blundell lunges and defends it safely.
On a length and on middle, some extra bounce. Kane Williamson fends it to short cover.
Bowls it fuller this time, Kane Williamson drives it but finds the fielder at extra cover.
This one lands outside off, Kane Williamson steers it to point for one. There is a direct hit at the bowler's end but nothing doing.
Good-length delivery, shaping away. Tom Blundell offers a dead bat to it.
Touch fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell gets behind the line and defends it back at the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Tom Blundell looks to cut it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces off the deck.
Bowls it on middle. Kane Williamson defends it with soft hands towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
Another one outside leg, Tom Blundell defends it towards the leg side.
Bowls it fuller and on leg, Tom Blundell defends it back at the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler again.
Another one outside leg, Tom Blundell pads it away.
FOUR! Caressed! Fuller in length and outside off, Kane Williamson leans into the drive and threads the gap at extra cover for a lovely boundary. He breaks into the 90s.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.

Edgy! This one lands outside off, Kane Williamson opens the face of the bat and plays it with soft hands. It takes the outside edge and Babar Azam, at first slip, attempts to grab it diving to his right but couldn't reach it. The batters collect one.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
This one lands on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it to deep backward square leg for a brace.
Fuller and just outside off, shaping away a touch. Tom Blundell looks to drive it but misses. Close!
Tossed up, down leg. Kane Williamson sweeps it but doesn't connect well as the ball rolls towards backward square leg. Dot.
Fuller and pitching way outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Kane Williamson tucks it to square leg for one.
Around the wicket. Fuller and angling in, Tom Blundell defends it to silly mid on.
Flights it up outside off, Tom Blundell walks forward and pushes it to short cover.
Slower and outside off, Tom Blundell shapes up for the square cut but then pulls out.
Over the wicket. On a length and outside off, Kane Williamson opens the face of the bat and taps it to the gully region.
This one lands outside off as well, Kane Williamson leaves the harmless delivery.
On a length and outside off again, Kane Williamson shoulders arms at it.
Touch fuller and on leg, Kane Williamson flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Good-length delivery, angling in, Tom Blundell defends off the back foot towards mid off.
Another length ball, outside off, Tom Blundell lunges forward and pushes it towards the cover fielder.
Flighted and around off, Williamson hangs on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Flatter and shorter on off, Williamson goes on the back foot again and this time punches it past the bowler to long off. Takes a single.
Loopy one, full and around off, Tom skips down the track a bit and defends it to the off side.
Advances down the track and drives it through the line. A bit uppish but it goes safely to the cover fielder.
A shade short and on middle, Tom goes back and works it wide of mid on for a brisk run.
Floated delivery, full and on off, Williamson eases it down to long off for a single.
Angling in from around middle, Kane closes the face of his bat and works it through square leg for a single. Moves to 98!

DROPPED! Once again Imam-ul-Haq is the culprit. Fuller in length, around leg, Tom Blundell flicks across the line but fails to keep it down. It goes low to Imam at short mid-wicket and he fails to hang on to the catch.
Fuller and around off, moving in late, Blundell drives through the line but mistimes it to covers.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
On the pads, it's whipped behind square leg for a couple of runs.

OUT! LBW! Pakistan have got success in the session and Tom Blundell's lucky stay at the crease is over. The ball is reversing and Mohammad Wasim makes full use of it. He hurls it on a length around off and gets it to nip back in sharply. Tom Blundell fails to keep it out and is rapped on the back leg. They appeal and the finger goes up. Tom Blundell and Kane Williamson have a chat and then the former walks back. Only an inside edge could have saved him which was absent. The 90-run stand is broken. New Zealand trail by 11 runs. The UltraEdge, later on, shows that it's touch and go and there could have been an inside edge before it hit the back pad. New Zealand will feel that Tom should have reviewed the decision.
Howout: lbw b Mohammad Wasim

Commentary: Flighted and full on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off, Williamson punches it to covers.
Goes on the back foot and blocks it to the off side.
Jumps down the track to a full ball and flicks it to mid on for a quick run. He moves to 99 now!
Turning in from outside off, Bracewell tries to defend but misses. It goes off his pads to first slip. They appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Fuller on middle, defended from the crease to short leg.

HUNDRED FOR KANE WILLIAMSON, his 25th in Tests, 5th against Pakistan and he continues to fancy the home team. Fuller in length, around off, Kane drives it towards mid off where the fielder dives to make the stop. They cross for a run. It's been a resolute knock by him and he will love to continue and help the Kiwis in gaining a handy lead.
Pitches it up and around off, Bracewell pushes off the front foot to short cover.
Around off, on a length, Bracewell plays it with an angled bat to point.
A length ball around off, shaping in, Bracewell tries to defend but gets an inside edge. It rolls through square leg and they cross.
Outside off, played to covers.
Full and angling in around middle, Williamson flicks but finds one of the two short mid-wicket fielders.
Flighted and full, outside off, Michael Bracewell drives but finds the cover fielder.
Short and outside off, turning in, Michael goes back and defends.
FOUR! What a shot! Fuller in length and outside off, landing on the rough, Michael Bracewell wears his skates and bludgeons it through mid off for a cracking boundary.
Loopy and full, around middle, Bracewell defends it back.

Appeal for a caught behind! Not given. Loopy again, landing full outside off. It turns back in as Michael Bracewell prods forward to defend. He misses and it flies off his pads to first slip. Babar Azam takes the catch and they appeal. Nauman convinces his skipper to take the referral. The UltraEdge finds no spike. The third umpire checks for the lbw as well but the impact comes out to be well outside off.
Full and flighted on off, Bracewell lunges and defends it.
Good-length delivery, angling in, Kane Williamson presents a dead bat to it.
Fuller one and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.
Another length ball angling into the batter, Kane Williamson blocks it solidly.
On a length and on off, shaping in, Kane Williamson defends it to silly mid on.
Good-length delivery, outside off, Kane Williamson taps it to mid off.
This one lands on leg, Kane Williamson flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, on off. Kane Williamson blocks it to the vacant silly point region.
Tosses it up on middle, Kane Williamson gently sweeps it to backward square leg for one.
Tossed up, on off. Michael Bracewell defends it with soft hands back towards the bowler.

OUT! TAKEN! Tossed up, on off, some extra bounce. Michael Bracewell looks to flick it across the line but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and lobs up towards mid off. Mohammad Wasim settles under it and takes a sitter. Pakistan are making the move late in the day. The deficit is 2 runs.
Howout: c Mohammad Wasim b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Over the wicket. This one lands on leg, Kane Williamson flicks it to backward square leg for one.
On a length and on off, angling in, Ish Sodhi blocks it to mid off.
Another one on off, shaping in, Ish Sodhi defends it to short cover.
Shorter one on off, Ish Sodhi fends it back towards the bowler.

A corker of a yorker from Wasim, right in the blockhole, Sodhi somehow has his bat down in time as he digs it out off the under edge. It beats the stumps and goes to fine leg. They cross. Scores level!
Another yorker and on middle, Kane Williamson digs it back easily towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi blocks it to mid on.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Keeps bowling fuller, Ish Sodhi lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.

Fuller and on leg, staying very low, Ish Sodhi does well to keep it away off the bottom part of his bat. The ball rolls back towards the bowler. Sarfaraz Ahmed quips from behind the wickets - 'Let's shower this wicket again and roll it when Pakistan will bat!' He said that in the local language. Funny!
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Ish Sodhi hangs back and defends it back towards the bowler.
Around the wicket. Bowls it fuller and on off, Kane Williamson blocks it to the off side.
Slightly shorter one, Kane Williamson hangs back and forces it through mid off for a single. New Zealand are in the lead.
Another fuller one on middle, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, turning away, Ish Sodhi looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it away.
Another fuller one, on off. Ish Sodhi blocks it to mid off.
Slightly shorter and on off, Kane Williamson punches it through covers for a single.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it away.
This one lands outside off, Ish Sodhi pads it away. A stifled appeal is turned down.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Ish Sodhi blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Ish Sodhi defends it with his pads as the ball lobs towards the slip fielder.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi prods forward and defends it to short leg. That will be STUMPS on Day 3.
A gentle loosened to begin the day's play. Length delivery, down the leg side, Williamson tries to flick but misses.
Right on the money this time. On a length and close to off, curling in, Williamson is on the back foot as he defends it back.
Again it's on a length and just outside off, Kane plays late with an angled bat but still finds the fielder at gully who moves across to his right to stop the ball.
Wasim bends his back to go short but the line is quite wide outside off, Williamson leans back a shade and makes a leave.
This time it's full and around off, angling into the batter, Kane is behind the line in defense.
Back of a length on off, Williamson punches from the back foot to mid on. Wasim begins Day 4 with a maiden.
Begins with a loopy delivery, full and around off, Sodhi defends it back off the front foot.
A touch quicker, full and on middle at 89.1 kph, Sodhi again is on the front foot in defense.
Flighted one, full and around leg, Sodhi flicks it a bit aerially but it goes safely to mid-wicket.
Fuller around off, defended off the outer part of the bat to the off side.
Slower this time, full and around off, again Ish defends it without any fuss.

Just about carried to gully. Loopy and full, around off and spinning away late, Sodhi tries to defend but it takes a soft outside edge and goes on the bounce to the fielder at gully.  This fielder had moved from silly point before this delivery and that move nearly worked.
Lands it on a length, close to off, Kane opens the face of his bat and pushes it to gully.
Serves it on a length, close to off, Williamson defends it from the back foot. Not much reverse happening for Wasim at the moment.
Pitches it up and around off, Williamson doesn't move a lot from the crease and just pushes it towards mid off.
A hint of inward shape on this delivery, on a length and curving back in from around off, Williamson covers the movement and defends it out.
Very full and around off, 134 kph, Williamson blocks it with firm hands to mid off.
First run on Day 4! Wasim serves a full ball on the pads, Williamson clips it behind square leg and keeps strike with a single.
Abrar delivers it full and down the leg side, Williamson eases it with his sweep shot and the ball travels to long leg. The batters cross.
Tossed up around middle, sliding in, Sodhi defends it down in front of short leg.
Almost chips it into the hands of short mid-wicket. Flatter one, around leg, Sodhi flicks late and finds the gap past short mid-wicket. Two runs.
Fuller and on middle, Ish works it behind towards short fine leg and picks up a single.
Flighted delivery, landing full outside off, Williamson leans and pushes it through covers for one.
This one goes straight on after landing full around off, Sodhi gets his bat down and defends it near his front pad.
Bangs it shorter and on off, Kane Williamson pulls it gently through mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly short, just outside off. Ish Sodhi taps it to the mid off region.

Touch fuller and on leg, Ish Sodhi nudges it through mid-wicket. The fielder has a long chase to do in the deep. The batters collect three runs off it. That was uppish but through the gap between a couple of close-in fielders at short mid-wicket. 450 up for New Zealand.
Bowls it on off, fuller in length. Kane Williamson drives it straight back towards the bowler.
Good-length delivery, on off, Kane Williamson defends it to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Fuller one this time, Kane Williamson eases it to the man at mid-wicket. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi defends it to the silly point region.
Another fuller one, this is defended back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Ish Sodhi defends it off his back foot.
Fuller one on leg, Ish Sodhi blocks it back towards the bowler.

In the air but lands safely. This is slower and on leg, Ish Sodhi looks to flick it but mistimes it completely. The ball lobs up in the air off the top edge but lands safely at the vacant short fine leg region. They cross.
This one lands on off, Kane Williamson blocks it to the cover fielder.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Ish Sodhi leaves it alone.
Fuller length and on off, Ish Sodhi defends it to the mid on fielder.
On a length and on middle, Ish Sodhi blocks it to the man at short mid-wicket.
A yorker right into the blockhole, Ish Sodhi manages to keep his bat down as the ball deflects off the inside half to his legs.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi eases it to mid off.
Another fuller one, on middle and leg. Ish Sodhi blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson plays it to the man at short leg.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Kane Williamson taps it but finds the man at point.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson blocks it to mid on.
Turning in a bit from outside off, Kane Williamson reads it well and lets it go.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson defends this off the front foot.
Bowls it on off this time, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it solidly.
Bangs a bouncer outside off, Ish Sodhi leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fine shot to bring up the first boundary of the morning. Slightly shorter and outside off, shaping away. Ish Sodhi hangs back and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
On a length and on off, Ish Sodhi defends this to the mid off fielder.

LATE CALL TO TAKE THE DRS! There's an appeal for an lbw but the finger stays down. Wasim spears in a very full ball around off, at 140 clicks, Sodhi tries to defend it with a straight bat but fails to middle it. He is pinged on the front pad, they appeal but to no avail. Mohammad Wasim is not too sure and Babar Azam hesitantly takes the review at the last second. The UltraEdge finds a spike. Pakistan lose another review, they are left with none now.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi blocks it to short cover.
Another fuller one and on leg, Sodhi eases it to the man at mid on.
Flighted and full, drifting in, Williamson stretches forward and defends it down safely.
Slightly short and on off, Kane goes on the back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Extra loop on this delivery, landing full around off, Sodhi presses forward in defense.
Quicker this time, around off and skidding in at 89.7 kph, Sodhi goes on the back foot and blocks it at the last moment.
Hangs on the back foot and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, full in length, Sodhi remains back and plays it down towards silly point.
Begins with a flighted delivery, landing full on off, Kane Williamson defends it back off the front foot.
Loopy and full, around off, Williamson gently pushes it wide of the cover fielder and pinches a single.
Fuller and on off, Sodhi defends it back to the bowler.
Again it's full and around leg, Sodhi keeps it out safely towards short mid-wicket.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball and pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Nauman keeps it full and in line with the stumps, Sodhi is content in defending it with a straight blade.
FOUR! Excellent shot! First signs of aggression from Williamson. He gives the charge to a full ball landing in his half and cleanly lifts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
The last shot prompts for a change in length and Williamson is waiting on the back foot. He punches the short ball to sweeper cover for a single.
Fuller and on off, defended back.
Quicker and fuller on off, at 92.3 kph, Sodhi defends it watchfully.
Going down the leg side, Ish works it off his pads but finds the fielder at short fine leg.
Keeps it flat and around middle, Sodhi stays back and defends it with firm hands to short mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery, landing full around leg and straightening, Kane goes on the back foot and defends it down at the last moment.

GIVEN LBW! Kane Williamson takes the DRS immediately. Nauman Ali gives this one some extra flight and serves it very full around leg. Kane goes down to sweep but fails to connect cleanly. He is hit on the front pad, they appeal and the finger goes up. It's time for the DRS. UltraEdge shows that there is a gap between the bat and the ball. Ball Tracking then goes on to show that it has PITCHED OUTSIDE LEG. The on-field decision is overturned and Williamson survives, all thanks to the technology.
Loopy delivery, full and on off, Kane is on the front foot as he pushes it defensively to covers.
Lunges to a full ball and pushes it to the off side, finds the cover fielder.
Again Kane is drawn forward to a full ball on off and he drives it towards the cover fielder.
Floated and full, around leg, Williamson walks forward and blocks. A rare maiden from Nauman.
Fuller around off, Ish brings his bat ahead of the front pad in defense.
Very full and on middle, defended to the leg side.
Too full and on off, Sodhi brings a straight bat and blocks it.
Floated and around off, Sodhi draws forward and defends it with an angled bat to point.
Keeps it full and on off, Ish is forward as he defends again.

FOUR! Shot! The invitation is there and Sodhi latches onto it. Extra flight this time from Ahmed, trying to lure the batter by serving it full and wide outside off, Ish drills his drive through covers for a boundary. The lead moves to 28.
Fuller one and on off, Kane Williamson leans forward and drives it through mid off for a single.
Bowls it fuller again, Ish Sodhi blocks it to silly point.
Bowls it on middle this time, Ish Sodhi defends it back towards the bowler.
Full and outside off, Ish Sodhi digs it to the mid off region.
This one lands outside leg, Ish Sodhi looks to tickle it but misses.
Fuller and on middle, with a hint of turn, Ish Sodhi presents a dead bat to it.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Kane Williamson eases it to the man at short leg.
Another fuller one, down leg. Kane Williamson sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
Full and on middle, Ish Sodhi defends off the front foot back at the bowler.
Bowls it just outside off, Ish Sodhi blocks it to the left of the bowler.
Fuller again, on middle and leg. Ish Sodhi eases it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Outside off, turning away, Ish Sodhi hangs back and defends it to silly point.
Bowls it outside off, turning away, Kane Williamson leaves the harmless delivery.
This one lands down leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Another one down leg, Kane Williamson defends it with his pads.
Fuller one on middle, Kane Williamson sweeps it towards deep square leg for one.
Fuller and around middle, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it away.
Oh, turn and some extra bounce from outside leg, Ish Sodhi decides to block it with the pads but due to the extra bounce, it hits his ribs and bounces off the deck.
Bowls it on off, Kane Williamson taps it to the man at extra cover.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson eases it to covers.
Another fuller one, on off, Kane Williamson drills it to long off for a single.
This one lands on middle and leg, Ish Sodhi blocks it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi hangs back and defends it to short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter one, on middle, Ish Sodhi defends it with soft hands back towards the bowler.
Over the wicket. Bowls it outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Fuller and on middle, Kane Williamson sweeps it towards deep backward square leg for one.

Catch it is the call! This is slightly shorter, it keeps a tad low. Ish Sodhi looks to pull it but gets a top edge as the ball carries towards backward square leg and lands just short of the fielder in the deep. Luckily for Ish, it didn't go into the hands. They collect one.

Another chance is created but the ball drops just short of the fielder. Fuller and on leg, Kane Williamson looks to sweep it from the rough but gets a top edge as the ball lobs towards the short fine leg region. Shan Masood tries his best but it falls in front of him.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it away.
Loopy and landing outside the leg side, Kane pads it away.
Floated and full around off, Sodhi presses forward and defends it back.

Aerial but again the batter is safe. Loopy delivery, full and around off, Sodhi top-edges his attempted sweep and looks down in disappointment. It flies to the right of short fine leg and falls safely. They get a run.
Quicker and around leg, it's worked to deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Flatter and shorter on off, punched off the back foot to covers.
Around leg, full in length, Kane helps it to mid-wicket.
Gets forward to a full ball and pushes it softly to short cover.
Tossed up outside leg, Sodhi pads it away.
Another delivery landing in the rough outside leg, Sodhi tries to pad it away again but misses. A good take by Sarfaraz Ahmed.
Quicker and very full outside leg, Sodhi steps back and drives it to mid off.
Beauty to beat the bat! Floated one, full and landing in the rough outside leg, Sodhi lunges to defend but it beats the bat and goes just over the top of the off stump. Nauman is in disbelief.
FOUR! Well played! Nauman is a bit on the shorter side, landing around leg and turning away a shade, Sodhi uses the depth of his crease and spanks it through covers.
Floated around leg, too full in length, it's defended back to the bowler.
Slow spin away from the batter around off, Williamson plays late with soft hands but fails to beat the first slip fielder.
Quicker and shorter on off, Kane moves back and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Nicely flighted around off, a touch short in length, Ish gets back and defends it.
Flatter and on off, defended off the back foot again.
Fires it full and around leg, again Ish defends it from deep inside the crease.
Serves it around off, Sodhi stays back and punches it towards the bowler.
Ali continues to target the rough outside leg, the length is a bit short this time and Kane nudges it wide of short fine leg for a run.
Down the leg side, Ish tries to flick but misses. Sarfaraz Ahmed fails to gather the ball cleanly.
Loopy and full, around leg and spinning away viciously, Sodhi is beaten as he prods forward to defend. Sarfaraz Ahmed fails to collect and they steal a bye.
Superbly executed. Full and flighted, outside leg, Kane Williamson reverse-sweeps out of the rough and sends it to deep cover. They get three runs.
Flighted and outside leg, Sodhi pads it away with ease.
Flatter and around leg, Sodhi defends it with the turn to the off side.
Tossed up around middle, defended on the leg side.
Around off, driven through covers for a single. The 50-run stand comes up!
Quicker and on off, defended from the back foot.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it back.
Full around off, the batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Short and on off, Ish punches but finds the fielder at cover-point. The third new ball is due now.
This one lands outside leg, Kane Williamson looks to reverse-sweep it but misses.
Pitches this outside the leg stump, Kane Williamson pads it away.

Five penalty runs! Flighted delivery, down the leg side, Williamson tries to sweep but misses. Sarfaraz Ahmed fails to grab and it goes through his legs to hit the helmet kept behind him on the ground. The lead crosses 50!
Fuller and on leg, Kane Williamson reverse-sweeps it to deep cover for a brace.
Goes for the reverse sweep but misses the ball here as it goes towards the keeper.
Fuller and outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Around leg, defended.
Fuller and on off, Sodhi defends it away.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Sodhi cuts it away through the point region and the ball races away to the fence in no time.
Fuller and on leg, Sodhi looks to flick it but misses as the ball hits his pads and rolls towards the leg side. They cross for a leg bye.
Fuller on the stumps, Williamson defends it to the mid-wicket region.
Fuller one as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one as this is again defended towards the bowler.
Fuller on the stumps, Sodhi defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on leg,  Sodhi tucks it away to short fine leg for a single.
Short of a length and on off, Kane Williamson eases it to the point fielder.
Outside off, this is played towards covers for a single. 500 comes up!
Fuller and on middle, this is pushed to the man at point.
Outside off, blocked at mid off.
This one lands outside leg, shaping away, Kane Williamson leaves the harmless delivery.
Touch fuller and outside leg, Kane Williamson looks to tickle it but misses.
Bowls it fuller and just outside off, Kane Williamson drives it towards deep cover for a single.

EDGED AND FOUR! On a length with some extra bounce, outside off. Ish Sodhi opens the face of the bat and looks to guide it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball races away to the third man fence. Lucky boundary!
A yorker right into the blockhole, Ish Sodhi digs it to the man at point.
Fuller one, angling in, Ish Sodhi reads it well and blocks it to short cover.
Tossed up, outside off, turning away. Kane Williamson slaps it to deep cover for a single.

FOUR! Slightly shorter and outside off, Ish Sodhi hangs back and cuts it through covers as the ball races away to the fence. Hasan Ali gives the chase but he loses the battle as the ball teasingly goes to the fence.
Fuller and on middle, Ish Sodhi defends it back towards the bowler.
Another one on middle, Ish Sodhi again defends it towards the bowler.
Fuller one and on middle, Ish Sodhi lunges and offers a dead bat to it.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Ish Sodhi eases it to the fielder at short cover.
Hurls across a length ball around off, angling in from 'round the wicket, Williamson remains on the back foot and guides it through point for a single.
Beaten! Hamza pitches it up and outside off, Sodhi pushes inside the line and misses.
FOUR! That's a nice shot. Full in length outside off, inviting the drive, Sodhi reaches out and strokes it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
Well played! A length ball around off, Sodhi wrists it through square leg and rotates the strike.
Back of a length around off, holding its line a touch, Williamson hangs his bat out pointlessly and it whistles past the outside edge.
Delivers it full and outside off, Kane gets forward and drives it in the gap at sweeper cover for two runs.
Flighted delivery, on middle, Sodhi works it towards short fine leg and takes a single.
Floated and full, drifting in around middle, Kane flicks it towards short leg.
Skidding in around off, Williamson goes back and keeps it away off the inner edge. It goes wide of short leg.
Full and around off, staying low, Kane moves back and pushes it to point.
Gentle hands. Full again, on off, Williamson pushes it off the front foot to covers.
Flatter and in line with the stumps, Williamson is on the back foot in defense.
Fullish and on middle, defended back safely.
Turning in from around off, Sodhi helps it off his pads to mid-wicket.
Very full and on off, Sodhi digs it out to point.
Fuller and around leg, Sodhi turns it calmly to short leg.
Gets on the front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted and full, around off, Sodhi defends it off the front foot to covers. That will be LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Runs straightaway although leg byes. Skidding down the leg side, Williamson tries to sweep but misses. It deflects off his pads to fine leg for two leg byes.
Flighted and full, around off, Kane is on the front foot in defense.
Shortish and on off, punched off the back foot to mid on.
Slightly fuller on off, Kane gets forward and pushes it to covers.
Fullish around off, turning in, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and pushes it with hard hands, back to the bowler.
Angles in a length ball on off, Sodhi stays back and helps it off his pads to short mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, Ish tickles it behind square leg for a run.
Back of a length, around off, Kane goes on the back foot and taps it down on the surface.
Fuller and around off, defended back.
On a length and close to off, Williamson plays it down to the left side of the cover fielder and pinches a single.
A bit short in length and outside off, going straight on, Sodhi remains on the back foot and lets it be.
Over the wicket. Bowls it fuller and on off, Kane Williamson lunges and blocks it to short cover.
Bowls it on middle, Kane Williamson hangs back and blocks it towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson moves forward and drives it uppishly towards deep extra cover for one.
This one lands outside off, Ish Sodhi looks to cut it but misses.
Another one outside off with some turn, Ish Sodhi looks to slap it but misses.
FOUR! Connects well this time. Tossed up, wide outside off. Ish Sodhi hangs back and slashes it through backward point for a boundary.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it solidly towards mid on.
Full-length delivery, angling in from outside off. Kane Williamson drives it but finds the man at covers.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson tucks it towards mid-wicket for a brace. Good running between the wickets.
Touch fuller and outside off, shaping away. Kane Williamson looks to defend it with soft hands but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards short fine leg. They cross.
Fuller and just outside off, Ish Sodhi blocks it to short cover.
Fuller one, angling in. Ish Sodhi defends off the front foot down to mid off.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter one, on middle, slower too. Kane Williamson rocks back and pulls it through the square leg region for a boundary.
Shorter and on off, Kane Williamson cuts it through covers for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi eases it to the man at point.

FOUR! Fifty up for Ish Sodhi. This is fuller and outside off, Ish Sodhi uses the pace of the ball and guides it through to third man for a boundary. 4th fifty in Tests for Ish Sodhi and the lead has also gone over 100.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi pushes it to covers.
Fuller and down leg, Ish Sodhi looks to flick it but gets a rap on his pads. It rolls towards the leg side as the batters cross for a leg bye.
Around the wicket. Length ball, outside off. Ish Sodhi pushes it towards point.
Fuller and on off, Ish Sodhi pushes it towards the right of mid on for a single.
On a length and outside off, shaping away a touch. Kane Williamson looks to block it but misses.

FOUR! Good-length delivery, outside off. Kane Williamson uses the pace of the ball and just guides it through to third man for a boundary. 150 up for Kane Williamson, this is the 9th time he has done so in Test cricket!
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.
Another fuller one, down leg. Kane Williamson flicks it straight to the man at square leg.
Tossed up, on middle, Ish Sodhi lunges and blocks it to mid off.

Miscommunication but no harm is done. Slower one, on leg. Ish Sodhi pushes it towards short mid-wicket and looks for a run. He is midway down the track but Kane Williamson shouts a big NO and sends him back. The bowler gets to the ball and fires in a throw but it's a bit weak and Ish returns with a clumsy dive. Williamson is now seen having a word with his partner.
Fuller and on middle, Ish Sodhi tucks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Skidding away on leg, Ish works it to deep square leg for a single.
This one lands on off, Kane Williamson defends it back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Kane Williamson strides forward to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball goes past the first slip fielder, and through to the third-man fence. Lucky boundary!
Tossed up, full and on off, Ish defends it back.
Arm ball around leg, Ish tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to short fine leg and they cross for a leg bye.
FOUR! Played well in the end. Another arm ball, around middle and leg and staying low, Kane does well to stands back and nudge it fine down the leg side for a boundary at fine leg.
Loopy and around off, turning away, Williamson defends it away with gentle hands on the off side.

FOUR! Fantastic shot! Kane Williamson has looked in control whenever he has advanced down the track. Full and flighted, around off and turning away, Williamson shimmies down and lofts it over mid on for a boundary. Lead - 122.
Slower through the air, outside off and breaking away a bit late, Williamson fiddles with it, inside the line and gets beaten.
Begins with a full ball on off, angling in, Sodhi plays it nice and late as he defends it ahead of his front pad.
On a good length outside off, Ish stays back and plays it down to point.
Fuller and on off, driven off the front foot to covers.
Puts it on a fuller length again, around off, once again Sodhi brings a straight bat down in defense.
EDGY FOUR! Wasim plants this delivery on a fuller length outside off, Sodhi gets forward to drive away from his body but it catches the outside edge and scoots past gully for a boundary.
Wasim is too straight with his line on this occasion and Sodhi works it to deep square leg for a run.
Loopy and full, landing around off, Ish Sodhi defends it back.
Fuller again, around off, Ish pushes it out off the outer half to point.
A touch flatter and around off, Sodhi forces it off the front foot to short cover.
Slower through the air this time, around off, Sodhi brings his front foot forward and defends it to the off side.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

Direct hit would have been close! Nauman gives this one some extra air and lands it full around off, Sodhi whips it wide of mid on and scampers across to the other end. Mohammad Wasim has a shy but misses and Ish makes it safely. The replays show that Sodhi would have been a goner in case of a direct hit.
Wasim has decided to operate from 'round the wicket. Serves a short ball around off, angling away, Ish Sodhi stays deep inside the crease and allows it through.
Short and around leg, Sodhi is on his toes as he keeps it out to mid on.
Down the leg side, on a shortish length and staying low, Sodhi tries to pull but it goes below his bat.

Effort ball from over the wicket. Wasim bangs it in short, around off, Sodhi is taken by surprise and fends it off from the shoulder of his bat. There is no silly point in place otherwise it would have been a simple catch. Now, silly point has come in.
Good energy on this delivery as well. Short but it's down the leg side, Ish gets across and allows it through to the keeper.
This is really good from Wasim. Hurls across another short ball around the rib cage of the batter, Sodhi fends it down wide of short leg. End of a probing over.
Loopy and full, landing outside leg, Williamson pads it away.
FOUR! Fine execution! Floated delivery, full and close to leg, Kane Williamson brings out the reverse sweep and nails it down to deep backward point for a boundary. Lead - 132.
FOUR! And again, this time in front of square for another boundary. Kane Williamson fetches it from outside leg and reverse-sweeps it firmly to the deep cover fence.
Misses this time! Nauman continues to serves it outside leg, this time Kane fails to connect with his attempted reverse-batted shot.
Miscued! Too full and just outside leg, Williamson goes down with the conventional sweep but fails to make connection.
Misses again! Nauman continues to bowl full and outside off, Kane initially shapes up for the reverse sweep and then tries to push it away on the leg side but misses. Got into a tangle.

Change of plans from Mohammad Wasim and he is having Sodhi in all sorts of trouble. Bangs a bouncer, well-directed, Ish Sodhi looks to pull it but the ball hits his right shoulder and lobs towards the off side at backward point.
FOUR! Sodhi has decided to fight fire with fire. Shorter and around off, Ish Sodhi hangs back and pulls it through backward square leg as the ball races away to the fence.
Shorter again, on middle. Ish Sodhi fends it back down on the surface.
Bowls it shorter again, Ish Sodhi ducks underneath it.
Fuller one this time, on leg. Ish Sodhi works it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Slightly shorter one, on off. Ish Sodhi defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Another one outside leg, Kane Williamson defends it with his pads again.
Fuller and outside leg, Kane Williamson sweeps it but finds the man at short fine leg.
Bowls it outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away again.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it to the man at short fine leg.
Fuller and down leg, Kane Williamson defends it with his pads again.
Shorter and on middle, Ish Sodhi fends it to short leg.
Bowls it fuller, on middle and leg, Ish Sodhi works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Shorter and on off, Kane Williamson gently pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Bangs it in short, Sodhi jumps and uses every inch of his height as he defends it down with a loose bottom hand. Has a big smile on his face. Good technique.
Slightly shorter one, Ish Sodhi flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Sodhi defends it to the short mid-wicket fielder.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson sweeps it but gets a top edge. The ball lands safely at deep mid-wicket and the batters collect two.
Fuller and on the pads, Williamson sweeps it to the short fine leg region.
This one lands outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Flighted and outside leg stump, Kane Williamson looks to sweep it but misses.
Bowls it on leg, Kane Williamson reverse-sweeps it through point for a brace.
Fuller and on the pads, Kane Williamson sweeps it away to the fielder at short fine leg.
Shorter and on off, Ish Sodhi leaves it alone.
Another shorter one, Ish Sodhi pulls it towards deep square leg for one. This is now Sodhi's highest Test score.
Bowls it shorter again, Kane Williamson pulls it in front of square on the leg side and picks up another single.
Bangs a short ball outside off, Ish Sodhi pulls it and keeps it down. The ball rolls towards deep square leg as the batters collect one.
Touch fuller and just outside off, Kane Williamson drives it but finds the man at short cover.
Short of a length and on middle, Kane Williamson pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for one. Lead - 150.
Full and flighted, outside leg, Williamson calmly sweeps but finds short fine leg.
Tossed up outside leg, Kane pads it away this time. Pakistan going through the motions now.

EDGY FOUR! Flighted delivery, landing full around leg, Kane Williamson tries to play the reverse sweep out of the rough but it takes the top edge and flies over the leaping slip fielder for a boundary.
Fuller and outside leg, Kane keeps his bat away and pads it on the leg side.
Wide! Way down the leg side, no spin there and Williamson leaves. Called a wide.
Fuller around leg, Kane defends it off the front foot to point.
Flatter and on the pads, it's tucked away through square leg for a single.

Loopy delivery, full and on middle, Williamson is on the front foot as he defends it to the leg side. He played it alright there as there was a fly that has gone into his eyes while pressing forward in defense.
On the pads, nudged to square leg for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan have their first wicket of the day but the stand between Ish Sodhi and Kane Williamson has done the damage. Floated delivery, full and on middle at 81.7 kph, Ish Sodhi attempts to take on the leg spinner and tries to heave it across the line. But it comes off from the top half of his blade and flies behind the bowler. Babar Azam is there at mid off and he takes the catch safely. New Zealand lead by 157 runs and still have three wickets remaining.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Flighted on middle, defended back.
Around off, on a fuller length, Southee defends it to the off side.

Shout for a run out at the bowler's end, taken upstairs. Full and around off, Southee forces it straight back and it kisses the hands of the bowler before going on to break the stumps at the other end. They appeal and the third umpire comes into play. The replays find that Kane has his bat planted inside the crease.
Flatter and around leg, Williamson works it through square leg for a single.
Short and close to off, Tim cuts but finds point.

OUT! Southee holes out! Pakistan have two wickets in no time, something to smile about for the home audience. Tossed up, full and around middle and off, Tim Southee gives the charge for a big shot but his bottom hand comes off the handle and the ball flies from the bottom part of his bat. It's a simple catch for Shan Masood at long off. Williamson is 15 away from his double century but is running out of partners now.
Howout: c Shan Masood b Nauman Ali

Commentary: Flatter and on off, short in length, Wagner goes on the back foot and defends it to short mid-wicket.
Turning into the batter from outside off, again the length is short and Wagner defends it from the back foot.
A touch fuller this time, around off, Wagner again defends it from the back foot.
Fullish and angling down the leg side, Kane sweeps it to fine leg and picks up a single.
This one is generously tossed up by Abrar, full and dipping in around off, Wagner pushes it defensively to covers.
Fuller and on off, at 84 kph, Wagner defends it to short leg.
Shout for an lbw, not given. Flighted around middle, spinning down, Neil Wagner tries to play the reverse sweep but misses. Going down, perhaps! Pakistan have no reviews left.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

OUT! TAKEN! Abrar has yet another 5-wicket haul in Tests, it has been a long hard toil but it has paid dividends. Flighted and full, around off, Wagner again attempts to play the reverse sweep but this time it catches his gloves and loops behind the keeper. Agha Salman takes a simple catch moving across from slip. This is the third wicket gone done in this manner in this inning. New Zealand lead by 159 runs.
Howout: c Agha Salman b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Wide! This one is down the leg side, Williamson leaves.
Flighted and down the leg side, Kane pads it away.
Action replay of the previous delivery. Williamson is not taking any chances so far.
Another one down the leg side and Williamson feels it's not worthy to touch his bat. Pads it away.
Down the leg side, again the batter pads it away.
Flatter delivery, close to leg, Williamson moves back and works it to deep square leg for a run. Ajaz has one ball to survive.

Huge shout for a bat-pad but the umpire remains unmoved. No reviews left for Pakistan. Floated one, full and around off, Patel tries to defend but it spins back in to beat his bat. It pops out off his pads and the short leg fielder catches the ball. They appeal but to no avail. The replays find no inside edge. It was Patel's bat brushing the inside part of his pad.
Fuller and on off, turning away, Kane Williamson looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

SIX! All the way. Tosses it on the middle stump line, Kane Williamson dances down the track and lofts it over long on for a maximum. Kane Williamson moves to 193 now! This is the third time he has ventured into this territory against Pakistan in Tests. He has a double century against them and also got out on 192 once, in Sharjah.
This one lands down leg, Kane Williamson looks to sweep it but misses.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Kane Williamson moves forward and tucks it to mid-wicket.
This one lands outside off, Kane Williamson hangs back and guides it towards covers for one. Ajaz Patel has one ball to survive again.

SHOUT FOR AN LBW! This one lands just outside off, Ajaz Patel moves forward to defend it but gets beaten and gets a rap on his back pad. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Pakistan are out of reviews! The replays show that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's the same for hitting the wickets.
This one lands outside leg, Kane pads it away.
Bowls it down leg, Kane Williamson moves forward to defend it with pads but leaves it alone in the end.
Another one outside leg, Kane Williamson pads it away.
Pitching outside leg, Kane Williamson looks to paddle it but misses.
Bowls it outside leg, Kane Williamson paddles it but finds the man at short fine leg.
Bowls it outside leg, Kane Williamson reverse-sweeps it to point for one. He keeps strike for the next over.
Bowls it on middle, Kane Williamson eases it to the man at point.
This one lands on middle and leg, Kane Williamson defends it to mid on.
Slightly shorter one, Kane Williamson hangs back and punches it down to short extra covers.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson defends it to mid on.
Tosses it up, on middle. Kane Williamson blocks it back towards the bowler.
Flatter and on leg, Kane Williamson moves forward and drives it straight back at the bowler this time. Pakistan have an entire over to bowl at Ajaz Patel now.
Tossed up, on off, angling in, Ajaz Patel lunges to defend but it beats his bat and strikes him on the pads. Outside the line of the stumps though.
Another one on off, Ajaz Patel defends it to the vacant silly point region again.
Bowls it outside off, turning in, Ajaz Patel looks to defend it but gets a hit on his pads. A loud appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. Impact is outside off, clearly.
Fuller and on middle, Ajaz Patel blocks it to short leg.
Tosses it outside off, Patel defends off the front foot towards gully.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Patel lunges to defend again but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and on off, Kane Williamson defends it to mid off.
Another fuller one, on middle, Kane Williamson blocks it to mid off again.
Bowls it on off, Kane Williamson eases it to mid off again.
FOUR! Slower through the air and fuller on off, Kane Williamson moves forward and lofts it over extra cover for a boundary. He moves to 199 now!

FIFTH DOUBLE CENTURY IN TESTS FOR WILLIAMSON, the most by a Kiwi batter! It's been a resolute knock from the former skipper. Unmatched brilliance. A spectacle that everyone has enjoyed. He reaches there by nudging a full ball through square leg for a single. The New Zealand dressing room is on its feet and Tim Southee has decided to declare on 612/9.
Southee begins with a full delivery, outside off and landing on the seam. Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone and it carries nicely to the keeper.
An outswinger on this occasion, on a length outside off and shaping away a hit, Abdullah Shafique stays back and lets it go.
Southee pitches it up and close to off, shaping away a hint again, Abdullah Shafique is on the front foot as he is forced to defend it on the off side.
Pakistan are away! Southee goes very straight in his line, Shafique flicks it through the gap at mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs.
Nice delivery, this one is on and around off, on a fuller length and going straight on, Abdullah covers his stumps and makes a leave.
In the channel outside off, once again this one holds its line, Abdullah Shafique shoulders arms. A decent start from Southee.
Flighted delivery, full and on off, Imam walks forward and drives it to mid off.
A bit of spin into the batter from the rough outside off, Imam inside-edges his attempted drive past short leg to backward square leg.
A touch short around off, Imam goes back to play at it and gets it away off the outer half. The ball rolls wide of backward point and they cross.
Loopy and full, around off, Abdullah is on the front foot as he defends to the off side.
Perhaps the arm ball, around middle, Abdullah Shafique tucks it away through mid-wicket for a single.
Too full in length, Imam digs it out back towards the bowler.
Fuller in length around off, shaping in a bit, Abdullah Shafique gets forward a bit and works it off his pads to wide mid on.
Keeps it full and around off, Shafique strides forward and defends it nice and late towards mid off.
Once again Southee bowls it full and around off, 128.5 clicks, Shafique is solid in his front-foot defense.
This one is a tempter! Southee sprays it fuller and wider outside off, throws the bait but Abdullah Shafique decides not to chase it away from his body.
Southee gets close to off, not close enough to bother the batter though. It's on a length and Abdullah allows it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Streaky! Southee delivers it on a fuller length around off, shaping away a bit. Abdullah Shafique presses forward to defend with a loose bottom hand but it takes the outer edge and races away to the fence at third man.
Extra flight there, full and landing in the rough outside off, Imam pushes it down to mid on.
A bit quicker and shorter on off, Imam goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Once again Imam goes on the back foot and plays it with the spin to short mid-wicket.
Too full and around off, Imam is drawn forward in defense.
Beaten! Fuller and just outside off, going straight on with the arm, Imam leans forward looking to defend with the spin but it skids through and beats the outside edge.
FOUR! Nice footwork! Tossed up outside off, full in length, Imam advances down the track and drives it crisply through covers for a boundary.

ALMOST A RETURN CATCH! Southee hurls across a length ball around off, Shafique gets forward and drives through the line but fails to keep it down. It goes aerially but just wide of the outstretched left hand of Southee. He enquires with Imam whether that was a slower one, as picked by the stump mic.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and on off, Abdullah Shafique defends it close to the front pad.
In the zone outside off, on a good length and shaping in, Abdullah Shafique covers his stumps and leaves.
Pitches it up and on off, Abdullah drives down the ground but finds mid on.
Again the length is full and it's close to off, Abdullah presses forward and drives it to mid off. End of a probing over!
Turning in from outside off, slightly shorter and quicker too. Imam-ul-Haq shuffles across to defend it but gets an inside edge. It goes through his legs to backward square leg.
Fuller on the stumps, Imam defends it by getting forward.
Tosses it up here, Imam drives it to the mid on region.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to mid on again.
Bowls it on middle, Imam-ul-Haq drives it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it away.
Flatter and on middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique tucks it to the man at short leg.
Fuller and on leg, Abdullah Shafique flicks it towards the fielder at backward square leg.
On middle this time, Abdullah Shafique blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and eases it to short cover.
This one lands on off, it keeps a tad low. Abdullah Shafique hangs back and plays it with soft hands past first slip. They cross.
Fuller and on the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to the short cover fielder.
Tossed up, on leg. Abdullah Shafique blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it on off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and defends it solidly.
Fuller and on middle, slower too. Abdullah Shafique blocks it towards short mid-wicket.
Slower one turning away, Abdullah Shafique looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Slows this one up in the air, lands it full and gets it to drift into the batter around off, Abdullah gets forward to defend but is beaten by the away spin.
Fuller on the pads, Abdullah Shafique clips it away towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Tosses it up on middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique flicks it towards backward square leg. Dot.
Fuller and on leg, Abdullah Shafique flicks it to square leg for one.
Tosses it up, slower through the air. Imam-ul-Haq prods forward and blocks it away.
Fuller and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to block it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards backward square leg. They cross.
Another fuller one and around off, Abdullah Shafique blocks it watchfully.
Ths one lands outside off, Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone.
Bowls it fuller and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and flicks it to the man at mid on.
FOUR! Perfectly timed. Fuller and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq dances down the track and drives it through extra covers for a boundary.
Another one outside off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it to short cover.
Tosses it up on middle, Abdullah Shafique lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller on the stumps, Abdullah Shafique defends it to mid off.
Slightly shorter one, Abdullah Shafique shuffles across to cut it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces off the deck. Ends with a dot.
Fullish and around off, Imam bunts it down to mid off and scampers across to the other end.
Spinning in from around off, Abdullah Shafique plays it off his pads and it goes on one bounce to leg gully.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted and on off, turning in, Shafique flicks it but finds the fielder in front of square on the leg side.
Uses the spin on this delivery and works it to short mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Abdullah draws forward and defends it with soft hands.
Slower through the air, full and landing in the rough outside off, Imam skips down the track and drives it past the bowler to mid off.
Edgy! Spinning in from outside off, Imam keeps his bat close to his front pad in defense and gets it away off the outside edge. The ball dribbles through point and they take two runs.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A full toss on off, Imam does not waste the chance there and forces it down to long on for a boundary.
FOUR! Better shot this time! Floated delivery, full and outside off, Imam drives it out of the rough and strokes it through the gap between extra cover and mid off.
Slower one, full and close to off, Imam defends off the front foot.
Lunges to a full ball and defends it right under his eyes. 10 from the over!
Slightly uppish but it goes safely to the fielder. Southee bowls it on a length and outside off, Abdullah drives it on the up towards point.
Full and angling in around off, Abdullah plays it towards mid on.
Shaping back into the batter from a length around off, Abdullah Shafique defends it from the inner half to short mid-wicket.
Pitches it up and outside off, Abdullah presses forward to drive but mistimes it badly. It takes the inside half and rolls to mid on.
Flicks this length ball with the angle of the bowler but finds the fielder at wide mid on.
A gentle length delivery outside off, Abdullah Shafique leaves it alone and it dies on its way to the keeper.
Floated and full, around middle, Imam wrists it in front of square on the leg side and gets a single.
Serves it full and outside off, not turning much, Abdullah Shafique tries to defend it with soft hands but it goes off the outside edge to third man. They take three runs.
Beaten! A hint of away spin from around off, Imam lunges to defend but it beats the bat.
Fuller and on off, Imam covers the line and defends it to the off side.
Around off, some extra bounce, Imam plays it down safely to backward point.
Slower through the air, full and outside off, Imam drives and the silly point fielder jumps to avoid getting hit. The cover fielder though has it covered.
Angles in a length ball on off, Shafique covers the line and defends it towards silly mid on.
Pitches it up and around off, at 130 kph, Abdullah Shafique drives but finds the short cover fielder.
Keeps it full and around off, angling in at 129 kph, Shafique defends it towards short cover.
On a length around off, ar 129.2 kph, it's defended off the back foot to covers.
Southee keeps probing around off, fuller in length, Shafique is forward as he blocks it safely.
Delivers it on a fuller length outside off, Abdullah Shafique allows it through to the keeper.
Around the wicket. Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq prods forward and blocks it away.
Fuller again, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it again off his front foot.
Bowls it outside leg, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and taps it to the man at gully.
Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq covers his line and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Imam-ul-Haq hangs back and flicks it towards deep backward square leg for three runs.
Over the wicket. Fuller and on middle, Abdullah Shafique lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
A tad fuller in length and in the channel outside off, Imam-ul-Haq lets it go.
Slightly shorter, on middle and leg, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to the man at backward square leg.
On off this time, Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to the fielder at silly mid off.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to mid on.
On a length and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on leg, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it down to deep backward square leg. Ish Sodhi is a bit lazy in the deep and they scamper back for the second run.
Fuller and on middle, Abdullah Shafique tucks it to backward square leg.
Bowls it outside off, Abdullah Shafique drives it but finds the man at short cover.
Slightly shorter one, Abdullah Shafique eases it to the man at mid on.
Fuller and on leg, Abdullah Shafique eases it to the man at short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and wide outside off, Abdullah Shafique shuffles across and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique lunges and defends it back towards the bowler.
Turning in from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to short mid-wicket.
Another one on off, turning in, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter one, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it towards deep backward point for one.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Abdullah Shafique eases it to the man at mid on.
Fuller one, outside off, Abdullah Shafique defends it to short cover.
Bowls it outside off, Abdullah Shafique lunges well forward and blocks it to short cover again.
Around the wicket. Tosses it up, full and on off, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it solidly.
Another fuller one, on off. Imam-ul-Haq eases it to mid off.
This one lands outside off, Imam-ul-Haq leans forward and drives it towards mid off for one.
Goes over the wicket and bowls a fuller one on leg, Abdullah Shafique eases it to the man at square leg.

OUT! TAKEN! Abdullah Shafique departs and New Zealand have a breakthrough in the game. This is fuller and on off, Abdullah Shafique advances down the track and looks to heave across the line but the ball hits the inside part of his bat. It carries aerially towards mid on where Glenn Phillips (sub) takes an excellent tumbling catch to his left. New Zealand will hope that this will open the floodgates. Only one question for Abdullah - What was the need? He has some explaining to do for both of his dismissals in this Test match.
Howout: c sub Glenn Phillips b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Fuller and on middle and leg, Shan Masood looks to block it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards fine leg. The batters collect three.
Fuller and on off, knocked down to mid on for a run.
On middle, helped to mid-wicket.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Flighted around off, Imam jumps down the track and flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Again Imam shows the urgency to run down the track and drives a full ball back to the bowler.

Stifled appeal for an lbw! Not given. Spinning into the batter from outside off, Imam draws forward to defend but it beats the inside edge and strikes him on the pads. Impact looks to be outside off. Southee decides not to review!
Fuller and around leg, Shan flicks but finds short leg.
Flighted delivery, full and on middle, Masood drives down the ground but finds mid on.
A shade short and on off, Shan goes on the back foot and punches it to short cover.
Beauty to beat the bat! Lovely line from Michael Bracewell. He dishes it out on a fuller length around off, Masood lunges to defend the line but it spins away to beat the outside edge.
Drags his length short, around off, Masood rocks back to cut but chops it down to covers.
Quicker one, full and skidding in, Masood defends near his front leg. A good over from Bracewell.
Flighted delivery, landing full around off, Imam uses his feet and defends it back.
Too full and around off, Imam walks forward and flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Tossed up outside off, full and spinning in, Imam gets down the track and tries to defend but misses. It goes off his pads to covers.
Loopy and around off, once again Imam is down the track as he blocks it to the leg side.
This one is flatter through the air, full and turning in from around off, Imam lunges and defends.
Jumps down the track to a full ball around off and brings his bat and pad together in defense.
Loopy delivery, full and on off, Masood presses ahead and defends it.
Drifting down the leg side, Masood works it off his pads and sends it through backward square leg. Two runs are taken.
Shortish and outside off, going straight on, Masood goes back to cut but chops it down to point.
Aerial but safe! Turn and bounce from around off, Masood draws forward and tries to defend with hard hands. It goes aerially but doesn't carry to the cover fielder.
Full and on off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Floated delivery on middle, full in length, Masood tries to flick but it goes off the inner half to fine leg. They collect two runs.
Well played! Short in length around off, spinning in, Imam immediately drops on the back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for a couple.
Short again, around off, once more Imam rocks back and slaps it to the left side of the deep point fielder. Another couple.
Fuller and just outside off, Imam dances down the track and defends near his front pad.
A bit flat and short on off, Imam moves back and nurdles it in front of square on the leg side for a run.
Loopy delivery, landing outside off and turning in, Masood presses forward to defend but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but the finger stays down. Impact is outside off.
Very full and on middle, helped to mid-wicket. Called a no ball for overstepping. Reload!

Spinning in from around off, Masood goes back and punches it down the ground. It goes on to hit the stumps at the other end. Imam dives as a precautionary measure. The bowler was nowhere near the ball though.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq dances down the track and drives it hard through extra cover as the ball races away to the fence.
Another fuller one, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to short leg.
Bowls it on leg, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and drills it but finds the man at mid on.
Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it away.
Slightly shorter one, on middle, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
This one lands on off, Shan Masood defends it back to the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, slower through the air, Imam-ul-Haq nudges it to deep mid-wicket for one.
A googly just outside off, Shan defends off the outside half of the bat towards short covers.
Turning in from outside off, Shan Masood prods forward to defend it but gets a rap on his pads. A stifled appeal but the impact was outside the line.
Slightly shorter and on off, Shan Masood punches it through covers for a brace.
Fuller and on middle, Shan Masood defends it to short leg.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq lunges to defend it but gets an inside edge onto the pads as it bounces off the deck.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq comes down the pitch and flicks it to wide mid on for a quick single.
Slightly shorter with turn and bounce, Shan Masood looks to block it but gets the inside half of his bat as the ball rolls towards short leg. Dot.
Outside off, defended towards silly mid on.
Fuller and on off, Shan Masood defends it to silly mid on again.
Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it away.
Turning in from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Another fuller one, on middle, Imam-ul-Haq works it towards square leg for one.

OUT! LBW! New Zealand have another wicket and they are celebrating. Ish Sodhi hurls across a fuller delivery around off, getting it to turn into the batter, Shan is caught on the back foot when he should have been forward as he tries to work it across the line. He misses and there is a loud shout for an lbw. The finger has gone up. Shan Masood has a clueless look on his face. He walks up to his partner and then takes the DRS at the last moment. UltraEdge detects nothing and the Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the leg stump. Umpire's call and Pakistan lose their second wicket. They trail by 103 runs.
Howout: lbw b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: HUGE SHOUT FOR AN LBW! The finger stays down. Fuller and outside off, turning in, Nauman Ali looks to defend it leaning forward but misses and gets rapped on the pads. A loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The players have a chat and Tim Southee decides not to take the review. The impact initially looked to be outside off but the Ball Tracking shows that it's in line but the ball is spinning too much and would have missed the stumps.
A googly outside off, Nauman Ali looks to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge. Brilliant over from Ish!
Over the wicket. Tosses it up, full and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to point for one.
Fuller and on off, Nauman Ali eases it to the man at mid off.
Tosses it up, outside off, Nauman Ali blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Nauman Ali defends it to silly point.
Slower and on middle, Nauman Ali defends it with the inside half of his bat towards short leg.
Another fuller one and on off, Nauman Ali lunges and blocks it to silly point.
Fuller and around off, Imam walks forward to the pitch of the delivery and defends it back.
A bit short and on off, turning in, Imam goes deep inside the crease and pushes through the line. The silly point fielder does well to stop it.

RISKY SINGLE! Floated delivery, full and on off, Imam skips down the track and bunts it towards mid on. He calls for a single and completes it with a dive as the fielder misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Slow turn back into the batter, from a shortish length around off, Nauman defends off the back foot.

FOUR! With every Kiwi player surrounding the nightwatchman, Nauman Ali buys a boundary for himself. Shortish and around off, Ali hammers it across the line from the back foot. It's a bit aerial but hurries past Neil Wagner at silly mid on for a boundary.
Flighted and full, around off, Nauman Ali presses forward and defends it to silly point. STUMPS ON DAY 4!
Flighted delivery, full and on off, Imam presses forward and defends it back.
Loopy and full, drifting in around off and turning away a bit, Imam is forward again as he defends it to the off side.
Slower through the air, full and dipping in on middle, Imam defends it watchfully.
Advances down the track to take it on the full and knocks it towards long on for a run. Pakistan are underway for Day 5.
Fullish and on off, Ali lunges and defends it ahead of his front foot.
Yet another copybook front-foot defense to complete the first over of the day.

Shout for an lbw! Tim Southee is very excited but once the umpire shakes his head, he returns to his bowling mark, without even thinking about the review. Tim begins from 'round the wicket and hurls in an inswinger on a good length outside off. Imam-ul-Haq offers no shot and takes it on his pads. It has not moved back in enough. The Ball Tracking confirms the same.
Full and around off, Imam uses his bat this time as he draws forward and pushes it to short cover.
Lands it on a length, outside off, Imam shoulders arms.
Southee probes around off, with a full ball at 128 kph, Imam blocks it solidly off the front foot.

EDGY FOUR! There is no slip in place. Full and outside off, Imam goes for the drive but edges it through the vacant slip cordon for a boundary. FIFTY FOR IMAM, his sixth in Tests. Pakistan will hope that he bats for the major part of Day 5 and help them in their task to save this Test match.
Pitches it up and outside off, with a wide slip in place. Imam allows it through to the keeper.
Flighted delivery, outside off and turning away a hint, Nauman allows it through to the keeper.
Fuller and on middle, defended towards short leg.

OUT! Given lbw! If there is no bat involved, it's gone. Nauman Ali has a word with his partner and then returns to the pavilion. Beautiful delivery from Michael Bracewell. He serves it full around middle and gets it to straighten a shade after landing. Nauman Ali leans forward to defend but it beats his bat and pings him on the front pad. The finger goes up and New Zealand have struck early by removing the nightwatchman.​ Pakistan trail by 92 runs.
Howout: lbw b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Flighted one, full and around off, Babar is on the front foot in defense.
Presses forward to a full ball, allows the ball to spin back in and defends it softly.

Bracewell pulls his length back a shade, lands it around off, Babar gets back to defend but it takes the outer edge and rolls wide of first slip. The fielder attempts to stop it with a dive but fails to do so cleanly. They cross for a run and Babar is off the mark.
Fuller in length and outside off, a hint of shape there, Babar gets on the front foot and defends.
Southee keeps it full and close to off, shaping away a bit again, Babar is forward in defense.
In the channel outside off, on a length, Babar has a watchful leave.
Another delivery outside off, Babar is content in leaving it alone at the moment.
This is the one that comes back into the batter. Full and around off, nipping in a shade, Babar flicks it through square leg for a run.
A gentle delivery in the zone outside off, Imam shoulders arms.
Tossed up, on off, turning in, Babar Azam defends it to short leg.
Another one on middle with a hint of turn, Babar Azam defends it solidly.
Fuller and on middle, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on off, Babar Azam taps it but finds the man at short covers.
Turning in from outside off, Babar Azam lunges and blocks it away.
Flighted ball, on middle, Babar defends it to silly mid on.
Around the wicket. Slightly shorter and shaping in, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Fuller one this time, outside off, Imam-ul-Haq leaves the harmless delivery.
That was similar to the last delivery as Imam-ul-Haq lets this one go towards the keeper again.
Another one outside off, Imam-ul-Haq shoulders arms at it.
Fuller one, on off this time, shaping in. Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off again, Imam-ul-Haq lets it go towards the keeper.
Tossed up, on leg, Babar Azam pulls it towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Fine shot. Slightly shorter and on leg, slower too. Babar Azam gets on his knee and helps it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it solidly.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and slower too, Babar Azam hangs back and pulls it through backward square leg for a boundary!
Bowls it on off, Babar Azam works it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Babar Azam defends it to the man at short leg.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it solidly back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fine placement. Fuller and on middle and leg, Imam-ul-Haq reads it well and flicks it in the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary. 100 up!
On a length and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Bowls it fuller and on the stumps, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it solidly.
This one lands on off, Imam-ul-Haq block it to the man at silly mid on.
Fuller one, outside off, shaping in. Imam-ul-Haq prods forward and blocks it to silly mid off.

OUT! LBW! Babar Azam looks very adjacent to the stumps here. He has a nervous look on his face, has a word with his partner and then takes the DRS. Ish Sodhi begins with a short delivery, landing around off and turning back into the batter along with staying a bit low. Babar Azam goes deep inside the crease to pull it across the line. But he misses and is struck on the pads. They appeal and the finger goes up. This one looks plumb and the Ball Tracking tells the same. First there was no bat on the UltraEdge and the ball is hitting the leg stump. Sodhi has hit the jackpot with his first delivery of the day and it's a body blow to Pakistan. They trail by 74 runs.
Howout: lbw b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Bowls it outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed lunges and blocks it away.
This was similar to the last delivery, Sarfaraz Ahmed defended it solidly.

Bowls it on middle and leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed clips it to deep mid-wicket. Ajaz Patel fumbles a bit but just manages to stop it before the fence. The third umpire has a look and feels that it's cleanly done. Three runs added to the total.
Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it out.
Tosses it up outside off, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to the man at silly mid on. Pakistan still trail by 71 runs.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes it to the man at covers.
Fuller one this time, on middle and leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed clips it to short mid-wicket and calls for one. Imam-ul-Haq at the bowler's end says a big NO and sends him back.
Fuller ball outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed drives it to short cover.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and outside off, shaping away, Sarfaraz Ahmed leans forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
FOUR! This one lands down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed reads it well and just tickles it through to fine leg for another boundary.
On a length and on middle, Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it back towards the bowler.
Turning in sharply from outside off, it stays a little low, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to short leg.
Bowls it outside off with some turn, Imam-ul-Haq looks to block it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it solidly.
Tossed up, slower through the air, Imam-ul-Haq clips it but finds the man at short mid-wicket.
Tosses it up here, outside off, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward to block it but gets a rap on his pads as the ball rolls back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq goes back and defends it away.
FOUR! Sarfaraz Ahmed is trying to be positive. Full delivery, around middle and leg, Ahmed goes down and sweeps it effectively past short leg for a boundary.
FOUR! And again, action replay of the previous boundary. Ajaz is full on middle, Sarfaraz Ahmed kneels down and nails his sweep shot through square leg.
Flatter and on middle, defended off the back foot to short leg.
As soon as the length goes full and the line is around middle and leg, Ahmed sweeps. He sends it down to fine leg and fetches a couple of runs.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over. A touch short and around leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed steps back to make some room and smacks it through cover-point for a boundary. The deficit has dropped below 50 now.

Full and flighted, down the leg side, Ahmed tries to play the reverse sweep but fails to connect cleanly. He perhaps gets some under-edge or top half of his bat as it scoots behind the keeper. They cross for a run. 15 from the over and Sarfaraz Ahmed at the moment is batting with a strike rate of 173.3.
Short in length and outside off, Ahmed pushes it in the gap at covers and picks up a single.
