ALMOST DRAGS IT ON! Floated delivery, full and landing on the rough outside off, Imam walks down the track to drive but is deceived in flight and turn. It takes the inside edge, beats the stumps and races down to fine leg. They get two runs. If not for that edge, it would have crashed into the stumps.
Full and around off, Imam comes down the track and knocks it down to long on for a run.
A bit short in length, around off, Ahmed moves back and cuts but finds the backward point fielder.
Googly around off, on the shorter side, Sarfaraz picks it and defends from the back foot.
Quicker one, a flipper perhaps, around middle and leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed gets forward but then offers no shot. It goes behind off his pads.
Loopy and full, around off, Imam jumps down the track and defends it down.
Fuller and on off, spinning in, Imam defends off the front foot to short mid-wicket.
Turning in from around off, Imam moves back to flick but gets a leading edge. It goes softly to covers.
Flatter and a bit short on off, Imam hangs back and defends it with the spin to short mid-wicket.
Short in length and outside off, Imam again is on the back foot as he steers it down to deep backward point for a run.
Down the leg side, spinning towards the stumps, Ahmed stands back and tries to work on the leg side but misses. It goes off his pads to short leg.

Fuller one, turning in from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq prods forward to block it but gets rapped on his pads and the ball lobs towards first slip. Ish Sodhi appeals thinking there was an inside edge. The umpire is unmoved as it was off the batter's pads.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it solidly back towards the bowler.

DRS time as the appeal for a bat-pad is not entertained. Flighted leg spinner, landing full around off and turning back in, Imam lunges to defend but fails to do so. It pops out to short leg and they appeal. Nothing from the umpire. UltraEdge shows there was a massive gap between the bat and the ball. The third umpire follows the protocol and checks for the lbw as well. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's missing the stumps. New Zealand waste one review.
Tossed up, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and defends it to mid off.
Ish Sodhi is really troubling the Pakistan batters here. Fuller and outside off, turning in. Imam-ul-Haq looks to block it but gets a rap on his pads. Sodhi appeals but nothing from the umpire.

Shout for an lbw! Once again turning in from outside off, Imam-ul-Haq gets struck on the pads, but he does well to get himself outside the line of the off stump. The bowler once again clears his lungs with a vociferous appeal but nothing from the umpire. A threatening over from Ish Sodhi comes to an end!
Bowls it fuller and outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed pads it away.
Another one outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed reverse-sweeps it to short point. Imam-ul-Haq wants a run but Sarfaraz Ahmed sends him back.
Outside off, left alone by Sarfaraz Ahmed.
Bowls it down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it with his pads.
Another one outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed pads it away again.
Fuller and outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed reverse-sweeps it through backward point. Michael Bracewell in the deep does well to stop it The batters collect two runs off it.
Fuller and outside leg, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and blocks it away.
Bowls it down leg this time, Imam-ul-Haq flicks it straight to the man at backward square leg.
Flights it up around off, Imam comes forward and steers it towards covers for one.
Short and wide, turning away from the right-hander. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to cut it but misses.
Bowls it on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it to the man at covers.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed guides it to backward point for a single. He keeps strike for the next over.
Slower and outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed lunges and blocks it away.
Another slower one, outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed pads it away.
Bowls it outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed doesn't offer a shot and takes it on his thigh pad.
Once again outside the leg stump, Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it away off his pads.
Outside leg again, Sarfaraz Ahmed pads it away.
Keeps bowling it outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed is in no mood to offer his bat.
Fuller one and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to short leg.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and defends it to silly mid on.
Flighted up, outside off, Imam-ul-Haq drives it to the short cover fielder.
Tosses it up outside off, turning in, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it towards backward point for a single.
FOUR! Short of a length here, down leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed gets on his knee and paddles it through fine leg for a boundary.
Bowls it outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it with his pads.

SIX! Lovely footwork and this one has gone all the way. Floated and full around off, Imam-ul-Haq runs down the track and powers it over long on for a biggie. The positivity of Sarfaraz Ahmed has rubbed on Imam. The trail is now 28.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
A touch short and on off, Imam goes back in defense.
Full and outside off, Imam lunges and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and on middle, Imam covers the spin and defends it down on the surface.
A touch short and outside off, Imam goes back inside the crease and defends it down watchfully.
Flighted leg spinner, landing outside the leg stump, Sarfaraz is happy to pad it away.

Fuller and outside leg, again Ahmed offers no shot and it goes off his pads to third man. No shot is offered and that's why they didn't cross. What happened there? Some words were exchanged. So, Sarfaraz Ahmed was outside the crease, doing some gardening and after collecting the throw, Tom Blundell tries to run him out. Ahmed thought since he had not offered the shot, the ball was dead. It was not as the umpire had not signalled for it. He could have been run out there! Correction - Umpire Dar had called it a dead ball, the replays confirm. Now we know why Sarfaraz Ahmed was agitated at that attempt by the Kiwi keeper.
Outside leg, padded away by Ahmed.
Stays on the back foot and punches it to deep cover for two runs.
Outside leg, padded away.
Fuller and outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed continues to offer his pads.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Flatter and on off, blocked off the back foot.
Loopy and full, around off, Imam lunges and defends.
Sharp spin back into the batter from a shortish length outside off, Imam defends off the back foot.
Uses his feet and flicks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Tossed up outside leg, Ahmed pads it away.
Leans forward and across to defend but misses. It goes off his pads to first slip.
Flighted and full, around off, Imam walks forward and defends it to the on side.
Oohhh... close! Sharp turn and bounce from around off, Imam goes back to cut but is hurried up and chops it down towards point.
Googly, landing too far outside off, Imam tries to cut but misses.
Fuller and on off, Imam gets to the pitch of the ball and forces it to mid on for a run. The 50-run stand comes up, off 88 balls. The deficit is 24 now.
Gets forward to a full ball and pushes it to covers.
Full and around off, Imam jumps down the track and eases it to mid on for a single.
Loopy and full, landing outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed doesn't offer a shot.
Phew, that was very close to the leg stump! Floated and full, landing outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to play the reverse sweep but misses. The keeper collects it close to the leg pole.
Outside leg, padded away.
Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to give himself room and the bowler follows him down the leg side. Sarfaraz Ahmed is happy to pad it away.
Slightly short and outside leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed successfully gives himself room this time and punches it down to long off. Three runs taken.
Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed paddles it to fine leg for a brace. The ball did carry but it was way out of reach of the fielder at short leg. The batters collect two.
Googly, outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Around the wicket. Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Short and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq slaps it towards deep cover for a brace.
Fuller and on off, this is defended off the front foot.
Slightly shorter and on off, Imam-ul-Haq goes back to pull but drags it towards wide mid on. Pakistan trail by just 15 runs now.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it outside off, shaping away, Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it to mid off.
Fuller again, around off, Sarfaraz Ahmed opens the bat-face and defends it towards point. No ball called for overstepping.
Good-length delivery, shaping away a touch, some extra bounce. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to drive it but misses.
On a length and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed guides it to deep point for one. He calls for the second run but Imam-ul-Haq denies it.
On a length and on off, Imam-ul-Haq tucks it to the man at short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed hangs back and gently pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for one.

Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to heave it but the ball hits the inside half of his bat. It carries towards the man at short mid-wicket who makes a diving attempt to his left but it evades him by a few inches. Close! They cross.
Fuller and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed lunges and blocks it away.
Bowls it on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed sweeps it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and works it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.

Appeal for an lbw! The finger has stayed down. New Zealand take the DRS. Coming to the delivery, Sodhi hurls across a full ball outside off and gets it to curl back into the batter. Imam steps forward to flick but misses and is rapped on the back pad. They put in an unsuccessful appeal. DRS time. No bat is involved and the Ball Tracking confirms that it's missing the stumps by a long, long way. New Zealand are now left with only one review. Need to be careful here.
Around the wicket with the keeper up to the stumps. Good-length delivery outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it to covers.

SARFARAZ IS SAFE! Short in length and outside off, Ahmed steers it to backward point where the fielder dives and takes the pace off it. Sarfaraz Ahmed steps out in search of a run but is sent back. Meanwhile, the cover-point fielder attacks the ball and throws it to the keeper who breaks the stumps. The third umpire is referred and the replays find that Ahmed is safe with a full-length dive. Direct hit would have been interesting though.

CLOSE! On a length and on leg, Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it to mid on and scampers through for a quick single. The fielder is quick to collect it and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. A direct hit would have been close. Two nervy moments for Sarfaraz Ahmed.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq blocks it to square leg.
Fuller one, angling in, Imam-ul-Haq drills it straight towards the right of mid on for a single.
Bowls it fuller again, on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed nudges it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Slightly shorter and on leg, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to the man at square leg.
Tosses it on off, Imam-ul-Haq moves forward and pushes it to mid on, and runs quickly. A direct hit at the bowler's end but Imam-ul-Haq is well home.
Bowls it on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it to mid on.
This one lands outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed cuts it to backward point. Calls for a run and then stops to admire the diving fielder. Once it goes past him, he crosses for a run.
Another one outside off, Imam-ul-Haq hangs back and cuts it to deep backward point for one.
Quicker one on middle and leg, it turns in as well. Sarfaraz Ahmed goes on his backfoot to block it but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Full and angling in around off, Imam works it across the line but finds short mid-wicket.
Four byes! Sprays a length ball way down the leg side, Imam lets it be and it goes wide of the keeper. Races behind for a boundary at fine leg. Pakistan are in the lead now!
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Gets forward and pushes a full ball to covers.
On a length and outside off, shaping away, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to defend it but gets an inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg. They collect one.
Too short in length around middle, Imam moves back and turns it through square leg for three runs.
Flighted and full, outside off, drawing the batter forward, Ahmed defends it to the off side.
Loopy and full, outside off, again Ahmed is drawn forward and he defends near his front pad.
Fuller and wider outside off, Ahmed drives but finds the fielder at point.
Loopy delivery outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it with soft hands to point and looks for a run. Sent back.
Spinning in from a fuller length outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed gets forward and across before flicking. He finds short mid-wicket. LUNCH ON DAY 5!
Southee runs in from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball around off, Imam stays on the back foot and defends.
Identical to the last delivery, again Imam sticks on the back foot as he blocks it to the off side.
Serves it full and wide outside off, there to be driven, Imam is very watchful as he makes a leave.
Fuller and on off, angling in, defended to short cover.
Another solid defense from Imam. Southee is sticking to a good line but there is not much support from the surface.
Lands it full and on off, Imam defends it to the right side of the short cover fielder. Maiden to begin proceedings after Lunch.
A touch short in length, around off, Ahmed gets back and punches it to cover-point. Wants a run but Imam sends him back.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR SARFARAZ! He is having a great comeback to this format and making his 50th Test special. Shortish and on off, Sarfaraz Ahmed hangs back and punches it strongly down to long on for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Fifty and out for Sarfaraz Ahmed and he walks off bitterly disappointed. Ish Sodhi serves a short delivery outside off and gets it to spin away from the batter at 81.5 kph, Sarfaraz Ahmed goes chasing after it but it takes the toe end of his bat and settles into the gloves of Tom Blundell. Good reaction by the keeper, he though was not appealing at all. The others appeal and the finger goes up. Pakistan have now lost half their side and are ahead by only 11 runs.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: A friendly full toss around middle, Salman pushes it gently to mid on.
Quicker around off, skidding in, Agha defends off the back foot.
A low full toss outside off, Salman drives but finds the fielder at short cover. End of a successful over for Sodhi who now has three wickets to his name in this innings.
In the channel outside off, on a good length, Imam allows it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Sliced away! Things happening here for the Kiwis. Full and wide outside off, Imam throws his hands at it and slices his attempted drive. It goes just wide of gully and races away to the fence.
Full and on off, angling in, Imam pushes off the front foot to short cover.
Full and quite wide outside off, further shaping away, Imam has nothing to do with it.
Imam is not shying away from driving. Fuller and around off, it's stroked through covers for a single.
Nice from Southee and equally good from Salman. Fullish and around off, curving in off the seam, Agha is on the front foot as he brings his bat ahead of the front pad in defense.
Tosses it up, slower through the air, Imam-ul-Haq eases it to short cover.
Another slower one, on middle, Imam-ul-Haq defends it to the left of the bowler.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq cuts it towards point for a single.
FOUR! A low full toss and on off, Agha Salman drills it past the diving fielder at mid on for a boundary.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Agha Salman blocks it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it up, outside off, Agha Salman lunges forward and defends it.
On a length and outside off, shaping away, Imam-ul-Haq leaves the harmless delivery.
Another one outside off, Imam-ul-Haq happily lets it go.
On a length, angling in, Imam-ul-Haq offers a dead bat to it.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and outside off, shaping away, Imam-ul-Haq opens the face of the bat and guides it past backward point for a boundary.
This one lands outside off as well, Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
On a length and on off, Imam-ul-Haq looks to defend it but picks up the outside edge. It goes to the fielder at gully on the bounce.
Fuller and on off, Agha Salman defends it solidly.
Another fuller one, this is pushed towards the man at mid on.
Outside off this time, Agha Salman pushes it to the man at covers.
Bowls it down leg, Agha Salman sweeps it towards fine leg for a brace. 200 up for Pakistan. They lead by 27 runs now.
Fuller and on off, this is defended solidly off the front foot.
Another one on off, Agha Salman drives but finds the man at covers.
Bowls it on off, turning away, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Imam-ul-Haq lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Turning it outside off, some extra bounce, Imam-ul-Haq looks to block it but misses.
Tosses it up, Imam-ul-Haq drives it but finds the man at short cover.
FOUR! Fine placement. Slightly shorter and outside off, Imam-ul-Haq opens the face of the bat and guides it through to third man as the ball races away to the fence.
Fuller and on off, Imam-ul-Haq defends it back towards the bowler.

OUT! TIMBER! Ish Sodhi is doing things here for New Zealand. The great Shane Warne would have termed this delivery as a natural variation - i.e. the leg spinner that doesn't turn. Sodhi has his fourth. He gives this one a good flight and lands it full around off. Salman gets on the front foot, trying to play with the expected spin but this one doesn't turn and goes straight on through the tiny gap between his bat and pad. The stumps are shattered and Pakistan are in a spot of bother. They are effectively 31 for 6.
Howout: b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Turning in from outside off, Saud Shakeel reads it well and eases it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slower one, outside off, Saud Shakeel defends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Fuller and on middle, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it away.
This one lands down leg, Saud Shakeel shuffles across and defends it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and close to off, Imam jumps down the track and jams it out on the leg side.
Advances down the track and drives a full ball. Finds mid off.
Fuller and on off, skidding in, Imam defends it close to his front pad.
Moves to 96. Fuller again, around off, Imam caresses it through covers for a single.
Too full and landing on off, Shakeel defends it back.
Yet another watchful defensive shot from Saud to end the over.
Flatter and a touch short on off, Imam goes back and defends it to the leg side.
Very full and around leg, it's clipped to short mid-wicket.
Turning in from outside off, on the shorter side, Imam goes on the back foot and defends.
Lets the ball to come to him and then defends it from the back foot to short leg.

OUT! STUMPED! The century was playing in Imam's mind and that got the better of him. The third wicket goes down for Pakistan after Lunch and they are staring down the barrel. Ish Sodhi has a fifer and he has made his comeback to this format memorable. Hurls across a well-disguised googly, lands it on the rough outside off, Imam-ul-Haq skips down the track, looking to flick it away but the ball spins away from his bat with some extra bounce. It's a great take from Tom Blundell to his left as he stretches his arms sideways and then breaks the stumps to find Imam short of the crease. Pakistan's inning has nosedived after Lunch and they are now effectively 32 for 7. Imam is frustrated on his way to the dressing room and is seen hitting a chair with his bat.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Flatter googly on middle, it's punched down to mid on. A wicket maiden from Ish!
Full and floated on around off, Saud defends it to the leg side.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller on off, defended.
Around off, full in length, Shakeel blocks.
Flighted and on off, Saud is in defensive mode, blocks again.
Lands it full and on off, Shakeel defends it off the front foot.
Flipper around off, Wasim goes back to cut but misses.
Flatter on off, defended from the back foot.
Short and outside off, punched down to the cover fielder.
Very full and on off, Wasim digs it out.
Googly, landing outside off, Wasim lets it be.
Quicker googly around off at 91.2 kph, hurrying into the batter, Wasim somehow works it past mid on and takes a couple of runs.
Shakeel is off the mark! Short and on off, he goes on the back foot and pushes it towards cover-point for a single.
Turning in from around off, Wasim prods forward and defends.
Lunges to a full ball and defends it with an angled bat to the off side.
Pitches it up and outside off, getting it to turn in, Wasim presses forward and jams it down on the surface.
Edgy! Loopy and around off, spinning in, Wasim gets forward to defend but it takes the outside edge and runs past first slip. They run three.
Edgy again! Floated and full, landing on off and turning away, Shakee tries to defend but edges it wide of first slip. Two this time. The lead moves to 40.
Wasim is turning out to be the master of edges. Tries to drive a full ball but edges it down to third man. Gets three more.
Turning in from outside off, Saud Shakeel stays back and defends it to square leg.
Slower and outside off, Saud Shakeel steers it down to the gully region for a single.
Slightly shorter and on off, Mohammad Wasim punches it to the left of mid off. The fielder there makes a sliding stop.
Another one outside off, Mohammad Wasim punches it to the mid off fielder again.
This one lands outside leg, Mohammad Wasim stays back and looks to play at it but gets a rap on his thigh pad. Ends with a dot.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel blocks it watchfully.
Another fuller one on middle, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
This was similar to the last delivery, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it away.
Tosses it up, slower through the air, Saud Shakeel eases it to mid off.
Fuller one and on off, Saud Shakeel blocks it to short leg.
Fuller one, around off, Saud Shakeel keeps it out.
Slower one, angling in, Mohammad Wasim eases it to short cover.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Mohammad Wasim defends it to silly point.
Bowls it outside leg, Mohammad Wasim looks to block it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls towards backward point. They cross.
Fuller and outside off, Saud Shakeel eases it to covers for one.
Bowls it fuller and on off, Mohammad Wasim lunges and blocks it solidly.
Bowls it outside leg, turning towards the stumps, Mohammad Wasim pads it away.
FOUR! This one lands on leg and turns down further, Saud Shakeel uses the pace of the ball and tickles it through to fine leg for a boundary. Lead is now 50 runs.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it away.
Fuller and on the stumps, Saud Shakeel defends to the man at silly point.
Fuller again, Saud Shakeel blocks it out solidly.
Bowls it on off, this is defended towards the man at silly point.
FOUR! Slightly shorter and outside off, Saud Shakeel hangs back and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
Bowls it on middle and leg, Mohammad Wasim looks to block it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller and on off, Mohammad Wasim defends it off the back foot.
This one lands down leg, Wasim goes back and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on the stumps, Mohammad Wasim defends off the front foot.
Slightly shorter and on middle, Mohammad Wasim rocks back and flicks it towards mid-wicket. Dot.
Fuller and on the stumps, Mohammad Wasim defends it away back to the cover region.
Full and flighted around off, turning in with some extra bounce, Shakeel defends it off the inner half and it pops out off the front pad. Drops in the middle of the pitch.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it.
Spinning in from around off, Shakeel lunges and defends from the inner half to short leg.
Loopy around middle, turning down, Shakeel goes back and taps it down to square leg.

Appeal for a run out! It's referred upstairs. No excitement shown by the Kiwis. Short and outside off, Shakeel guides it down to third man for three runs. The throw comes to the keeper and Blundell breaks the stumps. It's referred upstairs but Wasim is found to be safe.
Loopy and full outside off, Wasim presses forward and blocks it down.
Too full in length, drifting around off, Shakeel jams it out.

Shout for an lbw! Nothing from the umpire. Tim Southee has a word with his keeper and then decides not to review. Flatter and fuller, around off and turning in, Saud Shakeel lunges to defend but it hits the pad first and then the bat. Impact is outside off.
Short and on off, Shakeel punches it to covers where Williamson makes a diving stop. He immediately releases the ball towards the keeper and nearly creates a run-out chance.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.

CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP? New Zealand are appealing but the finger stays down. Tim Southee opts for the review. Sodhi gets some extra bite from the surface with the second new ball. It turns back in from around off, fuller in length, Saud Shakeel leans forward to defend with his bat hiding behind the front pad. It pops out to Daryl Mitchell at first slip and they appeal for a catch. DRS time. The UltraEdge finds that it has come off the pads and missed the edge of the bat by a whisker. A great decision by Alex Wharf and now New Zealand have no reviews left.
Flighted and around off, defended off the front foot.
Lands it on a length around off, Wasim defends it.
FOUR! Eased away! On a length and outside off, Wasim deals with the bounce well and guides it down to third man for a boundary. The lead is now 61 runs.
Back of a length, around leg, Wasim nudges it to fine leg for a single.
Slightly short in length and outside off, Shakeel pushes inside the line and plays it off the outer half to gully.
Fuller and on off, Shakeel defends it next to his front pad.
Darts a length ball on off, Shakeel blocks it from the back foot.
Flatter arm ball on off, Wasim punches at the last moment to covers.
FOUR! Nicely punched! A bit short and around off, Wasim goes on the back foot and forces it through covers for a boundary. Ajaz has struggled with his length today.
Spin and bounce, from outside off, Wasim tries to defend but misses.
Beaten! Close to off, on a shortish length and turning away a hint at the last moment, Wasim feels for it and then pulls his bat back at the last moment.
Short and on off, punched to covers.
Floated delivery, short and outside off, Wasim allows it through to the keeper.

FOUR! Poor length and punished! Short and outside off, Shakeel goes on the back foot and whacks it past the point fielder for a boundary. Runs are just as important as time here for Pakistan. Lead is 70.
Short again, around off, Saud forces it off his back foot to deep point. Conway stops it just before the fence and saves one run.
Flighted and full, around off, Wasim presses forward to defend and edges it down towards third man for a run.
Loopy delivery, full and close to off, Shakeel pushes it with an angled bat to backward point.
Flighted and outside off, Saud covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Very full and on middle, defended on the leg side.
Quicker and on off, Mohammad Wasim lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
Slightly shorter and on off, Mohammad Wasim punches it to point. Devon Conway hurts his fingers in an attempt to stop it by diving to his left.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it away.
This one lands on off, Saud Shakeel eases it to the man at mid off.
Bowls it on leg, Saud Shakeel blocks it to short leg.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel defends off the back foot to silly point. That will be TEA on Day 5.
Slightly shorter and on off, Mohammad Wasim punches it to the man at covers.
FOUR! Nicely played. Slightly shorter and outside off, Mohammad Wasim rocks back and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Wasim defends off the front foot back at the bowler.
A  googly spinning into the leg stump line, Mohammad Wasim gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the pads. A stifled appeal turned down.
Flights it up on off, Mohammad Wasim steers it towards covers for a single.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel hangs back and blocks it solidly.
FOUR! Fuller and on middle, it skids through, Mohammad Wasim looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge as it goes past the slip fielder for a boundary. The 50-run stand comes up!
Fuller and on off, Mohammad Wasim defends it solidly.
Another fuller one, Mohammad Wasim defends it.
Bowls it on off, Mohammad Wasim lunges and blocks it to silly point.
Another fuller one, on middle, Mohammad Wasim blocks it back towards the bowler.
This one lands on middle, Mohammad Wasim comes well forward and defends it back at the bowler.
Short and wide, Saud Shakeel hangs back and cuts it towards deep point for a brace.
Fuller and just outside off, Saud Shakeel plays it with soft hands towards short third man for one.
Bowls it just outside off, Mohammad Wasim hangs back and looks to play a cut shot but gets beaten on the inside edge.
FOUR! Well connected this time. Fuller and on off, Mohammad Wasim leans forward and drives it through covers as the ball races away the fence in no time.
Slightly shorter one, Mohammad Wasim flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and outside off, Saud Shakeel looks to defend it but misses and gets a rap on his pads. It lobs towards slips and Ish Sodhi appeals for a catch, but not out says the umpire.
On off, blocked out solidly.
SIX! All the way. Fuller and outside off, Mohammad Wasim gets on his knee and slogs it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
Fuller and on off, Mohammad Wasim looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards third man. The batters collect three. The lead crosses 100!
Bowls it on off, Saud Shakeel defends off the back foot towards short extra covers.
Another fuller ball as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off, Saud Shakeel guides it towards covers for one.
Flatter and shorter, close to off, Shakeel cuts towards point for a single.

OUT! LBW! This one looks plumb. Mohammad Wasim looks at his partner and then takes the DRS. Googly from Sodhi has troubled Wasim the most during his stay and it has eventually hunted him down. Landing around off, on the shorter side and turning into the batter. Wasim goes deep inside the crease to cut but it first hits him on the flap of the back pad. They appeal and the umpire agrees. DRS time. Ball Tracking finds that the impact is with the umpire's call and it's hitting the stumps. The 71-run stand has been broken and Pakistan lead by 103 runs.
Howout: lbw b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Beaten! Tossed up outside off, Hamza tries to defend with the spin but it goes straight on and beats the outside edge.
Fuller and on off, defended off the inner half to the leg side.
Loopy and full, around off and spinning in to beat Hamza's forward defensive prod. They appeal for an lbw but it's spinning too much.
Shortish and outside off, Mir keeps it out in front of silly point.
Full and floated, around off, Saud defends it off the front foot.
Skidding in from around off, Shakeel tries to defend but gets an inside edge. It runs down to long leg and Saud denies the single.
Flighted delivery, full and landing outside off on the rough, Shakeel pushes it to point.
Quicker and shorter on off, Shakeel punches it to sweeper cover for a run. Two balls to survive for Mir.
Fuller and on off, defended easily to short cover.
Loopy delivery, pitching full around off, Hamza defends it again.
Flighted and full on off, Shakeel defends.
A dipping full ball around off, Shakeel lunges to meet the delivery and blocks it down.
A near-yorker on middle, Shakeel does well to dig it out on the off side.
Sharp spin from around off, short in length, Shakeel goes on the back foot and defends it back.
Short again, on off, Saud cuts but finds the fielder at point.
Maiden! Too full and on middle, Shakeel flicks but it goes straight to the fielder at mid-wicket. New Zealand will now have an entire over to bowl to Mir Hamza.
Loopy and full, around off, Hamza defends.
Too full and landing on middle, again Mir defends it with ease.
Fuller and around off, Mir strides forward and defends it on the leg side.
Yorker on off, Hamza digs it out off the bottom edge to first slip.
Flighted one, full and on off, Hamza gets forward and defends it with hard hands.
Safely negotiated. Tossed up around off, Mir Hamza shows good technique to defend it off his front foot.
Flighted delivery, very full and on off, Shakeel drives it to sweeper cover for a couple of runs.
Patel pulls his length back and serves it on off, Saud moves back and defends it down.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Shakeel presses forward in defense.
Slightly short and on off, Shakeel goes back and punches it to mid on.

Run out chance! Patel bowls short again, outside off, Shakeel punches it to cover-point where the fielder makes a diving stop and parries it to the cover fielder. Mir Hamza sets off for a run but is sent back. He reaches with a dive as Patel fails to grab the throw. Had he collected, Mir would have been a goner. Is this the moment New Zealand will regret?
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Turning in from outside off, Hamza prods forward and blocks it to silly point.
Short and off, punched to covers.
Fuller and on off, Mir Hamza eases it to short leg.
Tosses it up on middle, Mir Hamza blocks it back towards the bowler.
Short and on off, Mir Hamza defends it to silly point.
Flighted ball on middle and leg, Mir Hamza defends it to short leg. Lead - 106.
Shorter and outside off, Saud Shakeel shuffles across to defend it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel eases it to silly point.
This one lands fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel lunges and blocks it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played. Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel gets on his knee and slog-sweeps it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! This one outside off, Saud Shakeel shuffles across and paddles it to fine leg for another boundary. The lead is increasing and the overs are decreasing. New Zealand are seeing the win slip away.
Bowls it on middle, Saud Shakeel eases it to silly point.
Fuller and outside off, Mir Hamza defends it to short cover.
Fuller again, on off. Mir Hamza looks to defend it but gets an outside edge as the ball rolls past the slip fielder towards third man. They cross.
Bowls it outside off, Saud Shakeel defends it off the back foot.
A low full toss, Saud Shakeel guides it to deep cover for one.
Beauty! This one lands on off and nips in sharply, Mir Hamza looks to defend it but misses. The ball just misses the outside edge and goes towards the keeper.
Fuller and on off, this is defended forward.
Tosses it up, Shakeel lunges and defends again.
Bowls it wide outside off, Saud Shakeel blocks it going to his left.
Fuller ball on middle and leg, Saud Shakeel defends it solidly.
Another fuller ball defended back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fine shot. Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel gets on his knee and slogs it over mid-wicket for a boundary.

SIX! FIFTY FOR SHAKEEL! A vital knock from him. Floated and full, around off, Shakeel jumps down the track and heaves it with the spin over the cow corner for a biggie - his first in Test cricket. 300 up, the lead is 126 runs!
This one lands outside off, Mir Hamza looks to play at it but misses.
Bowls it fuller and on middle and leg, Mir Hamza blocks it to short leg.
Tosses it up outside off, Mir Hamza punches it to the man at covers.
Bowls it on off, fuller in length, Mir Hamza digs it towards the man at silly point.
Fuller and on off, Mir Hamza defends it forward.
Flighted up, on middle, Mir Hamza eases it back towards the bowler.
Tosses it up on off, Shakeel lunges forward to defend it.
Another fuller ball as this is defended back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Saud Shakeel eases it to short cover.
Short and outside off, Saud cuts but finds backward point.
Skidding away from around off, Saud moves back to defend but it beats the outside edge.

Put down? Flighted delivery, full and around leg, Saud Shakeel goes down the sweep but gets a top edge. It flies towards square leg, Michael Bracewell runs back and dives but it just evades his fingers. They cross for a run.
Full on off, spinning in, Saud presses forward and defends it back.
Short and on off, staying low, Shakeel goes back and hits it back to the bowler.
Spinning in from around off, Saud goes on the back foot and defends it down on the surface.
A low full toss around leg, Saud clips it off his pads but straight to the fielder at mid-wicket.
FOUR! The lead moves to 131. Sodhi drops it short and wide outside off, Saud Shakeel goes on the back foot and slaps it through backward point for a boundary.
Short again, on off and spinning in, Saud goes back and plays it towards point.
Brave leave! Loopy and outside off, turning back in sharply, Hamza offers no shot. That was not too far away from the off pole.
Four byes! Once again there is big spin out from the rough, Mir draws forward to defend but it beats the inside edge and scoots past the keeper for a boundary.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it off the inner half to short leg.
Pitches it up around off, Mir presses forward and defends it well this time.
Very full and on off, Hamza jams it out.
Delivers it very full and on off, Hamza tries to defend but it takes the outside edge and runs down to third man. They get two runs.
A leg spinner landing on a short length around off, Saud goes on the back foot and defends.
Fuller this time, around off and turning in, Shakeel shuffles across and defends it with an open stance.
Too full this time, around middle, an easy defense for Shakeel.
Full and floated around off, Shakeel lunges and wrists it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off, Shakeel drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller and quicker on leg, Bracewell works it off his pads to short leg.
New Zealand are away! Loopy and full, around leg, Michael Bracewell walks forward and drives it to mid off for a single.
Flatter through the air, full and on middle, Conway clips it in front of square on the leg side for a single.
Flighted delivery, landing full around leg, Bracewell makes room as he advances down the track and lofts it over mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Full and pitching outside leg, Bracewell tries to flick but misses. They appeal but to no avail.

OUT! TIMBER! Smart bowling from Abrar Ahmed. He senses the charge and delivers a googly around leg. It's on the slower side and turns away a hint along with staying low. Michael Bracewell gives a premeditated charge, then gets into two minds. He tries to keep it away at the last moment but it's too late. The stumps are disturbed and New Zealand's idea to open with Bracewell flops. Will they still go after the target?
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Beaten! Lovely bowling as the batter is defeated all ends up while looking to drive.
Fuller and on off, swept through square leg for a single.
Fuller again around leg, Tom paddles it down to fine leg and the ball races away. Nauman gives the chase and stops it with his boot at the last moment. Saves one run.

Ouch, that would have hurt. Tossed up around off, Conway reverse-sweeps towards point where Abrar tries to stop but stretches a bit too much and seems to have hurt his groin. Nothing serious. They cross.
Another sweep shot, this time conventional from Latham and he sends it to deep square leg for a couple.
Flighted and around off, Latham walks forward and pushes it back. It's a bit aerial but doesn't carry to the bowler.
Quicker and outside off, Devon runs it down to third man for a single.
Flatter and quicker on middle, defended on the leg side.
Goes down on one knee and sweeps it aerially to deep backward square leg. Two taken.
Fires it on the pads, Latham eases it to deep square leg and picks another couple.
Five penalty runs! Loopy and full, down the leg side, Latham attempts to play the reverse sweep but misses. It goes through the legs of the keeper and hits the helmet kept behind on the ground.
Quicker and shorter on off, Latham punches off the back foot but finds point. 117 needed from the possible 72 balls.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Full and outside off, lofted down to wide long off. A single was taken as Imam quickly got to the ball.
Flighted on off, defended.
FOUR! Fine shot! Loopy and full, around off, Latham goes down and sweeps it sweetly through square leg for a boundary.
Tossed up and outside off, Latham tries to go over covers but fails to connect.
Around off, Latham plays an aerial sweep shot and it goes to deep square leg. Two more. 110 needed off possible 66 balls.
FOUR! Bang! Flighted delivery, around off, Devon Conway attacks it and drills it down the ground for a boundary at long off.
Quicker and around leg, defended back.
Full and outside leg, Conway reverse-sweeps it to deep point for a run.
FOUR! Well placed! Too full and around leg, Latham kneels down and nails it behind square leg. It beats the fielder near the fence and goes for a boundary. Sweep shot is working like a dream for Tom.
On the pads, helped to backward square leg for a run.

FOUR! Superb timing and execution. This is quality batting, 14 off the over. Conway goes down to fetch a full ball from outside leg and reverse-sweeps it with aplomb to the sweeper cover fence. 96 needed off 60 balls and Babar has a concerned look on his face.
FOUR! This one lands on leg, Tom Latham uses the pace of the ball and clips it over backward square leg for a boundary. Two fielders in the deep on the leg side and they failed to pick it up.
Slightly shorter one, Tom Latham drills it to mid on for a single.
Fuller and on off, Devon Conway looks to loft it but gets the inside half of the bat and the ball rolls towards long on. They cross.
SIX! All the way. A length ball around off, Tom Latham stays back to climb onto it and powers it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie. At the moment, everything is going wrong for Pakistan here! 50 up.
On a length with some extra bounce, Tom Latham looks to play at it but misses.
Fuller and on off, Tom Latham looks to drill it but doesn't connect well. It rolls towards mid off. They cross. 83 needed off 54 balls.
Slightly shorter one, Tom Latham guides it to backward point and rotates the strike.

On a length and around off, Devon Conway looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces off the deck. They collect a quick single asMir attacks the ball, turns but misses his shy at the bowler's end.
Fuller and on off, slower too. Tom Latham looks to loft it but gets the toe end of his bat. It lobs towards the vacant mid off region. They cross.

Full and on off, Devon Conway looks to heave it but gets an inside edge onto his knees as the ball rolls towards the gully region. They collect one and Conway is limping. That hit the unprotected area near the knee.
This one lands outside off, Tom Latham swings his bat at it but fails to connect.
Slightly shorter and outside off, Tom Latham looks to pull it but misses.
Around the wicket. On a length and on off, Devon Conway drills it towards long on for one.
On a length and on off, slower too. Tom Latham gently pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Bowls it wide outside off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
